title: ruth potts' pie crust
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Press into 9-inch pie tin and bake at 350° until crust is light brown.
Always flaky and delicious.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Bring soup to a boil.
Take gelatin with 1/4 cup water to dissolve.
Put cheese in bowl and add soup and gelatin.
Soften with beater.
Add mayonnaise, onions, celery and shrimp.
Stir before serving.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage with chopped onion and green pepper in skillet; drain.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Pour in casserole dish. Top with Cheddar cheese.
Put in oven; cook until brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Mix soup, milk and shredded cheese.
Pour over cooked vegetables.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Beat sugar, shortening, egg, milk and vanilla until smooth.
Add oats; mix well.

title: veal cordon bleu
directions: If using veal round steak, cut into 4 serving pieces.
Pound meat until 1/4-inch thick.
Place a slice of ham and cheese on each cutlet.
Roll up carefully, beginning at narrow end; secure rolls with wooden picks.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and allspice; coat rolls with flour mixture.
Dip rolls into egg; then roll into bread crumbs.
In large skillet, brown rolls in shortening, about 5 minutes.
Reduce heat and add water.
Cover; simmer 45 minutes or until tender.
Remove cover last 2 to 3 minutes to crisp rolls slightly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Spread sauerkraut in bottom of a 2-quart oblong casserole dish.
Sprinkle half of the caraway seed on sauerkraut.
Layer the corned beef slices, dressing, tomatoes, cheese, rye bread and rest of caraway seed.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Mix in remaining ingredients in order given.
Pinch off a small ball and pat out like a biscuit.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: grandma's chopped apple cake
directions: Cream oleo; add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs and beat 1 minute.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir into creamed mixture, then add remaining ingredients.
Stir just to mix well. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: haystacks(cookies)
directions: In top of double boiler, melt (only, do not let stiffen) the butterscotch morsels; add chow mein noodles and salted peanuts. Mix thoroughly.
Spoon small tablespoonful amount of mixture out onto wax paper.
Allow to harden.
Delicious!

title: "surprise" breakfast coffee cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, 2 teaspoons soft butter, cinnamon and crumbled fig bars; set aside.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs until frothy; beat in sugar and 1/3 cup melted butter until well combined.
Add vanilla and milk.
Beat in flour mixture until well combined.
Pour half of mixture into greased and lightly floured 9 x 9-inch pan.
Spread half of fig mixture over cake batter and top with remaining cake mixture and fig mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
(The blueberry and apple bars are good too!)

title: seville chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute chicken pieces in butter and olive oil until almost cooked through.
Transfer chicken to shallow baking dish.
To butter in skillet, add mandarin and lemon peel, 1/2 of the mandarin juice, lemon juice, and tarragon.
Cook and stir over low heat, gradually beat in the cream.
Beat in wines, add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook and stir just until thickened. Pour over chicken, sprinkle with paprika, bake for 30 minutes, or until chicken is done.
Cover with cheese and brown under broiler just before serving.
Serves 4.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Work dough together with hand and place on waxed paper.
Place another sheet of waxed paper on top, then roll out.
Put in pie plate and bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: old time gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Into large bowl, measure 1/2 cup boiling water and all ingredients. With mixer at low speed, beat until well blended, constantly scraping bowl with rubber spatula. Increase speed to high. Beat 2 minutes, occasionally scraping bowl. Pour batter into pan. Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour into pie shells. Chill at least 3 hours.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Combine first four ingredients until creamed, then add flour and salt until mixture sticks together.
Form into 1-inch balls and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400° until set, but not brown.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm, then roll again when cool.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except potato chip crumbs and grated cheese.
Place in greased, shallow casserole.
Sprinkle with potato chip crumbs and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: cousin ethel's oatmeal molasses bread
directions: Mix last five ingredients together and let cool until lukewarm. Add yeast mixture and add 2 cups sifted flour and 2 eggs.
Beat. Add enough flour to make a soft dough, about 3 1/2 or 4 cups. Grease top lightly.
Put in greased bowl.
Cover tightly and leave in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Take out.
Shape into 2 loaves. Cover and let rise until double in size.
Bake in moderate oven about 45 minutes.
This freezes well.

title: mark's spicy tea
directions: Boil gently for 10 minutes.
Add 1 cup hot milk.
Enjoy!

title: cool jello
directions: Mix the cottage cheese, Jell-O powder and Cool Whip together. Add fruit.
Drain canned fruits well before adding.
Then chill until set.

title: ham & broccoli hot dish
directions: Cook rice in water using the package directions.
Spread in a 2-qt. dish.
Layer ham and broccoli over rice.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter in a med skillet over med-hi heat.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk and mix well.
Cook, stirring continually, until thickened, about 4 minutes.
Pour sauce evenly over broccoli.
Melt remaining butter in a small saucepan.
Add bread crumbs and toss to coat.
Sprinkle over sauce.
Bake until hot and bubbly, about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with the Cheddar.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken and rice santa fe
directions: Saute onion and garlic until golden brown.
Add jalapeno pepper, chicken broth and picante sauce; simmer.
Add chicken and rice.
Simmer 5 more minutes.
Cook in skillet on stove or saute onion and garlic.
Mix everything together and put in oven.

title: german sweet chocolate pie
directions: Microwave chocolate and 2 tablespoons milk in large bowl on High until chocolate is almost melted (2 minutes).
Stir until completely melted.
Beat in cream cheese, sugar and remaining milk until well blended.
Refrigerate 10 minutes.
Stir in whipped topping gently until smooth.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours.
Garnish with chocolate shavings.

title: taco dip
directions: In a skillet, cook chopped meat.
Drain off fat.
Add package of taco seasoning and mix in.
Add 1/2 cup water; still have heat on low and mix in.
Turn off heat and add refried beans.
Put mixture in pan (being used) and let cool.
After mixture is cool, spread sour cream over top, then add chopped onion, shredded lettuce, chopped tomato, black olives and shredded cheese.

title: seven minute cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Pour into well-greased 10-inch pie plate.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
If in glass dish, lower heat to 300°.
Cool.
Top with canned cherries, strawberries, etc.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: With this dish, you put what you like on pizza.

title: herman sourdough bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, mix with Herman.
Add 4 cups flour, salt and sugar to yeast mixture.
Stir and cover.
Let rise until double in bulk, about 2 hours.
Add 1 cup flour and soda to risen mixture.
Knead in 1 cup more of flour until dough is smooth and not sticky.
Form dough into 1 large or 2 small loaves.
Place in greased pans.
Cover and let rise until double, about 1 1/2 hours.
Put in a shallow pan of water on bottom rack of oven.
Bake bread at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cream cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make into balls and roll in coconut.

title: frosty eggnog
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and salt.
Blend well.
Add milk; mix thoroughly.
Chill.
Pour into punch bowl.
Fold in whipped cream, add vanilla and dust with nutmeg.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and add water to make 3 cups of liquid. Mix with pudding mixes. Put in microwave. Cook 8 minutes on full power, stirring twice. Let cool. Add fruit and refrigerate.

title: cabbage and bows
directions: Cut raw cabbage into 1-inch strips.
Fry in bacon fat until browned lightly.
Boil egg bows and drain.
Mix all ingredients with 1 stick butter, then serve.

title: chocolate banana pudding pie
directions: Microwave chocolate, milk and butter in a medium, microwavable bowl on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds.
Stir chocolate until melted completely.
Spread evenly in crust. Refrigerate 30 minutes or until firm.
Arrange sliced bananas over chocolate.
Pour milk in large bowl.
Add pudding; beat with wire whisk for 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spoon over bananas in crust and top with Cool Whip.

title: microwave cheese sticks
directions: Cream butter and Cheddar cheese together.
Add other ingredients.
Pour onto well floured surface and roll out to about 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into thin strips and place on waxed paper. Microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: aunt mary's strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie crust and let cool completely.
Mix sugar and cornstarch together; add water.
Place over low heat and bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
Add Jell-O and cool.

title: plum tapioca cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Mix eggs (beaten), salad oil and baby food.
Blend.
Bake approximately 40 to 60 minutes (until springs back).

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except last 1/2 cup shredded cheese. Place in greased casserole pan.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This tastes like macaroni and cheese.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello according to package directions.
Pour into an 8 x 10 pan.
Chill until slightly thickened, add sliced bananas and pineapple chunks.
Let set until firm.

title: cornstarch finger paint
directions: Mix the cornstarch with the cold water first, until you have a smooth paste.
Stir in the boiling water.
Add a squirt of liquid detergent to make the paint easy to claen off things.
Color it with vegetable dye or tempra paint.
The dye will color your hands a little and could stain clothes too.
Let the finger paint cool before you use it.
Shelving paper, sunny side up, makes good finger paint paper.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O as directed on package in a 9 x 13-inch pan. When it starts to congeal, add blueberries and pineapple.
Let congeal and top with the following topping.

title: peggy's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except tomato sauce.
Shape into loaf.
Place in baking dish.
Pour tomato sauce over and bake in moderate oven until done.
You may add potatoes and carrots around outside of meat loaf when halfway done to make your meal complete.

title: orange brew
directions: Whip everything in large blender.

title: pineapple crunch
directions: Mix well together the pineapple, cheese, flour and sugar in casserole dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Pour on melted butter.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: potato-asparagus casserole
directions: Slice the potatoes and layer in baking dish.
Dice onions and put on top of potatoes, then add a layer of asparagus.
Dot with butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover tightly and bake at least 45 minutes until the potatoes are done.
Bake at 350° or at 400° to hurry it up!

title: spinach ricotta dumplings
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients, except flour.
Form into walnut-sized balls.
Roll lightly in flour.
Cover with waxed paper and chill or freeze, packed in layers with waxed paper between layers. Thaw, if frozen.
Boil water (salted).
Reduce to simmer.
Drop in half and cook until balls float to the surface (3 to 4 minutes).
Cook remaining balls and serve with tomato sauce. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: holiday surprise
directions: Place pineapple and juice in bowl.
Add pudding mix and blend thoroughly.
Fold in Cool Whip, marshmallows and pecans.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: leland's fat free apple pie
directions: Mix applesauce and graham crackers.
Let sit until crackers soften.
Add topping and serve.

title: "bishop's" special
directions: Fry tenderloin in oil until done.
Remove from pan.
Slice as for stir-fry.
Fry onion, mushrooms and green pepper until done; add meat, kidney beans, stewed tomatoes, garlic and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer on low for 30 minutes.
Put on top of cooked egg noodles.

title: mother's barbecue
directions: Saute ground beef and onion in large skillet.
Add chicken gumbo soup and water.
Add catsup and mustard, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chewy crackles
directions: Cream margarine, oil, sugars and eggs.
Add vanilla.
In a separate bowl, sift together flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Add to the creamed mixture.
Chill dough until firm at least 1 hour.

title: ima's prune cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil well.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg and cloves.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk to the egg and sugar mixture.
Add prunes and pecans.
Pour into oiled pan (12 x 15-inch).
Cook 45 minutes at 325°.

title: tropical fruit punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except orange slices.
Pour over ice in glasses.
Cut a slit halfway through orange slice and place on rim of glass for garnish and flavor.
Serves 14 (one-cup) servings.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Chop pepper, onion and celery; mix and brown.
Cook 2 packages egg noodles; drain and mix with mushrooms, tomato soup, tomato sauce, olives, hot sauce, salt, Worcestershire sauce and most of the cheese (save some cheese to sprinkle on top).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: santa fe soup
directions: Mix in large Dutch oven or crock-pot and simmer for 2 hours.

title: stephanie's fruit cake
directions: Mix baking powder, salt and flour.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time into butter/sugar mix, beating well after each one.
Stir in fruit. Mix well.
Lien pans with parchment and Crisco.
Pour batter in pans. Makes 3 or 4 loaves.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from pans.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Saute sausage and onion in skillet until sausage is done; drain.
Add sauerkraut and 2 tablespoons bread crumbs.
Combine cream cheese, parsley, mustard, garlic and pepper; stir in sauerkraut mixture.
Chill for 1 hour, then shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Coat balls with flour and dip in mixture of eggs and milk. Then coat balls with bread crumbs and deep fry until golden brown.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: In bowl beat together butter and powdered sugar.
Add milk and vanilla; beat until smooth and fluffy.

title: scalloped potatoes (high) - microwave
directions: Arrange half of the potatoes in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Combine flour and salt; sprinkle half over the potatoes.
Layer remaining potatoes and flour and salt.
Pour milk over; dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and microwave 11 to 12 minutes.
Turn dish after 5 1/2 minutes.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: batter for vegetables, fish
directions: Mix ingredients.
Dip vegetable or meat and fry.

title: applesauce cake
directions: In a bowl, cream the shortening until light.
Gradually beat in the sugars.
Beat in egg.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cocoa.
Stir vanilla into applesauce. Add sifted ingredients and applesauce alternately to the creamed mixture, mixing after each addition.
Add chopped nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Cool in pan on cake rack.
(Whipped cream topping is optional.)

title: date pudding
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in moderate oven for 30 minutes. Cool and cut in squares.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix all except biscuits together in a large bowl.
Pour into baking
pan
and cover completely with biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Slightly beat eggs; add milk, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in separate bowl.
Measure flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to liquid mixture and stir.
Fry in hot fat in frying pan by pouring a small portion into a funnel while moving funnel in a circular motion.
Drain and dust with 10x sugar.

title: baked crushed pineapple
directions: Blend eggs, flour, sugar and salt together. Add crushed pineapple and blend. Grease baking dish; pour mixture in. Sprinkle bread on top; pour melted butter over all. Bake 35 minutes in 350° oven. Number of Servings: 12.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits. Remove from heat; let cool for 10 minutes.	Add butter, milk and cheese. Stir in eggs, one at a time. Bake in greased casserole for 1 hour in 400° oven. Serves 6 to 8.

title: pudding dessert
directions: Mix flour and margarine like pie crust and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add 1/2 carton Cool Whip.
Cool crust, then spread with mixture.
Then mix pudding and milk for 2 minutes.
Pour on top of cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Mix thoroughly and toast in large pan in 250° oven for 2 hours.
Stir every 15 minutes. Keep in a tin box with a tight closing lid.
Three weeks is about the limit for freshness of taste.

title: madge's cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cool slightly.
Add the canned fruits and cream cheese.
You may also add nuts pieces, if desired.
Chill until firm.

title: candied carrots
directions: Melt butter and add brown sugar.
Heat until sugar dissolves completely.
Add carrots and cook over medium heat until all carrots are well glazed.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Whip cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add yogurt and mix until blended.

title: cajun cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand and bake in greased and floured 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch or flour and salt in the top of a double boiler; stir in cold milk.
Cook over boiling water until thickened, stirring constantly.

Cover and cook 15 minutes longer. Stir a little of the hot mixture into slightly beaten egg yolks. Add to remaining mixture in double boiler and cook for two minutes over hot, not boiling, water, stirring constantly.
Cool and add vanilla, then put in an 8-inch baked pie shell.
Spread meringue over filling and bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: sombrero dip
directions: Mix refried beans and taco sauce together.
Spread in 8 or 9-inch square baking dish.
Layer remaining in order.
Chill. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix and chill.
Shape into balls 3/4 to 1-inch in diameter. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
(Can freeze, thaw and cook.)

title: delicious red punch
directions: Combine all the juices.
Frozen juice is added as it comes from the can (the ginger ale dilutes it).
Stir in flavoring. Just before serving, add ginger ale.
If a bright red color is desired, add red food coloring.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Place bread in
bottom
of
9 x 13-inch pan.
Add diced chicken. Mix together eggs,
chicken broth, milk, salad dressing and salt.
Pour over bread and chicken.
Top with cheese, celery soup and bread crumbs. This may be covered and refrigerated overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: egg shrimp foo young
directions: Combine lemon peel, lemon juice, bean sprouts, celery, onions and shrimp.
Beat eggs and salt.
Add eggs to mixture.
Fry in hot oil in skillet, 1/4 cup of mixture at a time, until lightly brown, turning once.
Serve with soy sauce.

title: fiesta chicken by green giant
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet; cook chicken until no longer pink.
Stir in Pasta Accents and salsa.
Cover and reduce heat to medium.
Simmer 7 to 9 minutes until vegetables are crisp-tender. Stir occasionally.

title: chicken asparagus casserole
directions: Cut chicken into strips. Sprinkle with garlic salt and pepper. Heat oil and brown chicken. Cook asparagus according to directions. Stir together soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Place asparagus in single layer on bottom of shallow baking dish.
Place chicken over asparagus and spoon on sauce. Sprinkle on cheese. Cover with foil. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato and apple casserole
directions: Combine last three ingredients.
Layer half each of sweet potatoes and apples in an 8-inch square baking dish coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Sprinkle half of the cinnamon mixture over potatoes and apples, drizzle half of the melted butter over potatoes and apples.
Repeat procedure with remaining ingredients. Cover casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Check often.

title: spinach pie
directions: Mix and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Cream together the above and spread thin on a pizza pan (do not try to roll).
Just press with hands.
Bake at 325 degrees for about 15 minutes.
For the filling, blend 8 oz. cream cheese (softened) and 1/2 cup sugar.
Spread on cooled crust.
Drain 2 cups of frozen strawberries, retain and add enough water to make 1 cup liquid.
Combine liquid with 4 Tbsp. cornstarch.
Cook until thick and combine with strawberries.
Spread on top of cream cheese.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Separate and debone boiled chicken into small pieces.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix soup, sour cream and broth.
Pour on top of chicken.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Pour melted oleo over crackers.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and brown.
This makes a large casserole.

title: lazy daisy frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread evenly over Lazy Daisy Oatmeal Cake while cake is still warm.
Broil until frosting becomes bubbly.

title: swieback
directions: To raised sponge, add the cooled milk and some flour (about 1/3 cup).
Then add other ingredients and mix.
Let rise.
Knead and let rise again.
Knead and shape into swieback.
Let rise again (about 1 hour).

title: gooey butter cake
directions: *I use cherry chip or strawberry for a different flair.

title: crumb cake
directions: Sift dry
ingredients.	Mix
in
shortening
as for pie crust. Set aside 2 tablespoons of mixture.
Add egg, molasses and milk. May
add nuts and/or raisins.
Beat mixture together.
Place
in baking pan.
Sprinkle with dry mixture; bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Beat all together.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake until firm and brown.
Makes 1 large or 2 small pies.

title: golden punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except ginger ale.
Freeze until needed.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: beef casserole
directions: Combine and simmer 5 to 10 minutes the ground beef, salt, sugar, tomatoes, tomato sauce, garlic powder and pepper.
Cook noodles; drain and add to mixture of sour cream and cream cheese. Arrange in layers in greased casserole dish the meat mixture and noodle mixture.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Heat in 350° oven until cheese is melted and casserole is bubbling.

title: possum pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar and 1 tsp. vanilla.
Crush crackers, mix with egg whites and nuts.
Put in greased pie plate.
Bake at 325 degrees for 15 minutes.
Cool, cover with cool whip and add coconut.

title: bean pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan and cook on medium until thick.
Pour into already baked pie shell.
Serve cold or warm.

title: sausage pinwheels(appetizer)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together in a bowl.
Add shortening and blend with pastry blender.
Add milk; blend lightly until mixed.
Turn on floured board.
Knead about 20 strokes. Divide dough.
Place half on board.
Roll 1/4-inch thick into a rectangle.
Pat 1/2 pound sausage on top of dough.
Roll dough and sausage like a jelly roll.
Repeat with other half of dough and sausage.
Roll each in waxed paper and aluminum foil and refrigerate or freeze until needed.
When ready to bake, slice 1/4-inch thick with a sharp knife.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 425° until brown, approximately 10 minutes.

title: harvest loaf cake
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt and spices.
Cream the shortening in a large bowl; add sugar.
Cream at high speed until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs; beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with pumpkin; begin and end with dry ingredients. Blend well after each addition.
Stir in chocolate bits and nuts. Pour in greased loaf pan.
Bake 65 to 75 minutes at 350°.
Cool. Drizzle with glaze.
Let stand 6 hours.

title: cindi salad
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Do not add juices.
Ready to serve or may chill and eat.

title: cold oven cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Put in a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Put in cold oven and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil potato until well done; then mash and mix enough sugar with potato to make the mix thick enough to roll out flat. Sprinkle dough board with small amount of powdered sugar and roll potato mixture out flat.
Spread peanut butter over the potato mixture; roll slowly into a roll and wrap tightly in wax paper. Place in the refrigerator until roll is hard enough to slice.

title: chicken or turkey dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into a baking pan and bake at 400° until brown and crisp on top.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: One day prior to serving:
Peel eggplant; slice thin (in circles).
Layer slices in large bowl.
Every third or fourth row, sprinkle with salt.
When done, cover with saucer or plate and place heavy object on top to press (i.e., pitcher of water).
Let sit overnight.

title: almond chocolate biscotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mix at medium speed the sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add 1 cup flour and next 6 ingredients.
With mixer at low speed, beat until blended. Stir in remaining 1 1/2 cups flour, then add almonds.

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Split wings at each joint and discard tips; pat dry and cover. Deep-fry at 400°
(High) for 12 minutes or until completely cooked and crispy; drain.
Combine hot sauce and butter.
Dip wings in sauce to coat completely.
Serve with celery and Blue cheese dip. Makes 24 to 30 individual pieces.

title: mincemeat pie
directions: Mix well and put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 35 minutes at 375°.

title: blueberry dessert(can substitute other fruit.)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and spread on top of blueberry mixture.
Pour boiling water over all.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: texas hot trash
directions: Mix well and bake in a 225° to 250° oven for 1 1/2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: chicken vin rouge
directions: Boil chicken in water with salt and garlic powder.
Heat oil in saute pan.
Saute vegetables in oil until tender.
Cube cooked chicken and add to vegetables.
Cook until chicken is light golden.
Add wine and additional garlic powder; stir.
Cover, simmering, for 3 to 5 minutes.
Combine tomato sauce, cinnamon and sugar.
Add to chicken and vegetables.
Sprinkle with pepper and cornstarch, stirring until sauce creates a thick coating.
Serve alongside spaghetti or other pasta.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Boil together. Pour over the first mixture and let stand until cool. Refrigerate.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cook cornbread according to directions on package. Layer ingredients, beginning with crumbled cornbread, beans, corn, onion, pepper, tomato, dressing, cheese and bacon. Repeat as needed. If you use all the cornbread, you will need 2 cans of beans and 2 cans of corn.

title: black forest cake
directions: Combine flour, margarine and pecans; mix well.
Lay out in a 9 x 12-inch pan as crust; bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Soak Grape-Nuts in a little cold water, then add beaten egg yolks, sugar, raisins and milk.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Put into custard cups.
Whip egg whites; add 4 tablespoons sugar and brown in slow oven.
Serves 8.

title: sweet and zesty spareribs
directions: Place pork spareribs, meaty side up, on a rack in shallow roasting pan.
Roast, uncovered, in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours. Mix remaining ingredients.
Brush over pork, roasting, turning and brushing frequently with pineapple mixture until pork is done (approximately 45 minutes longer).
Use half the mixture for brushing, the remaining half of mixture heat to a boil and serve with pork as sauce.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour, salt and dash of white pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook quickly, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add cheese and stir until smooth.
This is great over broccoli or other cooked vegetables.

title: french cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add cream, cracker crumbs, nuts and chips.
Fill waxed paper cups, placed in tins, with mixture.
Bake at 375° for 10 or 12 minutes just so they are set.
Frost with melted plain chocolate bars.
Makes 80 to 90 cakes.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onions. Drain.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: corn-on-the-cob italiano
directions: Pull back corn husks; remove silk.
Drizzle each ear of corn with 1 tablespoon margarine.
Sprinkle with seasonings; replace husks.
Place on open grill over hot coals (coals will be glowing). Grill 30 minutes or until tender, turning occasionally.
Serve with remaining margarine.
Serves 4.

title: pineapple-lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and cool. Add other ingredients, mixing well. Pour into a small mold and refrigerate several hours or overnight. Makes 4 servings.

title: cranberry orange bread
directions: Combine sugar, egg, orange juice, orange rind and biscuit mix. Beat hard about 30 seconds. The dough will be lumpy. Stir in nuts and cranberries. Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350°. Test for doneness with a toothpick. Remove from pan. Cool before slicing.

title: feather cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add milk and flavors.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Last fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Frost with your favorite icing.

title: party mix
directions: Melt butter; stir in seasoning salt and Worcestershire sauce. Add mix and stir until covered.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Press rolls into crust (9-inch pan); sprinkle with nuts.
Add zucchini that has been sauteed with seasoning.
Pour well beaten (fluffy) eggs over the zucchini.
Top off with the grated cheese. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Keep checking.

title: olive cheese balls
directions: Mix with fork the cheese, oleo, flour and cayenne pepper; when ingredients are well blended, roll dough around pimento-stuffed olive.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 85 balls.

title: mexican hot sauce
directions: Place tomatoes, garlic, oil, salt and pepper in blender.
Mix well.
Place in a boiler and bring to a boil.
Simmer over low heat for 15 minutes.
Cool and serve with chips or place in jars.

title: eagle brand milk(condensed milk)
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and mix.
Use in any recipe that calls for condensed milk.

title: better than nintendo
directions: Bake cake by directions in oblong pan.
Let it cool some. Punch holes into cake with the end of a wooden spoon.
Fill holes with Eagle Brand cream.
Pour caramel topping next.
Then spread Cool Whip over the cake.
Then grate Snickers bars (3) over top. Then cover and chill for several hours.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Mix together first 2 ingredients; set side.
Combine all remaining ingredients (except flour) with the softened yeast.
Add flour to rest of ingredients to form a stiff dough, beating well after each addition.
Let rise in a warm place until doubled in size (50 to 60 minutes).

title: heavenly apple salad(refreshing fresh fruit flavor.  tasty dressing.)
directions: Sprinkle gelatin into a 9 x 13-inch dish; add boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted. Stir in cold water.
Refrigerate until gelatin thickens.
Fold apples, pecans and pineapple into thickened mixture.
Refrigerate until set.

title: chicken pie
directions: Simmer chicken with salt and pepper in enough water to cover until tender. Debone and skin pieces. Cut into small pieces and spread evenly in a 12 x 9-inch pan.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs into pie mix and spread on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Pour melted margarine on top of cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Garnish with whipped topping if desired.

title: a recipe for making a great principal!
directions: Blend In: A generous helping of a good sense of humor and a lot of being a good sport.

title: punch
directions: Mix well and serve over ice.
If it tastes too strong, dilute to taste with water if you are serving it immediately.
If prepared ahead of time, add ice to chill.
As this melts, it will dilute the mixture.
It is wise to add the ginger ale right before serving.
It makes the punch bubblier.

title: vanilla sugar
directions: Combine sugar and vanilla bean.
Place in shaker.
Cover tightly to preserve vanilla aroma.
Shake on desserts, etc. and serve.

title: garden egg salad
directions: Combine ingredients together.
Cover and chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well after each one.
Add milk and flour; add coconut.
Bake in 9-inch pie plate at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes one pie.

title: strawberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place paper liners in 20 muffin cups. Stir the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon together in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center of the flour mixture.
Add the milk, eggs and butter to the well and stir quickly just to combine.
Add the berries and sugar; stir quickly again just to combine.
Spoon the batter into the muffin cups, filling almost to the top.
Bake until brown and crusty, about 20 minutes.
Makes 20 muffins.

title: parmesan roll-ups
directions: Trim crusts from bread.
Flatten each piece with a rolling pin. Spread each slice thinly with Cheez Whiz (don't glob).
Roll each piece like a crescent roll.
Dip quickly in melted butter (use tongs).
Roll in grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, until lightly brown.
Cut each in half before serving.
For later use, freeze immediately on tray.
When partially frozen, cut in halves.
Store in freezer bags.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake for 20-25 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp cocktail sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: corned venison(for 100 pounds meat)
directions: Boil spices in one pint of water.
Combine all ingredients and mix well before adding meat.
Can adjust to half for less meat. Meat should be submerged.
A plate with weight on top works.
It takes 10 days to cure if pieces weigh 2 to 4 pounds each; up to 16 days if pieces weigh
6 to 8 pounds.

title: chocolate nut squares(cioccolato noci quadro)
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Place shortening and sugar in saucepan;
melt.
When
slightly
melted, place in mixing bowl and add
eggs, beating after each addition.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into lightly greased
x
13-inch pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes. Cut into 24 squares when cooled.

title: chili bean dip
directions: Melt cheese in microwave.
Add chili and olives.
Heat through.
Stir and enjoy.
Serve with corn chips.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Soak beans overnight or boil 2 minutes and soak 1 hour.
Add salt; boil gently 45 minutes.
Drain and save.
Fry sausage until brown; mix all ingredients.
Place layer of beans, then layer of sausage and top with layer of beans.
Bake 15 minutes in oven of 400°.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Make cream cheese into ball, mixing in all ingredients.
Serve with crackers.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together in large baking dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over top and bake at 350° until golden brown.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: aunt hazel's sugared pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water until soft peaks are formed. Add pecans and mix well. Combine sugar, vanilla and salt in a separate bowl. Add pecans to mixture and mix well. Spread in an ungreased cookie sheet and bake approximately 1 hour at 250°. Stir the pecans half way through the cooking time and begin checking for doneness at 50 minutes by tasting. Cooking too long will cause a scorched taste.

title: julie's favorite pancakes
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Beat in melted butter and sugar.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add this to creamed mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Fold in beaten egg whites with a spoon.
Bake on heated griddle.

title: vegetable salad dressing
directions: Combine yogurt or sour cream and Blue cheese in a small saucepan.
Warm over low heat for 1 to 2 minutes, whisking constantly, just until the Blue cheese has melted.

title: frosted cran-orange salad muffins
directions: Sprinkle cranberries with sugar, set aside. Peel 2 oranges, chop up and set aside. Squeeze the other oranges to make 2/3 cup of juice. Combine the juice, cream cheese, and vanilla. Beat until fluffy. Stir in chopped oranges, cranberries, apples and dates. Set aside.

Whip cream until soft peaks form. Fold into cream cheese mixture. Spoon mixture into muffin pans lined with paper baking cups. Cover and freeze until firm. To serve, remove paper cups and place on top of firm lettuce leaves. Garnish with whipped topping.

title: fat free bran muffins
directions: Mix cereal and milk; put aside.
Stir flour, sugar, salt and baking powder; set aside.
Add egg, yogurt, applesauce and banana or raisins to cereal mixture; mix well.
Add flour mixture, stirring only until all ingredients are moist.
Bake in muffin tins about 20 minutes or until golden brown at 400°.

title: pork steak hot dish
directions: Cut pork steak into small pieces and brown in skillet.
Saute green pepper as desired with meat.
Simmer meat and green pepper in small amount of water for approximately 45 minutes.
Add soup and cook 10 to 15 minutes longer adding enough water to keep like a sauce or gravy.
Add noodles, season to taste and serve.

title: hors d'oeuvres or tv snacks(onion pie)
directions: Together smother bacon, onions and butter.
Do not cook onions completely done (cool).
Mix eggs, flour and milk, beat lightly. Now
combine everything and fill pie shell.
Bake at 400° until custard is set and the surface has a golden hue.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon together.
Combine eggs, oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini in a large bowl.
Beat well.
Stir in the flour mixture until smooth. Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour mixture into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 40 minutes or until center springs back when lightly pressed with fingertips.

title: whiskey chicken wings
directions: Heat first 6 ingredients in saucepan.
Pour over chicken wings.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours, basting wings often. You can save leftover sauce for next batch if you want.
Keep a lot of napkins handy; wings should be real sticky.

title: appetizer tray
directions: Arrange vegetables, cheese and ham on tray with dip and crackers at side.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Put pineapple in bottom of cake pan. Pour pie filling over pineapple. Put cake mix on top of pie filling. Pat dough oleo slices over entire top.
Sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk to soft ball stage.
Have remaining ingredients ready in large mixing bowl.
Add cooked syrup mixture and mix well.
Pour in buttered dish and let cool.

title: easy deep dish pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch) or cookie sheet.
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms.
Pat dough on bottom and up sides of pan with floured hands.
Or roll into rectangle, 13 x 10-inch, and place on cookie sheet.
Pinch edges of rectangle, forming 3/4 inch rim.

title: baked picnic ham
directions: Soak ham in cold water for approximately 1 hour.
After soaking, wash ham real well.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Add 2 cups water and ham.
Bake for approximately 3 1/2 hours, or until done. During the last 30 minutes of cooking, mix mustard and syrup together.
Baste it all over ham; finish cooking for about 25 minutes.

title: molasses pecan pie
directions: Place pastry in pie plate; prick bottom and press sides with fork.
Crimp edges.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: First, lay on a large platter, jalapeno bean dip.
Second, peel, pit and mash avocados.
Stir in lemon juice, salt and pepper and spread for next layer.
Third, mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Fix the remaining ingredients in layers.
Serve with round tortilla chips or Tostitos.
This is great for parties.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into bite size pieces.
Mix dressing and toss with broccoli.
Crumble bacon on top.

title: pineapple-lime salad
directions: May add some Cool Whip.

title: chicken philippine style
directions: Marinate chicken in remaining ingredients for about 30 minutes.
Can be done in skillet to be used for cooking.
Heat on top of stove until it boils, cover and simmer about 40 minutes or until almost all liquid has evaporated.
Serve hot or cold.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Drain pineapple well.
Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Form in a shape of a ball. Serve on platter with party rye or crackers.

title: crab spread
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water and mix in to the soup.
Heat mixture until gelatin dissolves.
Add soup mixture to cheese and stir. Stir in chopped onion, celery and crab.
Pour in to a mold and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add next 4 ingredients. Mix lightly but well.
In a separate bowl, mix dry ingredients, then add to first mixture, mixing well.
Add nuts and divide batter into two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until done.
Remove from pans at once.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Mix together, bake until bubbly at 350°.
Serve with crackers or nacho chips.

title: chocolate brownies(in 3 steps)
directions: Mix well all the ingredients and set aside.

title: quick broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Cut broccoli in small pieces using the more tender parts of the stems, also.

Place in deep saucepan. Cover broccoli with water. Bring to a boil. Turn flame down to simmer. Add bouillon cubes. Stir flour and milk together, then add to pan. Add 1/8 teaspoon pepper and stir while adding shredded Cheddar cheese. Stir until melted. Serve.
Serves 6.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil peeled and cut potatoes until tender. Drain and cool. Add all of the other ingredients.
Mix well.

title: beef and bacon delight
directions: Cut franks in half. Wrap a slice of bacon around each frank half. Secure with toothpicks. In crock-pot, place a layer of wrapped franks and a layer of brown sugar. Cover and cook slowly for 2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: ba ba beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Drain and place in a casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients, stir and top with bacon pieces.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sunflower waldorf salad
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine apples, sunflower nuts, grapes and celery.
Fold in yogurt and banana.
Serve on individual lettuce lined leaves.

title: easy sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger meat. Add soup and salsa. Heat through. Top with cheese. Serve on bun.

title: key lime cheesecake
directions: Beat softened cream cheese with sugar until fluffy.
Blend in lime juice until smooth.
Add food coloring and blend.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: lime jello pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and 1 tablespoon drained pineapple juice together until smooth and creamy.
Fold in Cool Whip. Spread mixture into prepared and cooled pie shell.
Mix jello according to package.
Add drained pineapple to jello and refrigerate until thickened.
Spread thickened jello mixture over first mixture in pie shell and chill.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix well and drop by spoon on greased cookie sheets.

title: light lemony angel cake
directions: Beat pudding and skim milk according to package directions. Fold in lemon yogurt until blended.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together, then add eggs and pumpkin. In another bowl, mix flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Stir into pumpkin mixture, then add oats, nuts and chocolate chips.
Spoon 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: tropical punch
directions: Combine in order.
Add ginger ale just before serving. Garnish with orange and lime slices.
Makes 30 to 35 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add fruit, nuts and sugar to slightly thickened jello.
Blend all together and chill until thick.

title: substitute for eagle brand milk
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender, adding boiling water last. Blend until creamy.

title: chicken in raspberry-vinegar sauce
directions: Dredge chicken in flour and lightly saute in oil and butter. Remove chicken and set aside.
Deglaze pan with raspberry wine vinegar; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add chicken stock. Return chicken to pan and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove chicken (keep warm).
Bring liquid to a boil reducing liquid until it has the consistency of cream.
Reduce heat to medium.
Add cream and allow to thicken.
Pour over chicken or serve along side.

title: cheese ball
directions: Finely chop pecans.
Combine cream cheese, pineapple, green pepper, onion juice, salt and 1 cup pecans.
Shape into ball; roll in 1 cup of pecans.

title: sugar cookie frosting
directions: Mix powdered sugar and margarine.
Stir in vanilla and milk. Beat until smooth. Color, if desired.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and eggs and then flour.
Chill overnight.
Can be rolled out or make logs and slice.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: nanny kessell's cooked frosting
directions: Over low heat, combine milk and cornstarch.
Stir constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat and allow to cool completely. In a large bowl, combine sugar, Crisco, margarine and salt.
Mix until smooth.
Add cooked mixture by small amounts to the creamed mixture.
Mix on high for 10 minutes.
Add vanilla and mix well.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain spinach well, set aside.
Combine soup mix, sour cream and mayonnaise; mix well.
Add spinach, stirring well.
Chill 2 hours.
Stir before serving.
Good dip for sourdough bread pieces.

title: kluski noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed, adding 1 tablespoon olive oil so they will not be sticky.
Drain; set aside.
Brown meat with salt and garlic to taste.
Mix sour cream, cream cheese and chilies together.
In lightly greased casserole, layer ingredients:
meat, sour cream mixture, noodles, green onions, ending with Ragu on top. Cook in a 350° oven until bubbly, about 30 minutes.
This dish was often served at Guild luncheons.
Good and easy.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt butter, cocoa and milk in a saucepan on low.
Add sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Mix well and pour into a prepared pie crust. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until firm.
Makes a delicious fast dessert for chocolate lovers!

title: pineapple crisp
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Form balls and roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: baked fried chicken
directions: Brown chicken in butter and shortening.
The pieces may be floured, if you wish.
Fry until well brown.
Transfer to oven and continue baking until done at 350°.

title: italian corn
directions: Mix
all ingredients together and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally, adding reserved liquid if mixture is too dry.

title: scalloped apples
directions: Pare, core and slice the apples.
Place in a buttered casserole and add the cinnamon, salt, lemon juice and water.
Work the sugar, flour and butter together until crumb-like in consistency.
Spread this over the apples and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chocolate cream fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and butter.
Bring to a boil for 7 1/2 to 8 minutes (no longer).
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat; add chips and stir until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into buttered pan.
Let cool and cut into squares.
Makes 5 pounds and keeps indefinitely.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and chop eggplant.
Cook until done in small amount of water.
Beat 1 egg; add 1 teaspoon dried onion or tablespoon of fresh onion.
Break up 8 to 10 crackers.
Mix all with eggplant. Break up 4 slices American cheese or equal amount of Cracker Barrel cheese (sharp).
Mix 3 slices of cheese and 2 tablespoons milk with eggplant.
Arrange pieces of 4th slice of cheese on top of casserole.
Bake in greased casserole, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: flintstone dip
directions: Cut out the center of the bread, about 1-inch from edge and bottom.
Put mixture of remaining ingredients in center of bread. Break up bread you cut out.
Use to dip with.
Eat the bowl and enjoy.

title: brownie frosting
directions: Blend butter, cocoa and vanilla in small bowl. Add sugar and 1 tablespoon of the milk. Gradually beat in rest of milk, possibly adding more until of frosting consistency. Spread over cooled brownies.

title: chicken pie
directions: Stew chicken; debone, cube and place in baking dish.
Combine soup with broth; pour mixture over chicken.
Mix flour, buttermilk and butter; pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: famous chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Mix sugar and flour together. Chop up nuts and all other ingredients together. Pour into graham cracker pie crust and bake 1 hour. Make sure top is golden brown. Cool completely before cutting.

title: baked crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese well.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Thoroughly combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Pour into greased crock-pot.
Cover and cook on high for 1 hour, then turn to low for 4 to 5 hours.

title: orange julius
directions: Put all ingredients into large blender and blend on high speed until smooth.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into hot greased skillet.
Bake at 400° for approximately 45 minutes.
(Check after 30 minutes.) Insert knife in middle to check for doneness.

title: boiled custard
directions: Beat egg yolks until they almost look cooked.
Heat milk, but never boil.
Add eggs and sugar to milk.
Let come TO A BOIL. Never boil.
Add flavoring.
Cool in a pan of cool water.
Stir. Store in refrigerator.
Will keep several days.
Remember to use fresh milk.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: lentil soup
directions: Rinse lentils and add all ingredients.
Bring to boiling, reduce heat, cover and simmer 45 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Whip in medium bowl until blended.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 325° for one hour.
Fix in 9 x 14-inch cake pan.
Feeds lots.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Drain hominy.
Cook mushroom soup on low heat, put in cheese. Add tomatoes and hominy.
Pour into baking dish.
Cover with corn chips and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: toffee cream royale cake
directions: Variation: Use chocolate instant pudding. In place of coffee, use few drops peppermint extract.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add egg yolks.
Mix separately the flour, soda and salt.
Then add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add melted chocolate, then fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake in three 9-inch pans, about 35 minutes at 350°. Cool before icing.

title: beef-vegetable soup
directions: Place soup meat and bones in large pot of cold water; bring to a boil and skim off the scum which comes from the meat and bones. Then cut up the soup vegetables in small pieces and add to meat and bones.
Add the can of crushed tomatoes and seasonings.
Cook for 2 hours.
Serve cooked egg noodles in soup.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.

title: a quick candy cookie
directions: Melt bits in double boiler.
Stir in noodles and peanuts. Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients, then other ingredients.
Use 6 or 7 small aluminum pans.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Makes great gifts for Christmas.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar	until
light
and
fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add
vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Roll and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: oyster stew (chesapeake)
directions: Cook bacon crisp; drain.
Cook onions and celery in bacon fat. Drain.
Brown oysters in pan, a drop.
Add juice and let the edges just curl.
Warm milk to almost simmer; add tapioca powder. Let it expand to a gelatinous mass. Pour oysters, juice and vegetables in.
Check for salt.
Put crumbled bacon on top; dust with saffron.
Add butter.

title: cheesy sausage biscuits
directions: Crumble sausage in large skillet.
Add onion and cook over medium heat until brown.
Drain well. Combine all ingredients. Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Drop batter by heaping teaspoons about 2 inches apart on a lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender; remove from bone and cut into small pieces.
In chicken broth, cook onion and celery until tender; add broccoli and cook 8 to 10 more minutes.
Drain.
Empty soup into pan.
Add cheese and melt over low heat.
When melted, stir in drained pimentos and chicken.
In casserole dish, add layer of chicken, sauce, vegetables, half of stuffing and rest of vegetables.
Layer chicken and stuffing over the top.
Dab with butter and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: glazed strawberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar in heavy saucepan.
Add water gradually, stirring until smooth.
Add lemon juice.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and clear. Add enough food coloring to make sauce ruby red.
Cool sauce completely.
Halve or slice berries and add to sauce and stir gently until well coated.
Put into shell and cover with Cool Whip.

title: cream fudge
directions: Melt cream cheese in a double boiler over low heat (do not let cheese cook).
Add the powdered sugar, a little at a time.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Place in a buttered pan; chill.
(For chocolate, add desired amount of cocoa.)

title: broccoli-zucchini soup
directions: Add a lot of broccoli flowerets and cubed zucchini chunks in 1 quart water with chicken bouillon or 1 quart chicken broth.
Cook until tender.
Add soup and cheese.
Reduce heat and stir until cheese melts.
(I've also made this soup using broccoli only.)

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift flour and dry ingredients into bowl.
Make a well and add all remaining ingredients.
Mix together until smooth.
Pour into 3 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: nut brittle
directions: Stir together sugar, water and syrup in a 2 quart casserole. Microwave on High (100%) for 12 to 14 minutes or until bubbly. Stir in nuts.
Microwave on High (100%) for 4 to 6 minutes or until light brown.
Stir coconut and vanilla into syrup.
Microwave on High (100%) for an additional 1 to 2 minutes or until hard crack stage is reached.
Add baking soda.
Stir until light and foamy. Pour mixture onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Spread to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cool.
Break into pieces.
Recipe yields 1 pound.

title: spun honey
directions: Beat all ingredients together with electric mixer.
Store in refrigerator.

title: fresh basil tomato sauce for pasta
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil.
Add basil and cook for 1 minute. Add tomatoes, salt and pepper and let simmer for 15 minutes until tomatoes are soft.
Makes a chunky tomato sauce for 4 servings. Pour over linguine or spaghetti.
Add Parmesan cheese.

title: lemon crunch
directions: Cream the cream cheese and gradually add powdered sugar; set aside.
Mix 1 teaspoon vanilla and Cool Whip.
Add that to the cheese mixture.
Spread over crust and chill.
Spread lemon pie filling over top.
Then spread sour cream mixed with 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla (mix well and pour over lemon filling).
Chill.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: In flat 2-quart baking dish, press cream cheese in bottom of dish.
Top with 1 can beans.
Layer chiles on top of beans.
Layer other can of beans on top of chiles.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven until heated through and cheese melts or microwave on High about 15 minutes.
Serve warm with nachos.

title: eggplant in oven
directions: Peel and slice eggplant.
Mix mayonnaise, salt and onion and spread on sliced eggplant.
Mix remaining ingredients and roll eggplant slices in mixture to cover.
Place in 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pasta al pesto(makes 4 servings)
directions: Brown quickly on both sides and place in a baking dish.
Pour undiluted cream of celery soup over the chops.
Bake 45 minutes to an hour at 350°.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Deep fry pork cubes until brown; remove from oil.
Mix all ingredients, except cornstarch and green pepper.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 30 minutes, or until meat is tender.
Mix cornstarch and 1/4 cup cold water; add to pork mixture with green pepper. Boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Serve over rice or alone.
Serves 8.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs, pumpkin and vanilla. Beat well.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 75 minutes. Makes 2 loaves.

title: persimmon pudding(uncooked)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into a roll and place on oil paper.
Sprinkle with more cracker crumbs.
Wrap oil paper around roll.
Cool and slice.
May be frozen.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Sprinkle rice in buttered casserole dish.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Mix soup, water and bouillon cubes and bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken and rice.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours, covered.
Uncover and continue baking for 30 minutes.

title: zesty chicken taco rice salad
directions: Cook and stir chicken in hot oil in large skillet until lightly browned.
Add broth, tomato sauce, and seasoning mix. Bring to a full boil, stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes, fluff with fork.
Serve with cheese and chips.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook in crock-pot for 4 hours on simmer.

title: carnation freezer cake
directions: Whip milk, sugar and lemon juice until stiff.
Put a layer of crumbs in a pan, then a layer of whipped topping.
Repeat layers, ending up with crumbs.
Freeze.

title: rice pudding
directions: Place rice in a strainer and pour the boiling water over rice. Drain well. Steep 1 hour or until all is thick and creamy. Stir in butter, sugar, almond extract, nutmeg and almonds. Serve warm or chilled with whipped cream.

title: mashed potatoes with cream cheese
directions: Boil potatoes 20 to 25 minutes or until tender; drain.
In a large bowl of electric mixer, combine potatoes with all other ingredients.
Beat until creamy and smooth.
Spoon into buttered microwave dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: tuna waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle apple with lemon juice; combine with remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix together and shape into balls.
Fry in a small amount of oil until brown.
Pour off fat.
Add 1 can of mushroom soup and 1 can water.
Mix and pour over meat.
Turn to low and cook 30 minutes.

title: manicotti
directions: Combine Ricotta cheese, half of Mozzarella cheese, sugar, eggs, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Fill the uncooked Manicotti shells, using paring knife to fill.
Pour half of sauce (below) in bottom of dish.
Put in shells in single layer.
Cover with other half of sauce.
Cover with foil and place in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove foil.
Sprinkle with remaining half
of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream(for six quart freezer)
directions: Put 1 quart of milk on stove and simmer.
Beat eggs in bowl with mixer very well.
Add flour and cornstarch (and cocoa).
Put in 1 cup sugar gradually to egg mixture.
Beat (will get creamy). Add this gradually to hot milk on stove.
Stir until it comes to a boil.
It will get thick.
Add 1 1/2 cups sugar, another quart of milk and cream to freezer.
Use ice around and put rock salt around top and freeze.

title: cheddar cheese quiche
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; crumble.
Drain and reserve drippings. Cook onion in drippings until transparent.
Combine milk, eggs, 1/4 cup cheese, salt, pepper, parsley, sugar, nutmeg and red pepper in mixing bowl.
Stir in bacon and onion.
Pour into pie shell land sprinkle with remaining cheese, then with paprika. Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine, chill and serve.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, mandarin oranges with their juice, oil and eggs.
Beat with an electric mixer.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Turn batter into pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: heavenly chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir cake mix and cocoa.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until blended.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan or two 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool and frost.

title: candied fruit slices
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in chopped pecans and cherries.
Chill for 1 hour or more.
Divide dough in thirds. Shape into rolls, about 10-inches long.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill about 3 hours.
Cut into 1/8-inch slices.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 12 to 15 minutes in 325° oven until lightly browned.
Cool on wire rack.
Yields about 70 cookies.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray casserole dish with Pam.
In Tupperware bowl, combine bread crumbs, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Wash and pat dry the chicken parts.
Dip chicken into melted margarine, and place in bowl with crumb mixture.
Cover tightly and shake to cover chicken.
Arrange in baking dish. Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture and pour remaining butter over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Mix jello and let set until it begins to jell.
Beat jello and cream cheese; stir in Cool Whip, nuts and well drained pineapple. Pour into mold and let set up.

title: paul newman cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions.
When done, remove from oven and poke holes in top of cake.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over the cake.
Allow to cool.
Spread caramel topping on cake.
Top with Cool Whip.
Break up Heath bars and sprinkle on top.
Refrigerate.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: mama's cornbread dressing
directions: Mix crumbled cornbread, stuffing mix, onions, parsley, salt, pepper, celery soup and well beaten eggs together with enough broth to make it rather soupy.
Bake at 375° to 400° for about an hour or until done and brown.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Mix ingredients and put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: sweet potato pie(my mother-in-law's recipe)
directions: Mix all and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: susan bars
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, cream sugars and shortening.
Add and mix well eggs, vanilla, flour and rolled oats.
Spread in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes (until top is a nice brown and has pulled away from the sides a little).
Melt chocolate bits and spread over hot base.
Sprinkle with shredded coconut or chopped walnuts or pecans. Let cool before cutting into squares.

title: cherry pecan quick bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan. In a large bowl, combine butter, sugar and eggs; beat with mixer until creamy. Add soda, salt, flour and buttermilk. Mix on low until blended. Fold in vanilla, cherries and nuts. Bake 60 minutes.

title: kate kirby's butterscotch squares
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar.
Beat well.
Cool.
Add eggs and blend well.
Add flour, flavorings, coconut and nuts.
Spread on greased cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients
well.
Pour
into	a large greased casserole. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8 well.

title: pop rouge ice cream
directions: Pour into freezer bucket by alternating, first with evaporated milk, then pop, then Eagle Brand until all containers have been emptied.
Freeze in hand or electric ice cream maker.
Let stand for a 1/2 hour before serving.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: In bottom of an 8 1/2-quart punch bowl, crumble half the cooked, cooled cake.
Layer 1/2 pudding, 1/2 crushed pineapple, 1 can pie filling, 1 carton whipped topping and 1 cup pecans. Repeat process using remaining ingredients in the same order. Chill 24 hours.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Put butter in a pan; then layer asparagus, cheese, pimiento and soup.
Dot with butter, salt and pepper.
Put in oven at 400° and let come to bubble, 20 to 40 minutes.
Take out of oven and sprinkle with corn flake crumbs.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter and pour over top.
Put in oven for a few minutes.

title: baked raccoon with vegetables
directions: Soak the raccoon in a vinegar and water solution for about 1 hour.
Drain and cut into serving size pieces.
Salt and pepper the pieces and cover with water in a boiler.
Add garlic and bay leaves and boil until meat is partly tender.
Remove meat and brown in a roasting pan.
Add a little flour to the pan drippings and mix in enough water to make a thin gravy.
Place the vegetables in the pan and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until meat and vegetables are tender.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream sugars, vanilla and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Add chips and nuts.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 9 minutes.
Watch carefully!

title: caesar salad with sourdough croutons(6 servings)
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients in blender or processor.
With machine running, gradually add oil in thin steady stream.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: beer dip
directions: Bring all ingredients to room temperature and blend well.

title: cheesy new potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes.
Slice 1/4 inch slices.
Cook in boiling salt water.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 2 quart casserole dish. Place layer each of potatoes, cheese, bacon, potatoes, cheese and bacon.
Pour on half of butter.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Repeat.
Heat in oven 15 minutes.

title: mary jane's coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and vanilla until smooth, add eggs and beat well.
Add flour mixture alternately with sour cream and beat well.
Put batter in well greased pans (2 loaf pans or 1 angel food cake pan),
swirl filling through the batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 30 minutes and remove from pans.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water. Add sliced bananas, pineapple with juice and strawberries.
Pour half of the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Set in refrigerator until firm (1 hour).
Beat cream cheese, sour cream and sugar.
Pour over Jell-O mixture. Add remaining Jell-O mixture. Chill until firm.

title: tropical crumble
directions: Spread pie filling evenly in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over pie filling.
Drizzle melted butter over cake mix.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or until it springs back at touch.
Serve warm or cool with whipped cream.
Serves 9 to 12.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and Crisco for 8 minutes or until very fluffy.
Add eggs, vanilla and flour.
Mix very well.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick comes out clean.
Frost with Lemon Glaze.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat; simmer about 20 minutes or until noodles are done and celery is tender.
(Celery may be sauteed in a little butter before combining with other ingredients.)

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Place frozen yeast rolls in Bundt pan.
Melt the margarine and pour over rolls.
Sprinkle with butterscotch pudding.
Mix together the cinnamon, crushed pecans and sugar, then pour over rolls.
Cover with towel and let stand overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach and cheese squares
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs.
Add flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Add cheese and spinach, mixing well. Spread into pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool 30 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares.
Makes 40 squares.
These freeze well in plastic bags.

title: turkey balls with tomato sauce
directions: Empty all canned tomatoes into large top of stove pot.
Add paste can of water and, as mixture is cooking, mix thoroughly. Let cook until it begins to bubble on top.
Put turkey into large bowl.
Add onion, salt, pepper, bread crumbs, mixed with ketchup, and 2 ice cubes with a little water to moisten.
Add Egg Beaters, garlic and 1/2 of the Italian herbs.
Mix thoroughly either with fork or hands.
Let stand for about 1/2 hour in order to have crumbs absorb moisture.

title: chocolate star cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream shortening, peanut butter and sugars until smooth.
Add egg, milk and vanilla to shortening mixture; blend well.
Gradually blend in dry ingredients.
Shape into balls and roll in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for eight minutes at 375°.
Take out of oven, press chocolate stars in center of cookies and bake for another 2 minutes.

title: barley soup
directions: Soak the barley in cold water to cover for 12 hours.
Drain. Melt butter in a large skillet and saute the bacon, onion, celery and shallot until it is translucent.
Pour in the broth and bring to a boil.
Add the barley and cook until tender, about 1 hour. Pour the soup into a tureen, sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: strawberry dream cake or cherry
directions: Cook jello, cornstarch and water until thick.
Add sugar to this mixture.
Drain strawberries and add water to make 1 cup. Let cooked mixture cool and get thick.
Add strawberries or cherry pie filling.
Whip Dream Whip with milk.
Whip together cream cheese and 1/2 cup milk.
Mix together cream cheese and Dream Whip.
Make a 9 x 13-inch graham cracker crust or butter and flour and spread in pan and bake.
I have to use a small amount of water and a little more flour to have enough to press up sides of dish. Let cool.
Put a layer of white filling (about 1/2) on crust. Add red mixture and top with white mixture.
I put cracker crumbs on top.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: senate bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight in 1-quart water, or for quick soak bring beans and water to boil for 2 minutes.
Cover and let stand 1 hour. After soaking, drain beans and measure liquid.
Add enough more water to make 2 quarts.
Place beans, water and ham hocks in kettle.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Add potato, onion, celery and garlic.
Simmer 1 hour longer.
Remove ham hock and cut up meat. Remove 1 cup beans and some liquid; puree in blender and return to soup.
Heat.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with parsley (optional).

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions, drain.
Add tomatoes, onion, and all of the soups and cook
until bubbly.
In a
9 x 13 inch casserole dish place a layer of meat mixture, a layer of Doritos and repeat layers until all of the meat mixture is used.
Put cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: udderly fantastic milk punch
directions: Mix in punch bowl the softened ice cream and fruit juices. Then milk and stir gently. Add the 7-UP for zip.

title: pasta and cabbage salad
directions: Cook pasta in boiling water according to directions on package.
Immediately drain.
Rinse under cold water; drain well. Mix with all other ingredients.
Chill.

title: creamed chicken over corn bread
directions: Melt
margarine
in
heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring
until
smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until
mixture
is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in chicken
and mushroom soup.
Stir constantly until thoroughly heated.

title: baked corn
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Add all ingredients.
Bake at 325° until golden brown (about 1 hour).
Can use 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: english apple pie
directions: Beat butter and brown sugar until pale and fluffy.
Stir in flour and 1 tsp of cinnamon and water until smooth and thick.
Add nuts.
Mound apples in a 9 inch pie plate.
Mix granulated sugar with remaining cinnamon and sprinkle over apples.
Spoon flour mixture in dollops over apples evenly.

title: creamy chicken and broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Layer chicken, then broccoli in the dish.
Mix soup and milk. Pour over broccoli.
Arrange cheese slices on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through. Serves 6 to 8.
Recipe can be halved and baked in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: summer chicken salad
directions: Combine pineapple syrup and mayo in mixing bowl, then gently toss with the rest of the ingredients.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat.
Add pineapple and bread cubes; stir.
Bake in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: black forest cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt in a bowl. Add all at once the oil, vinegar, water and vanilla.
(Do not use metal to mix with or in.)
Bake in large sheet cake pan at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool.
Cut in half and put together with topping.

title: grape-nut bread
directions: Pour milk over Grape-Nuts; let stand a few minutes.
Add beaten eggs and sugar.
Sift flour and baking powder together; add to wet ingredients.
Batter is very stiff.
Pour into well-greased 9-inch loaf pan; let stand 15 to 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or more.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar and water to clear crystal stage. Bring to a boil and add chocolate and margarine.
Boil to 232° on a candy thermometer.
Put this mixture in a well-greased pan.
Allow to cool.
Put in a deep dish.
Add vanilla and beat to right consistency. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar; cream until fluffy.
Dissolve soda in the water and pour into creamed mixture along with the salt.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Gradually stir in buttermilk and cake flour.
Add flavoring last.
Pour batter into greased and floured 12 cup tube pan and bake about 1 1/2 hours at 275°.
Do not open oven door while cake is baking.

title: wild berry cobbler
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and milk; stir with wire whisk until smooth.
Add melted butter and blend.
Pour batter into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Pour berries (amount depends on personal preference) evenly over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: grandmom richardson's pot roast
directions: Brown meat on all sides in cast-iron (or other heavy) stew pot. Combine water, puree, vinegar, sugar, bay leaves and bacon; pour over roast.
Cover and bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Add onion and carrots.
Continue baking 60 to 90 minutes longer.
Remove meat. Thicken gravy by adding flour to cold water, then to pan juices. Bring to boil, scraping bottom of pan; simmer until thickened. Season with salt and freshly grated black pepper.
If desired, add raisins; cook 5 minutes.
Serve sliced meat with gravy over it.

title: salmon salad spread
directions: Mix together drained salmon, celery, onion, lemon juice, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate.
Use spread on bread or crackers or use to stuff tomatoes or celery.
Makes 2 large sandwiches.

title: gouranga potatoes
directions: In large saucepan, parboil potatoes.
Drain and refrigerate. When cool, peel and cut in 1/2-inch slices.

title: frooty popcorn treats
directions: You will need 8 (7-ounce) plastic cups and 8 wooden popsicle sticks.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Beat eggs in a small bowl.
Dip chicken breasts, one at a time, first in eggs, then in bread crumbs.
Brown chicken in oil. Arrange in baking dish.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and 2 tablespoons grated cheese.
Pour spaghetti sauce over all. Sprinkle with remaining grated cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in the blender.
Pour into a greased 10-inch pie plate.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Pie makes its own crust and topping.
You'll have to try this to believe it.

title: corn light bread
directions: Mix all together and cook in a Bundt of tube pan that has been greased.
Steam first for 15 or 20 minutes by placing the pan of batter in a large, covered pan with about 1-inch of water.
(I use a 9 x 13-inch cake pan and cover it with heavy aluminum foil.) Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes or until brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine or butter on bottom of casserole.
Pour stuffing over margarine.
Defrost broccoli.
Beat with 1 egg.
Add corn.
Mix well.
Pour on top of stuffing in casserole.
Cover with 1/2 cup stuffing.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven (do not cover).

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, flour and salt.
Add milk and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
