Remove from heat and stir a small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks; return to hot mixture in saucepan.
Cook 1 minute more, stirring constantly. Add peanut butter and margarine; stir until blended.
Pour into cooled pastry shell.
Top with meringue and bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: horio cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well and spoon-drop onto a cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: tostados with guacamole
directions: Heat beans in pan, adding taco seasoning and stirring to prevent scorching.
Prepare vegetables in separate containers. Heat about 1 inch of oil in skillet.
Fry corn tortillas one at a time until crisp, turning once.
Drain on paper towel.
Spread a spoonful of hot bean mixture on tortilla; sprinkle with cheese, lettuce, tomato and onion.
Top with guacamole, if desired.

title: hobo supper
directions: As you like, sliced onions, sliced squash, sliced potatoes, carrots and cut up cabbage, torn apart.
Line a shallow baking pan with tinfoil (enough to cover supper after it is put in pan). Layer the bottom of the pan with cabbage.
Pat out 2 hamburger steaks.
Salt and pepper, then place them on top of the cabbage. Place onions on steaks, then place squash around the onions.
Place potatoes around, then the carrots.
Add salt and pepper and put a few slices of oleo on top.
Fold tinfoil over to cover tightly and place in oven at 350° for about 45 minutes or until done.
Serve with rolls and you have a meal for two.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix meal, water and salt; boil for 5 minutes.
Add milk, eggs and fat; pour into hot greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: colonial candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook sweet potatoes with their jackets in very little water, covered, for 15 minutes or until tender.
Remove, cool and set aside until ready to use.

title: tiger butter
directions: Melt
chocolate disc in microwave and pour in rectangular dish.
Then
melt
white
disc
along with peanut butter. Pour peanut
butter
mixture over top of the chocolate to give it the marble
effect.
Take a butter knife and cut around to mix it better,
swirling
to
give
it the marble effect down through.

title: michigan sauce
directions: Brown hamburg and chopped onions.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer in slow cooker.
Serve with your favorite hot dogs.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Using half the prepared pastry, line a 9-inch pie pan.
Roll out the remaining pastry and cut in strips, 1/2-inch wide. Combine remaining ingredients, except butter, and turn into the pie pan; dot with butter.
Arrange pastry strips, lattice-fashion, over fruit.
Seal edges; trim and flute.
Bake in hot oven, 400° for 40 to 50 minutes or until crust is golden and fruit is cooked.

title: pirate pups
directions: Sift all dry ingredients, except cereal.
Add cereal.
Beat egg, milk and oil together.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Stick skewers into ends of franks.
Wipe franks with dry cloth.
Dust with flour.
Dip into batter.
Drop into deep fat at 375°.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve hot.
Makes 10 to 12 Pirate Pups.

title: squash bread
directions: Mix squash in blender with orange juice until smooth.
Set aside.
Scald milk and add margarine to melt it.
When milk is lukewarm, add yeast and sugar to it in a large bowl.
Add salt and squash mixture and 2 eggs.
Mix.

title: simple coleslaw
directions: Chop tender cabbage thoroughly.
Add diced ripe tomato.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add mayonnaise.
Mix well.
More mayonnaise may be added if needed.
Keep refrigerated.

title: clam sauce
directions: Saute all in olive oil for 5 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add soups, sauce and touch of garlic and simmer.
Line large casserole with tortillas.
Add meat mixture.
Layer twice and top with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 250°.
Can be made into 2 casseroles, freezing one for later.

title: saucy turnips
directions: Place turnips in a large saucepan.
Add 1/4 cup water; bring to a boil.
Cover; cook for 12 minutes.
Add green onions, butter, garlic powder and salt.
Cook an additional 5 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1/4 cup water; add to turnips, stirring until combined.
Add cheese; cook until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: fried calves liver with apples and onion
directions: Melt half the butter in a frying pan.
Fry the onion rings and apple slices until they are light brown.
Season with salt and pepper.
Set aside and keep hot.
Dust the liver slices with flour.
Fry them in the remaining butter, allowing approximately 2 minutes on each side.
Do not overcook.
Serve the liver slices garnished with the apples and onions.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix
all ingredients together except oil.
Make patties. Fry in shortening or oil for 5 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; remove bones and cut into small chunks.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake at 275° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy beef tips
directions: Cut beef into bite size pieces, placing in a 9-inch baking dish.
Pour mushroom soup over meat and sprinkle onion soup mix over this mixture. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender, adding a little water if needed.
Serve over rice.

title: fruit filled watermelon
directions: Cut thin horizontal slice from bottom of watermelon so it will rest evenly.
Slice watermelon lengthwise in half.
Carve a decorative zigzag edge from sliced edge of 1/2 of the melon. Scoop out fruit to form a bowl.
Scoop melon balls from second half.
Fill bowl with watermelon, honeydew, cantaloupe, pineapple chunks, strawberries, blueberries or any other fresh fruits in season.
Pour Aloha Sauce over fruit in bowl; toss lightly (or use as dip).

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter an 8-inch square baking pan. Spread apples in pan; sprinkle with water.
Combine flour with cinnamon and salt.
Blend in sugar and margarine.
Sprinkle this mixture over apples.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: amaretto dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well; refrigerate for at least 2 hours for best flavor.
Delicious served with fresh apple slices.

title: kenny's surprise
directions: Cream the margarine and sugars.
Add egg; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients one at a time; mix.
Stir in pecans.
Chill well.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Put egg, salt and milk in blender.
Turn on long enough to blend.
Then add potatoes, cut in small pieces, and onion, quartered.
Blend.
Take off blender and add a little flour, enough to make the right consistency.
Fry in oil.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put peaches in a pan. Prepare cake mix and pour on top of peaches. Top with almonds. Spread butter or margarine evenly over almonds. Cook at 350° for one hour. Enjoy!

title: south carolina red chicken stew(serving size: 12)
directions: Cook the chicken in a covered Dutch oven until very tender, using just enough water to keep from sticking.
Remove skin, then pull meat from bones and tear into serving-size pieces.
Discard skin and bones.
Return chicken pieces to Dutch oven.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs together.
Add apples.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon together and add to creamed mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 11-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This pudding/cake is great with the following sauce poured over each serving (preferably warm).

title: boiled cake
directions: Boil first 7 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Add baking soda and flour.
Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: In large container, combine gelatin with boiling water.
Stir until dissolved; then fold in all at once strawberries with juice, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Pour half mixture into long dish; refrigerate until firm.
Keep the other half over warm water to keep it from congealing.
Spread sour cream over firm Jell-O then spoon the other half of mixture over sour cream.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours or until firm.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: pineapple ham loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Turn crushed pineapple with juice into a small pan; bring to a boil.
In a medium bowl, combine beef, ham, 1/2 cup rolled oats, mustard and egg.
Stir hot pineapple into meat mixture.
Turn into a greased baking pan.
Bake until firm, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put into casserole dish broccoli, soup, cheese and crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes uncovered.

title: jello pastels
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and salt; add oleo, milk and sugar. Mix in egg, vanilla and almond, then add Jell-O.
Mixture is creamy.
Drop by a teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: In a large bowl mix ingredients with hands until well blended. Make balls the size of marbles on lightly greased cookie sheet. Press balls flat with back of fork.
When cool, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: portuguese shrimp (g)
directions: Sauce:
Mix first 7 ingredients.
Use about 2 quarts of shrimp for 1 recipe of sauce, preferably fresh shrimp, unpeeled with heads on.
Arrange shrimp in shallow pan in rows very close together and spoon sauce evenly over shrimp.
Sprinkle generously with black pepper (garnish with lemon slices, bell pepper slices, pimento, etc., if desired) and marinate 1 hour or longer.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve as an appetizer or one dish meal with plenty of hot, unbuttered French bread to dunk into the sauce.

title: chalupas
directions: Heat lightly greased skillet.
Add ground beef or turkey and onion.
Cook until meat is browned.
Drain off grease.
Add seasonings and mix thoroughly.
Blend in beans and their liquid. Cover and simmer for about 30 minutes.
Heat shortening in a skillet.
Fry tortillas for 1 minute on each side.
Drain on absorbent paper.
You may wrap tortillas in foil and heat in oven until warm.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash the broccoli. Peel stems.
Remove rosettes and cut into small pieces.
Chop stems.
Chop the onion, eggs and olives.
Mix all together and add the mayonnaise.
Mix, then marinate in the refrigerator at least 1/2 day.
(I only use 2 hard-boiled eggs when I make this recipe.)

title: nordy bars
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt the butter. Add the butterscotch chips and brown sugar; melt.
Remove from the heat and stir in the eggs. Add the flour, baking powder and salt. Add the vanilla. Set aside until cool.
When cool, add the chocolate chips, marshmallows and nuts. Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool before cutting, it is a lot easier.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, green pepper and onion.
Drain.
Add tomatoes and corn.
In a separate pan, cook zucchini.
Mix all ingredients together in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together and store in a covered container.
Add 1 to 2 tablespoons per cup of boiling water.

title: pink lady salad
directions: Bring crushed pineapple to boil; add strawberry Jell-O.
Add cottage cheese.
Blend pecans with Cool Whip; mix into Jell-O, pineapple and cottage cheese.
Chill.

title: crisco icing
directions: Cook milk and flour over low heat, stirring constantly, until real firm.
Put in refrigerator.
Mix together butter, Crisco, sugar and vanilla; beat until real fine.
Add mixture from refrigerator.
Beat with mixture until whipping cream consistency.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Heat 2 cups of milk to simmering.
Add salt, cornmeal and butter to hot milk.
Cook 10 minutes in double boiler.
Cool to lukewarm; add baking powder dissolved in 1 cup of cold milk.
Beat in egg yolks.
Fold in stiffly beaten whites.
Pour into deep buttered baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Serve hot with butter or ham gravy.
Serves 6.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Spray bottom of oblong pan with shortening.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding and milk together, then stir in Cool Whip.
Layer in a 13 x 9-inch pan:
layer of graham crackers, layer of pudding mixture, another layer of graham crackers, layer of pudding mixture and 1 more layer of graham crackers.
Spread can of icing on top.
Better if put in refrigerator overnight.
This is a quick and yummy dessert.

title: no-cook tomato sauce
directions: Dice tomatoes.
Toss with herbs.
Add vinegar and oil.
Chill while cooking tortellini or ravioli.
Toss together.
Serve immediately.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Pour hot water over soda and dates.
Mix butter, sugar and beaten egg.
Add flour gradually, then nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: baked pita chips
directions: Preheat the oven to 400. Split the bread rounds into halves. Cut each Half into 8 wedges. Arrange the wedges in a single layer on an 11x17 inch baking sheet. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown. Makes 64 chips.

title: sweet and zesty spareribs
directions: Place pork spareribs, meat side up, on rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Roast, uncovered, in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fried okra
directions: Cut okra into 1/2-inch slices.
Beat egg white with water. Pour over okra.
Coat okra with egg and water mixture.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over okra.
Cook in hot fat until golden brown.

title: farmers' market medley
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add garlic, broccoli and cauliflower.
Cook and stir 4 to 6 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add water.
Cover.
Cook 2 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Add zucchini and dill weed.
Cook and stir 3 to 4 minutes or until zucchini is crisp-tender.
Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: red beans and rice
directions: In saucepan, heat beans without letting them boil. Stir in chili powder, cumin and garlic salt. When piping hot, add warm rice and gently mix.

title: peanut butter bars(easy to make and a favorite of all family members!)
directions: Mix flour, sugar, milk, eggs, margarine, baking powder and vanilla well and pour into 11 x 17-inch greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
As soon as it comes out of oven, spread 1 cup of peanut butter over cake.
Sprinkle the chocolate chips over peanut butter and spread.
Refrigerate (to harden chocolate), then cut into squares.

title: carolyn's scalloped corn
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish. Stir. Cook at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: deer jerky
directions: Slice venison 1/2-inch thick by 2-inches wide.
Length doesn't matter.
Combine soy sauce, liquid smoke, pepper and garlic into a pot.
Add meat; stir and refrigerate for 24 to 48 hours.
Stir at least 3 times a day.
When meat has refrigerated for the required time, drain meat and place on oven rack.
Set oven temperature on low.
Drying time will vary on the thickness of the meat.
Usually 6 to 8 hours.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter, powdered sugar and butter.
Mix well. Add Rice Krispies and mix by hand.
Melt chocolate and wax in a double boiler; dip balls into this.
Cool on wax paper.

title: quick stuffed mushrooms
directions: Chop and saute the mushroom stems in the butter.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Fill the mushroom caps with the mixture and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet sour sausage
directions: In saucepan, blend sugar, flour and mustard; stir in pineapple juice, vinegar and soy sauce.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add sausage links and heat through.

title: monaco chicken breasts
directions: Cover the bottom of ungreased 8 x 12-inch baking dish with chipped beef. Wrap each breast half with 1/2 slice of bacon. Place these over the beef.
Mix sour cream, parsley, soup and mushrooms.
Pour over the breasts.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper.
Mix all other ingredients together in baking dish.
Add meat mixture; bake 1 hour at 350°. Do not overcook.

title: porcupines
directions: Combine meat, rice, egg, parsley, onion, salt and 1/4 cup soup.
Mix these well and shape into small balls, about 20. Place in large skillet; mix remaining soup, water and Worcestershire sauce together.
Pour mixture over meatballs. Bring to full boil, then reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 40 to 45 minutes.
Keep stirring often; add a little water if needed. Serves 4.

title: cheese soup
directions: Mix broth and water together.
Add potatoes, celery and onions.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add package of California vegetables.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add soup and cheese. Stir and serve.
Freezes well.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Using a 2-quart serving bowl, layer lettuce, tomatoes, mushrooms, peas, onion rings and cheese.
Spread salad dressing over, sealing to edge of bowl.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Garnish with crumbled bacon, cooked crisp.
Add additional cheese.

title: sopa de pan (bread pot soup)
directions: Toast and butter the French bread.
Break into large pieces; put several in bottom of individual bowls.
Drop one whole uncooked egg in each bowl.
Dissolve the bouillon cubes in 4 cups of boiling water or bring your 4 cups of homemade broth to a boil. Pour the liquid on top of the eggs.
Sprinkle with grated cheese. Put a slice of Swiss cheese on top of each bowl.
Put bowls in the oven under the broiler until cheese begins to melt.
Garnish with parsley.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Stir together soup, sour cream, 3/4 cup Cheddar cheese, onion and green chilies.	Reserve 3/4 cup for sauce.
Then add chicken or turkey.	Flour
tortillas
and
fill
with mixture, place in greased baking
dish. Add the 1/2 cup milk to the 3/4 cup of reserved sauce and pour over top.
Garnish with 1/4 cup cheese. Bake at 350°
for
about
minutes.
Makes
6 to 8 tortillas.

title: ranch potato salad
directions: Finely chop all vegetables and the eggs.
Cook potatoes in a small amount of boiling salted water for approximately 35 minutes or until just tender.
Drain and peel when cool enough.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes and place in a large bowl.
Add Italian dressing and toss lightly.
Cover and refrigerate 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add all ingredients except for green onions and toss gently to mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.
Sprinkle with the green onions just prior to serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 inch x 12 inch baking dish.	Add each ingredient in order as listed, spreading out over pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 30 minutes. Let cool in pan until cold. Cut into squares.

title: southern georgia chocolate pound cake
directions: Into
bowl of mixer, sift together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients and add butter, milk and vanilla.
Beat with dry ingredients for
5 minutes.
Add
cream
and
eggs,
one
at a time, beating thoroughly	after
each.
Pour batter into well-oiled 10-inch tube pan
or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or
until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool completely on wire rack. Freezes well.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs with mixer; add sugar at low speed.
Add oleo, vanilla and milk.
Add flour.
Stir in coconut by hand.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Crust forms on the bottom, custard in the center and coconut comes on top.

title: nutty cookie balls
directions: Mix well; shape into balls and chill.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Fill pastry-lined pie pan with rhubarb custard filling: Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk.
Mix together and stir in sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Mix in rhubarb.
Dot filling in pan with butter. Cover with lattice top.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes until nicely browned.
Serve slightly warm.

title: crispy shortbread cookies
directions: Preheat
oven	to
Cream
margarine
and
sugar together.	Add flour;
mix
well.	Spread	1
layer
of
Rice Krispies on flat
dish
(add as needed).
Shape mixture into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Flatten between palms of hands.
Press 1 side onto Rice Krispies.
Lay,
2 inches apart, on ungreased baking sheets (Krispies side up).	Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, or until edges are lightly browned.	Makes about 3 dozen.

title: peanut rocky road
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Fold in peanuts and marshmallows.
Drop on waxed paper in mounds.
Chill until firm.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter and roll chicken parts in the butter.
Mix the two soups, water and rice together and pour over the chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: swiss steak
directions: Place steak on bread board.
Mix flour, salt and pepper. Pound into steak on both sides.
Brown steak on both sides in hot fat.
Add tomatoes or stewed tomatoes, onion and green pepper. Cover tightly and simmer for 1 hour or until tender.
I use electric skillet.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Prepare cake
mix
according
to
directions.
Bake
or 2 pans for 20 to 25 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, pudding and milk;
heat until thick.
Cool until cake is cool.
Place
on cooled cake.
Top with the following: drained pineapple
or
pie
filling, whipped topping, coconut, walnuts. Refrigerate until served.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix apples, sugar and cinnamon.
Cover and set for 30 minutes. Add egg, oil, baking powder, baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour; mix well and then add nuts.
Stir and then pour in greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When finished, cool in pan for 20 to 30 minutes, then remove cake to prevent sticking.

title: the dare devil
directions: In a glass bowl or on a plate, place one brownie.
Scoop 1/4 of a pint of ice cream onto brownie.
Top with another brownie square.
Add hot fudge sauce, strawberry sauce and 1/4 cup whipped cream.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Melt chocolate with shortening.
Combine with sugar and mix. Add eggs and mix.
Add baking powder, salt and vanilla and mix. Mix in flour.
Batter will be stiff.
Chill and roll into walnut-size balls.
Roll top of ball in powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 (softer cookie) to 15 (harder cookie) minutes.

title: turnip casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except for 1/2 cup of bread crumbs and 2 tablespoons melted margarine.
Whip together with a fork. Turn into buttered 1-quart casserole.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven about 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon-colored.
Stir in milk.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to egg mixture, mixing until smooth. Using a 1/4 c. measuring cup, drop into a buttered skillet on medium heat.
Spread batter evenly to make thin, crepe-like pancakes.
Turn when underside is light brown.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: fried onions with apples
directions: Cook onions slowly in drippings until nearly tender.
Add apples (sliced), water and salt.
Cover.
Cook until apples are soft.
Remove cover.
Cook until water is gone and light brown. Serve hot.
Yield: 3 servings.

title: boiled crawfish
directions: Add lemons, onions, crab oil, salt and pepper to a 10 gallon or larger stew pot.
Bring water to a boil.
After water boils for 5 minutes, add potatoes.
Boil 10 minutes.
Add crawfish and boil 10 more minutes.
Add corn and remove from heat.
Cover and let crawfish and vegetables soak for 15 more minutes to allow flavors to absorb in meat, corn and potatoes.
Drain and sprinkle crawfish with Creole seasoning to taste.
Serve immediately.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Line 9-inch square baking dish with 2/3 of buttered crumb mixture.
Whip the cream.
Mix sweetened milk and lemon juice. Beat well.
Add cherries, pecans and whipped cream.
Fold in gently.
Pour into crumb-lined pan; top with remaining crumbs. Chill in refrigerator.
Cut into squares for serving.
May be frozen if desired.

title: croutons italiano
directions: In a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish, place cubes.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes, until cubes begin to dry. Sprinkle herb seasoning and garlic salt evenly over bread cubes. Drizzle with butter to coat cubes.
Microwave on High for 4 to 6 minutes, stirring every minute, until crisp and dry.
Makes 6 cups.

title: fresh cranberry relish
directions: Put the cranberries, apples and oranges through a coarse die on a meat grinder, then blend together with all ingredients in a bowl. Check salt content and adjust if necessary.
Refrigerate in plastic or stainless steel for at least 2 days for best flavor.
Serve with chicken, turkey or duck, especially during the holidays.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Blend in applesauce after egg.
Dissolve soda in boiling water and add alternately with dry ingredients.
Serve un-iced or use white icing.
Grease and flour cake pan.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: deep-dish pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Lightly grease jelly roll pan. Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms. Gently smooth dough into a ball on floured surface. Knead 20 times. Pat dough on pan bottom with floured hands. Go up side of pan with dough. You can use Pillsbury pizza crust and put in pan the same way.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix
in
large
bowl
sugar and flour.
Mix cocoa, oleo, Wesson oil
and water in saucepan and bring to boil.
Pour over flour
and sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Beat together milk, eggs, soda
and
vanilla
and
add
to other mixture.
Bake on cookie sheet at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Ice while cake is hot.

title: chocolate rolls
directions: Spread this mixture on pie crust.
Cut to the way you want and fold to meet.
Bake at 400° until crust is brown, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: teff skillet flat bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour with baking soda.
Stir in buttermilk, then add enough water to give the mixture a fairly thick yet fluid consistency.
Stir in oil.
Heat a 6-inch nonstick crepe pan until sizzling hot.
Pour in a scant 1/4 cup of batter and quickly tilt pan to form a round.
Cook until golden brown on each side; repeat with remaining batter.
Makes 12 to 14 pancakes. Delicious with stews and chili.

title: scrambled egg sandwich
directions: Prepare bacon in a skillet until crispy; drain.
Add beaten eggs; cook until done.
Add to lettuce mixture, stirring continuously.
Add vinegar; keep mixing.
Season with salt, pepper and sugar.
Serve on toast or as a salad.

title: fillet of fish amandine
directions: Place almonds and butter in 8 inch microproof baking dish. Cook, uncovered, on HI for 5 minutes or until almonds and butter are golden brown; set aside.
Place fish in baking dish, turning fish to coat both sides with butter.
Sprinkle with lemon juice, salt, dill and pepper.
Top with parsley.
Cover with waxed paper and cook on HI for 4 minutes.
Sprinkle almonds over fish.
Cover with paper towel and cook on HI for 1-2 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Let stand 1 minute before serving.
3-4 servings.
Total cooking time:
10-11 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic in skillet; add tomato sauce, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Heat through.
Line greased shallow casserole with tortillas, 1/2 for 2 rows (or make 4 rows). Cover with meat mixture on each row.
Combine soup and milk; pour on top.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 servings.

title: slaw
directions: Add potatoes to boiling water; cook 14 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Mix mayonnaise and mustard in large bowl.
Add potatoes, bacon and chives; mix lightly.
Refrigerate.
Makes 6 servings.

title: toll house cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugars and add egg.
Dissolve soda in a few drops hot water and mix alternately with sifted flour and salt. Add chocolate chips and nuts; mix well.
Add vanilla and drop by 1/2 teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes in a 375° oven.
Makes 60 cookies.

title: fluff dessert
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into serving dish and chill.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Whisk together all 3 ingredients.
Chill at least 1/2 hour. Serve with fresh raw vegetables.
Also a good topping for baked potatoes.

title: chili burgers
directions: Prepare grill for grilling.
Place meat in bowl and mix well with tomato, olives, garlic, mustard, chili powder, basil, oregano, lemon zest and dill.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Gently form into 4 patties.

title: white fruit cake
directions: *For color, I mix red and green cherries together to equal the 3/4 pound.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and slice sweet potatoes.
Fry in oil. Keep turning potatoes.
When almost done, add sugar and milk.
Simmer on low heat until done.

title: carrots and grapes
directions: Saute carrots, cut in thick diagonal slices, in butter. Sprinkle carrots with sugar.
Cook, stirring, for 1 to 2 minutes. Add vodka and water.
When almost tender, add grapes.
Cover and cook until very tender.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Cook all dressing ingredients except salad oil until sugar is dissolved. Cool.
Add oil.

title: mashed potato donuts
directions: Beat eggs with sugar and vanilla until light.
Add potatoes and shortening.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk. Beat well.
Chill dough 3 hours.
Fry in deep, hot fat at 375° for about 3 minutes, turning often.
Makes 2 to 2 1/2 dozen.

title: crunchy pops
directions: You will need 12 popsicle sticks.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in greased pan at 400° until golden brown.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together and put in 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Melt 1/2 stick butter and drizzle over top; top with 2 cups cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados in a medium size bowl.
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper.
In a separate bowl, combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.

title: chicken corn bread casserole
directions: Combine corn bread, green pepper, onion and celery; mix well. Place half of mixture in 2-quart baking dish.
Spread chicken over corn bread layer.
Bake in oven at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: cabbage hot dish
directions: Shred a head of cabbage rather coarsely. Saute the hamburger with onion. Heat it through but don't brown. Season with salt and pepper if desired. Butter a medium sized
casserole dish and add half the cabbage then the hamburger
mixture. Put cheese over hamburger then put the rest of the cabbage over the top. Pour the can of tomato soup over entire mixture. Cover and bake 55 minutes at 350 degrees or until done.

title: zucchini squash loaf or dressing
directions: For a large batch or dish, peel 2 large squash.
Cook until soft or done.
Drain and mash.
Add egg and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in a casserole and bake at 375°.
Garnish with parsley flakes or paprika.
Makes a nice casserole.

title: barbecue wieners
directions: Cook on high for 2 hours and on low for 3 hours in crock-pot.

title: linguine salad
directions: Cook linguine in unsalted water; drain and rinse.
Chop vegetables.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, sour cream, nuts, yellow cake mix, eggs and vanilla.
Grease and flour pan.
Pour 1/2 of batter into pan and sprinkle cinnamon and brown sugar over it.
The pour the rest of the batter over it.
Move rack down 1 notch and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle more cinnamon and brown sugar to cover top of cake, to give it more cinnamon taste.

title: no-fat italian dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender or food processor and puree until smooth.
Chill 15 minutes before serving.
Store in a covered container in refrigerator.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring oil, oleo, water and cocoa to a boil.
Mix sugar, flour and salt together.
Pour in cocoa mixture.
Add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch well-greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost with chocolate icing.

title: cream cheese cool whip banana pudding
directions: Crush vanilla wafers. Blend rest of ingredients together to make a mixture.
Layer bananas and mixture and fold in crushed wafers.

title: summertime tea
directions: Steep tea bags in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, chill.

title: applesauce-spice loaf
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger, salt and cloves; set aside.
In a large bowl, cream the butter. Gradually beat in sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Stir in flour mixture alternately with applesauce just until blended.
Stir in walnuts.
Turn into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool in pan on rack for 5 minutes.
Remove.
Cool completely.

title: hot sausage balls
directions: Mix all together very well.
Will be dry and take time to mix. If you have a dough mixer, it will do the job.
Roll into small balls.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until light brown.

title: crab soup
directions: Blend in blender all ingredients (except crab).
Heat slowly until hot.
Stir in crab meat.

title: tomatoey beans n'burger
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet and drain off fat.
Stir in seasoning mix and water until thickened.
Add tomato paste. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in beans and mushrooms. Turn into a 2-quart casserole and top with cheese.
Bake in a preheated oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: cherry supreme
directions: Let all ingredients set in refrigerator in cans overnight. Drain pineapple and oranges.
Mix all ingredients with a folding motion.
I usually add chopped pecans.
Serves 8.

title: peanut marbles
directions: Sieve powdered sugar into butter and peanut butter (mixed together).
Add raisins, chocolate chips and nuts and make into small balls.
Moisten with milk and roll in coconut.

title: strawberry-blueberry cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine ingredients in saucepan and cook, stirring occasionally, until bubbly and slightly thickened.
Pour into a greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: blueberry buttermilk biscuits
directions: *Use less buttermilk with oil and more with shortening.
For 1/3 cup shortening use 3/4 cup buttermilk.

title: lasagna
directions: In a heavy pan, lightly brown beef and onion in oil. Add tomatoes, paste, water, parsley, salt, sugar, garlic powder, pepper and oregano. Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, about 30 minutes.

title: cheese meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in iron skillet at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: crawfish linguini
directions: *Can substitute shrimp or chicken.

title: salmon burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients except oil.
Shape into 6 patties. Rub surface of nonstick skillet with oil; pan-fry salmon patties until golden brown.

title: hurry-up batter rolls
directions: In mixing bowl, combine 2 cups of the flour and yeast.
In saucepan, heat milk, Crisco, sugar and salt just until warm (115° to 120°), stirring until Crisco almost melts; add to dry mixture. Add egg.
Beat with electric mixer at low speed for 1/2 minute, scraping bowl.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, beat in remaining flour until batter is thoroughly mixed.
Cover; let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Stir down and beat thoroughly with wooden spoon.
Let rest 5 minutes.
Drop batter by tablespoon into greased muffin pans, filling half full.
Cover; let rise until double, about 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 400°.
(Optional: Brush tops lightly with melted Crisco; sprinkle with poppy seed.) Bake at 400° until done, 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 18 to 20 rolls.

title: creamed crab meat with artichoke hearts
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, melt butter and stir in flour, cook 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring often.
Add onions, cook 2 to 3 minutes without browning.
Stir in parsley.
Gradually add cream and heat well.
Add wine, salt and pepper.
Blend well.
Bring to a simmer, stirring occasionally, remove from heat.
When sauce has cooled to lukewarm, add lemon juice.
In a 3-quart casserole, alternate layers of crab meat, artichoke hearts and mushrooms, spreading sauce between layers.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 45 minutes. May be prepared in advance, freezes well.
Serves 8. Rich, filling and fattening!

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix until blended well.
Form into 1 inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: texas devil's food cake
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, soda and salt. Cream sugar and margarine. Add vanilla and eggs to creamed mixture. Beat well. Add 1 cup buttermilk alternately with dry ingredients. Add 1 cup boiling water. Grease and flour large cake pan or cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In a saucepan, combine peaches with syrup, cornstarch and cinnamon.
Bring to a boil, then simmer approximately 10 minutes. Place peaches in a baking dish.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Melt margarine; mix together with peanut butter, graham cracker crumbs and powdered sugar. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. (Do not grease pan.) Melt Hershey chocolate bars and smooth over top. Cut into small bars.

title: brown sugar coffee cake
directions: Baking Temperature: 325°.
Baking Time: 45 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Simmer hen until tender in salted water.
Remove meat from broth and debone.
Put meat in pan and keep warm while making dumplings.

title: carrot-pineapple bread
directions: Mix and sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon into a medium bowl.
Beat eggs and sugar together; stir in oil, carrots and pineapple.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients and vanilla. Grease and flour bread pans.
Spoon batter into pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Check with toothpick.

title: sunburst macaroni salad
directions: Prepare Velveeta shells and cheese as directed on package. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Chill!

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat in hot oil.
Add garlic and cook until yellow.
Add soy sauce, salt and 1/4 cup water.
Cook for 45 minutes.
Add vegetables.
Cook 10 minutes.
Stir in cornstarch mixed with 1 cup water.
Add tomatoes and cook for 5 minutes.
Serve over rice. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: butter cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Put dry ingredients together and stir.
Place in greased/floured cake pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: caramel nut candy(microwave)
directions: Place caramels, butter, and cream in a 2 quart microwave safe dish.
Microwave uncovered on medium for 2 minutes; stir. Microwave 1-3 minutes more, stirring every minute until smooth. Stir in sugar until smooth.
Add peanuts.

Gently fold in marshmallows, sprinkle coconut on a 10x5-inch strip onto 2 sheets of waxed paper; spoon caramel mixture down the center of coconut. Using the waxed paper coat caramel with coconut and roll into 2-10inch logs.
Discard waxed paper.
Wrap logs in plastic wrap and chill for 4 hours.
Remove plastic wrap.
Cut logs into 1/2-inch slices.
Store in air-tight container in the refrigerator.

title: blond brownies
directions: Cream eggs, sugar, shortening, vanilla and water.
Add all dry ingredients.
Fold in chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes.

title: french bread
directions: Measure these into a large mixing bowl.
Make a hole in the center of flour mixture and pour liquid mixture.
Stir thoroughly, but do not knead.
The dough will be soft.
Cover with a damp cloth and set in a warm place to rise, allowing about 2 hours.(Put cold oven on for 1 minute then cut off and let dough rise in there.) Punch down the dough.
Place on a floured board and pat into two equal oblongs.
Form each into a French loaf by rolling the dough away from you.
Continue rolling, pressing outward with the hands and tapering the dough toward the ends until a long, thin form results.
Place the 2 loaves on a greased baking sheet.
Cut diagonal 1/4-inch deep slits across the tops with sharp pointed scissors.
Set in a warm place to rise to somewhat less than doubled in bulk.
Preheat oven to 400°.
On bottom of oven, place a pan filled with 1/2-inch boiling water.
Bake 15 minutes then reduce heat to 350° and bake about 30 minutes.
Yeild 2 loaves.

title: texas chili
directions: Brown meat in skillet; drain off grease.
Put in a 2-quart pot and add all ingredients.
Stir and blend thoroughly.
Simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken gravy and biscuits
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Salt and pepper the chicken to taste.
Dip chicken in melted margarine.
Add flour to margarine with a fork; work flour into margarine.
Add broth; stir until smooth.
Place in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Check in 15 minutes and stir mixture to smooth any lumps.
When chicken is done, put biscuits on top of chicken and gravy; either canned or homemade biscuits.
Bake until brown (serve hot).

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Put rice in shallow baking dish.
Put pork chops on rice.
Add salt and pepper.
Add soup and water. Cover with foil and bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.
Uncover and brown under broiler.

title: soup supreme
directions: Cook ground beef; drain grease.
Mix ground beef with the onions, chicken noodle soup and cream of chicken.
Cook for 20 minutes.

title: ramer lunch rolls
directions: Add dry ingredients to liquid, gradually add more flour until soft
dough
forms.
Stir
until
dough pulls away from sides of bowl.
Roll out, cut and place on baking sheet, brush with oil. Let rise until double.
Bake at 400° until browned. Brush with melted oleo when done.

title: yeast buns
directions: Dissolve yeast cake in 1 cup of lukewarm water.
Add remaining 3 cups of water.
Add enough flour to make a stiff batter.
Set in warm place.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Make out buns; let rise and bake at 350°.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and let cook on low for at least 1 hour.
The longer it cooks, the better it is.
This is great for the crock-pot.
Add small can of tomato paste for thicker sauce.

title: cole slaw
directions: Thoroughly blend sugar, milk, beer, vinegar and salt. Combine cabbage, green pepper and carrot. Pour dressing over cabbage mixture. Blend all together and chill. Just before serving, toss lightly. Yields 1 quart.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in bottom of casserole dish.
Add all other ingredients and mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Bake with lid.

title: angel crisp cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Add vanilla.
Drop one teaspoon onto greased baking sheet (less if you want smaller cookies).
Press down with a glass, dipped in ice water.
Bake at 400° until brown for 4 to 5 minutes.

title: raspberry syrup
directions: You will need the bottle the syrup came in.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Unthaw vegetables.
Mix mayonnaise and soup together.
Mix vegetables, cheese and onion.
Pour soup mixture over vegetable mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Place in baking dish and top with cracker crumbs.
Pour margarine on top of cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: norwegian dump cake
directions: Take an ungreased Bundt or tube pan.
Pour in the pie filling and the pineapple.
Shake it to even out.
Sprinkle the box of dry cake mix over the top.
Cut over the top 1 stick margarine.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: icebox slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, medium green peppers and onions.
Bring next 6 ingredients to a boil.
Pour over cabbage mix.
Eat within 2 weeks or anytime.

title: crispy mandarin pork
directions: Combine egg white, 2 tablespoons cornstarch and soy sauce. Stir in cubed pork.
Combine biscuit mix, water, sesame seed and combine with pork mixture.
Place 8 pieces of pork, one at a time, into deep hot fat.
Fry 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain on paper towel. Keep warm in 250° oven.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Lightly grease 2-quart oblong baking dish.
Place a layer of onion and layer of zucchini.
Repeat with onions, then zucchini. Drizzle with 1/4 cup melted margarine.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Combine remaining margarine, bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle crumbs mixture evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until zucchini is fork-tender.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites in a small bowl until foamy.
Add sugar slowly, beating until peaks form.
Fold in chocolate chips and pecans. Place ungreased foil on 2 cookie sheets.
Preheat oven to 350°. Drop the mixture by teaspoon onto the cookie sheets.
Place cookies into the heated oven and turn off heat overnight.
Do not open the oven during this time.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine chicken and water.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Skim off any residue that rises to surface.
Add bouillon cubes, 1/2 cup onion, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Cover.
Simmer 35 to 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from broth.
When cool enough to handle, remove chicken from bones and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Skim fat from broth.
Return chicken to broth.
Stir in celery, carrots and 1/4 cup onion.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Drop noodles into boiling soup.
Cook, uncovered, 5 to 10 minutes or until noodles are tender, stirring occasionally.

title: crock-pot breakfast
directions: While crock-pot is warming up on high setting, place barley in 1-quart of water and bring to a boil.
When barley comes to a boil and crock-pot is hot, pour barley and water into crock-pot and add remaining water.
Cover, turn heat to low and leave on all night. About 15 minutes before serving, add remaining ingredients except almonds and stir together.
Place in serving dish and sprinkle with almonds.
Yields 4 servings.

title: puppy chow mix
directions: Melt peanut butter, chocolate chips and oil together.
Pour cereal into a brown bag.
Pour melted mixture over cereal and shake up to blend.
Shake confectioners sugar over mix. (This is addicting!)

title: butterscotch cheesecake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, brown sugar and butter.
Mix well.
Firmly press mixture into bottom and up sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.

title: mary's famous italian love cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Prepare cake mix according to package directions and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. In a mixing bowl, combine ricotta cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla and put on top of unbaked cake mix. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Sift together flour, cocoa, baking powder, salt and baking soda and add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove and cool.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls out with fingers until it covers cookie sheet.
Seal edges really well and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Vary with garlic, dill, oregano, Bleu cheese, etc.

title: peach salad
directions: Drain peaches; save juice in a 2-quart pan.
When hot, add Jell-O; stir until dissolved.
Add peaches, sugar, spices and vinegar; let stand 15 minutes.
Add pineapple and oranges; stir and put into mold or pan.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugars, vanilla, water and eggs until light and fluffy.
Mix flour with soda and salt; blend into shortening mixture.
Stir in nuts and chips.
Drop 2 inches apart from teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain excess fat.
Add garlic salt and salt.
Simmer 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in spaghetti sauce. Cook, stirring occasionally, 10 to 15 minutes.
Boil lasagna noodles as directed.
Combine eggs, sour cream, Parmesan cheese, parsley and pepper.
Blend well.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, and salt; cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal. Gradually add milk, stirring to make a soft dough. Roll dough into a 1/8 inch thick rectangle on a lightly floured surface; cut into 5 inch squares. Place 3 or 4 pieces of apple on each square. Sprinkle each with 2 tsp. sugar and cinnamon and nutmeg to taste; dot with butter. Moisten edges of each dumpling with water; bring corners to center, pinching edges to seal. Place dumplings 1 inch apart in a lightly greased shallow baking dish. Combine last five ingredients; stir to dissolve sugar. Pour syrup over dumplings. Bake at 375°
for 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown. Serve hot with cream, if desired. Makes about 1 doz.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Add milk and cheese and stir until smooth.
Add rice and corn.
Salt and pepper to taste; pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk together in a large saucepan.
Bring them slowly to a boil while stirring.
Continue to boil and stir for 5 minutes.
Quickly stir other ingredients in and stir together until they are all melted.
Spread into a 14 x 16-inch pan.
Cut after completely cool.
Can be made ahead and frozen.
Makes 5 pounds but in our house this serves about 3 people!
It has tons of fat and calories.
I only make this at Christmastime.

title: green enchilada casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook hamburger meat; break up as it cooks.
Add onion and shredded cheese.
In oil, heat 12 tortillas or rub oleo lightly on both sides.
(Just as good and easier to do.)
Then fill each tortilla with meat mixture; fold over and lay in a greased baking pan.

title: maple walnut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine walnuts, butter, brown sugar and flour.
Mix with a pastry blender and press over the bottom and sides of a buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Prick bottom and bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Sprinkle gelatin over milk in a heavy saucepan.
Add salt.
Beat egg yolks with 1/2 cup of the syrup and the cream.
Stir into the milk and gelatin mixture.
Cook over low heat until mixture thickens slightly, about 5 minutes.
Chill, stirring occasionally, until it mounds when dropped from a spoon.
Beat egg whites until stiff, gradually adding maple syrup that remains.
Beat until very stiff. Fold into gelatin mixture.
Turn into crust and chill until firm.

title: horseradish salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add other ingredients; pour into mold.
Put in refrigerator until firm.
Very good to serve with ham sandwiches.

title: becca's creamy pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except pastry shell.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and continue baking 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted 1-inch from edge comes out clean.
Cool.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: noodles
directions: Combine ingredients.
Knead 5 to 10 times.
Roll out to thin dough and cut in strips.
Let dry to use immediately.
Noodles freeze well.

title: mom's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skins approximately 30 minutes.
Peel skin. Cut into bite-size chunks.
Sprinkle with celery salt (cover tops of potatoes).
Chop 4 of the eggs and add to potatoes.
Mix mayo, mustard, salt and pepper.
Add to potatoes, toss to cover.
Slice remaining eggs.
Decorate top of salad with slices.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In mixing bowl, mix together all ingredients, except crackers. Pour into greased casserole dish.
Crumble enough Ritz crackers to cover top of casserole.
Bake at 400° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: easy upside-down apple pie
directions: Fill pie pan 2/3 full with peeled and sliced apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over apples. Spread evenly over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Fill baking dish with alternate layers of tomatoes and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: lace roll-ups
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix flour and nuts in medium saucepan. Heat corn syrup, shortening and sugar to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Gradually stir in flour-nut mixture.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water. Add pudding mix and beat well.
Stick in freezer for 5 minutes. After removing, fold in whipping cream.
Spoon 1 cup of mixture into 2 1/2-quart serving bowl.
Top with 1/3 of the wafers and 1/3 of the bananas.
Repeat layers, ending with pudding.
Crumble a few wafers on top.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Lay bacon on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan (Pam first helps clean up).
Sprinkle rice and seasoning packet over the bacon.
Lay chicken breasts on top of rice.
Mix soups and milk (and mushrooms if used).
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 2 hour, uncovered.

title: scallops nicoise
directions: Plunge the tomatoes into a pan of boiling water and hold them under the water for 15 to 20 seconds.
Drain and cool under cold water.
Peel off the skin and cut the tomatoes in half crosswise, parallel to the stem.
Squeeze, pressing out the seeds and excess juice.
Cut the tomatoes into 1/2-inch pieces.
Melt the butter in a large saucepan.
Add the garlic and saute for 5 to 10 seconds. Then add the wine, salt and pepper; cover and cook for about 1 minute.
Add the scallops and tomatoes; bring the mixture to a boil over high heat, shaking the pan occasionally.
Cook for a couple of minutes, until the scallops are cooked through.
Toss in basil.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Clean strawberries, hull and half.
In a blender, puree strawberries and mint.
Add sugar to taste.
Add juices and serve immediately over ice.

title: lamb shanks casserole
directions: Heat oil in a heavy casserole.
Brown lamb on all sides. Remove from pan.
Add carrot, celery, onion and turnip; turn to glaze in fat.
Then return lamb to pan.
Add seasonings and broth; cover and cook until lamb is tender, about 1 hour.
Add rice, raising lamb so that rice is submerged in liquid.
(Add more broth if necessary, to cover rice by 1 inch.)
Add beans and tomatoes. Cover pan tightly.
Return to boil, then simmer about 20 minutes, stirring once, until rice is done and lamb is very tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chilled cucumber soup
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl, stirring and mixing well. Blend in blender at low speed until mixed well.
Serve chilled. Serves 8.

title: chicken wiggle
directions: In large pot, boil hen.
Add celery and garlic (stick a toothpick in em so's yawl can find the onry little things to take out).
Scatter enough salt and pepper to make it taste rite.
Cover with wattah and cook the old sister til the meat is 'bout to fall off bones.
Remove skin and bones.
Now, break up about 1/2 of box spaghetti in the stock and cook til almost tender.
Dump in the ole hen, a can of tiny green peas and pimento.
Let it heat and then add about 2 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce.
Serve with salad and homemade bread.

title: apple raisin bread
directions: Combine 2 1/2 cups flour with yeast and honey.
Beat in milk slowly, then water.
Continue
beating
to
3 minutes. Add butter.
Mix well.
Add
remaining
flour
to
make
dough stiff. Let rest 5 minutes.
Add raisins, apples and cinnamon. Knead for 6 to 7
minutes until fruits are evenly distributed. Place in large greased bowl
and cover with damp towel.
Place in warm place 1 to 1
hours.
Punch down dough.
Knead on floured surface 3 to 4 minutes.
Shape into large ball.
Place in greased and floured baking
pan.
Let
rise
uncovered
20 minutes in a warm place. Preheat
oven to 425°.
Place pan of hot water on lowest rack. Bake
bread for 30 minutes.
Remove water and reduce oven to 300°.
Bake
for
to 40 minutes. Cool on wire rack.
Breakfast bread.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all except nuts and chips.
Mixture will be thick.
Add nuts and chips and spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: dressing for tossed salad
directions: Put all ingredients in a jar and shake well.
Also shake before each use.
Keep unused portion in fridge.

title: crisp baked eggplant
directions: Slice eggplant into 1/2 inch slices. Combine mayonnaise, salt, pepper, and onion. Set aside. Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, and Italian Dressing. Spread both sides of eggplant slices with mayonnaise mixture. Coat with bread crumb mixture and place on a baking sheet. Bake at 425° for 15 to 17 minutes or until golden brown.

title: parmesan cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except the pecans.
Shape into a large ball or 2 smaller balls.
Roll in nuts.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and then Reynolds Wrap and freeze for a day or more to combine the flavors.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients and chill 2 hours.

title: cream of broccoli soup(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Wash broccoli and cut off flowerets.
Set flowerets aside. Peel the stems and chop coarsely.
In large saucepan, place the stems and cover with chicken stock.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Drain and reserve stock.
Puree stems and set aside.
Put flowerets in chicken stock and bring to boil; simmer 5 to 7 minutes.
Melt butter in saucepan and saute onion and celery for 5 minutes.
Stir in flour and cook for 3 to 4 minutes.
Slowly stir in stock and flowerets and puree and add cream.
Bring to boil; add nutmeg, salt and paprika to taste.
Remove from heat. Serve with a dusting of Cheddar cheese.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs until well blended.
Add sugar, salt, nutmeg and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Add hot milk, slowly stirring constantly.
Pour into deep dish pastry shell.
Bake in a 425° oven until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: roast opossum
directions: Put skinned and cleaned opossum in large kettle, cover with water.
Add salt, peppers, onion, and bring to boil; reduce heat, and simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove meat, place in roasting pan. Increase heat and boil water mixture until only 3 cups remain. Pour over meat in roasting pan.
Cover and roast in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add sweet potatoes and celery.
Baste meat, cover, and roast for an additional 30 minutes or until tender.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients well and chill before serving.

title: pork chops casserole
directions: Salt pork chops and brown slightly.
Cut the onion and green pepper in rings. (Same amount as pork chops.)
Place onion and green pepper on bottom of skillet. Add 1 heaping tablespoonful of rice for each pork chop.
Place pork chops on top.
Pour the tomatoes on top of all. Sprinkle salt and add 1/2 to 3/4 cup water.
After coming to a boil, turn on low for 45 minutes. Cover.

title: september relish
directions: Add salt to chopped vegetables and let stand overnight.
Press out juice and drain.
(If desired, run a little water over the mixture and drain.
If this is done, the relish is not quite as salty.)
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and let boil slowly for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Makes 5 or 6 pints.

title: super quick cinnamon twists
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar.
Roll each biscuit into a long rope. Roll in melted butter, then cinnamon-sugar.
Tie in a knot.
Bake according to package directions for biscuits.

title: sharon's pudding dessert
directions: Stir together until thick.
Spread on top of cream cheese mixture and top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt and set aside.
Work shortening with a spoon until fluffy and creamy, then add sugar gradually while continuing to work with a spoon until light.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour mixture alternately with the bananas, a small amount at a time, beating smooth after each addition.
Turn into a greased or oiled loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done (toothpick test).

title: everyone loves orange sherbet
directions: In saucepan, mix gelatin, sugar, water, and salt.
Heat until gelatin dissolves.
Add orange peel and orange juice.
Chill until partially thickened.
Beat until fluffy.
Stir in milk.
Pour into 2-quart refrigerator tray.
Freeze until firm.
Makes about 1 1/2 quarts.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order given. Bake in greased small loaf tins. Bake at 325° for 55 minutes to 1 1/4 hours. Done when toothpick stuck in center of loaf comes out clean. Makes 2 loaves.

title: cream cheese puffs
directions: Blend cream cheese, egg, onion, salt and pepper. Spread mixture 1/4-inch thick on the crackers.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Place crackers on a cookie sheet under the broiler to puff and brown.

title: mexicali chicken
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Cook chicken in oil over medium heat about 15 minutes or until brown. Drain off oil.
Mix salsa, water, salt, oregano, garlic and onion. Pour over chicken.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Place chicken in ungreased baking dish. Cool.
Sprinkle with cheese; cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 400°.
Bake covered 20 minutes; remove cover and bake another 20 minutes.

title: peaches and cream dessert
directions: Stir together flour, pudding mix and baking powder.
Combine egg, milk and melted butter.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix well by hand.
Spread in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Drain peaches, reserving 1/3 cup liquid.
Chop peaches and sprinkle over batter in pan.
Beat together cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/3 cup peach liquid; pour over peaches.
Combine 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: glazed meatballs
directions: Soak bread in milk until soft.
Add eggs, horseradish, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Beat smooth.
Add beef and mix well. Shape into 3/4-inch meatballs.
Place on rack in shallow baking pan.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Heat remaining ingredients to boiling; stir often. Add meatballs; heat through and keep warm.
Serve with wooden picks.
Makes 65.

title: corn bread
directions: Blend eggs, beaten, sour cream, oil and corn.
Add corn meal mix and spread in pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 425°.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Sift first four ingredients together in mixing bowl.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add the sugar one spoonful at a time until blended.
Set aside.
Beat egg yolks until light.
Add lemon juice, rind, melted butter and milk.
Stir egg yolks and juice mixture into flour mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in the egg whites.
Pour into a buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Set in a pan of hot water 1/2-inch deep.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Chill before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon cheese filling
directions: Cook very slowly, adding butter last, until thick and creamy. Cook eggs and sugar, adding lemons and butter.
Use only between layers.

title: lemon fish and rice almondine
directions: Bring water and lemon juice to a boil in saucepan; stir in rice, salt and nutmeg.
Cover tightly and simmer 20 minutes. Remove from heat.
Let stand, covered, until all liquid is absorbed, about 5 minutes.
Stir green onions into rice.
Spoon rice into a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: easy pizza
directions: Lightly brown pizza crusts in preheated 400° oven.
Brown ground chuck and onion together.
Drain meat. Pour 1/2 jar of Pizza Quick sauce over each crust.
Add ground chuck, pepperoni, Cheddar cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Cook at 375° until cheeses are melted.
Makes 2 large pizzas.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix flour, oleo and pecans.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° until brown.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip. Spread over crust.
Top with pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Bring Karo and sugar to full rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add other ingredients.
Make sure some of the corn flakes are crushed.
Drop by tablespoon, after mixing well, on wax paper. Keep in covered container.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Simmer until thickens, about 15 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Bake 20 minutes on greased cookie sheet at 325°.

title: cheese cake
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix with Cool Whip and sour cream until well blended.
Pour into pie shell; top with cherries and chill one hour.

title: campbell's chicken
directions: In a 12 x 8-inch baking dish, arrange chicken skin side up; drizzle with butter.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.
Stir sauce before serving.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Cream butter; gradually add 1 1/4 cups sugar, beating at medium speed of mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in sweet potatoes and milk.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and nutmeg; add to creamed mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Stir in raisins and pecans.
Spoon into greased muffin pan, filling 2/3 full. Combine 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/4 teasponn cinnamon; sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 400° for 22 to 25 minutes.

title: cherry or blueberry crunch
directions: Mix the
first 4 ingredients together and place in pan. Pat this down
in
pan	to make a crust.
Put in oven and bake for about 15 minutes. Take out of oven.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 9-inch pan in oven.
Pour a mixture of the first 5 ingredients over the margarine. Top with sliced peaches, saving 1/2 of the juice-liquid.
As the flour mixture rises above the fruit and starts to brown, pour saved liquid-juice over it evenly.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Wash, core and slice apples.
Heap high into crock-pot, alternately with sugar and cinnamon.
Cover and turn temperature control to high.
Cook 4 hours.
Remove from pot.
Rub through Foley food mill or colander.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal. Makes 4 pints.

title: lemon, banana, pineapple salad
directions: Mix lemon Jello and boiling water.
Add marshmallows to mixture and stir until melted.
Add drained pineapple and sliced bananas to lemon mixture.
Let set in refrigerator in 9 x 13 glass dish.
Put pineapple juice, sugar, flour, margarine and eggs in saucepan. Cook until bubbly and thickened.
Let cool.
Add Cool Whip.
Fold into cooked mixture.
Spoon and spread on top of lemon mixture and refrigerate until well set (several hours).

title: strawberry dessert
directions: In a saucepan, combine the 1/3 cup sugar and the water.
Bring mixture to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes. Stir in vanilla. Sift together flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter or margarine until mixture is crumbly. Add milk and stir just until well combined.
Place berries in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour hot sugar mixture over. Immediately drop dumpling dough in 8 to 10 spoonfuls over berries. Sprinkle dumplings with the remaining 1 tablespoon sugar.
Bake in a very hot oven at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes or until dumplings are done.
Serve warm from casserole into individual dessert dishes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients (but chips).
Stir in chips after all mixed.
Form into balls and flatten out.
Place on a lightly greased and floured baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain corn and pour in medium size bowl.
Add tomato, onion and cheese.
Put enough mayo to mix well.
Chill for at least an hour.

title: apple dapple
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes in an oblong pan.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugars, vanilla and eggs.
Add remaining dry ingredients and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mincemeat brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl with an electric mixer or wooden spoon, beat margarine, brown sugar, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Stir in mincemeat and flour mixture until well combined.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in prepared pan; bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool slightly and cut into squares while still warm.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: corn bread deluxe
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Add shortening and boiling water.
Stir until shortening is all dissolved.
Add beaten egg yolks and flavoring at once and beat well.
Fold in egg whites which have been beaten stiff.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Put the soup diluted with yogurt and white wine or milk over layer of cooked chicken and cooked broccoli in a flat casserole dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese; cover with aluminum foil.
Bake in a 325° oven until heated through, approximately 45 minutes. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice and cook squash in a little water; drain and mash.
Add onion, carrots, soup and sour cream (and pimentos); blend.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with stuffing mix (and peanuts). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until it bubbles.
Serves 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Put into casserole dish and top with chow mein noodles.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken; remove from bone.
Mix soup and sour cream; mix with chicken.
Place in baking dish; top with margarine.
Add cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle poppy seed on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, except Raisin Bran, in very large bowl.
Add beaten eggs and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Add butter and mix again.
Stir in Raisin Bran.
Let set for several hours before baking first time.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
This mixture will keep in the refrigerator for approximately 6 weeks.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Heat cider, sugar, cinnamon, cloves, allspice and nutmeg to boiling.
Simmer 20 minutes. Strain. Serve hot.
Makes 32 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and peanut butter.
Add flour and mix well. Add eggs, soda, salt and baking powder and mix well.
Roll into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with fork.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach salad
directions: Chill the first 4 ingredients in bowl without mixing.
Pour dressing over salad; toss just a few minutes before serving.

title: broccoli-n-rice casserole
directions: Cook rice until tender.
Set aside.
In large skillet, melt butter and saute onions.
Add broccoli.
Cook on medium heat until tender (stir occasionally).
Put broccoli and rice in casserole dish.
In same skillet over medium heat, mix Cheez Whiz, milk and cream of chicken soup until blended.
Pour over broccoli and rice. Mix well.
Cover.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lo-cal stroganoff
directions: Heat oil and butter in heavy skillet.
Saute meat and onions until it loses the red. Mix bouillon cube and cornstarch in water. Add this to all items (except yogurt) to meat.
Simmer 1 hour until meat is tender.
Stir in yogurt and heat thoroughly.
Serve over hot rice.
Yields 4 (3/4-cup) servings.

title: mixed up lasagna
directions: Boil macaroni and drain.
Set aside.
Cook ground chuck and drain grease.
Add salt, spaghetti mix, paste, sauce and water in pan and bring to boil.
Reduce and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Put in shallow 2-quart casserole dish. Layer 1/2 of the cooked macaroni, 1/2 of the cheese and 1/2 the meat, macaroni, cheese and meat.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, uncovered, or until cheese is bubbly.

title: roti chateaubriand
directions: Brown in a preheated oven about 500°.
Melt 1-inch slice from 1 pound of butter or margarine.
Butter must not become brown. Put on the roast the melted butter, pepper, steak spice, parsley and a slice of onion.
Put the roast back in the oven at 325° for rare (12 minutes per pound); medium (15 minutes per pound).

title: italian dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Blend well.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add remaining ingredients, except mashed potatoes and cheese.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with mashed potatoes.
Add Cheddar cheese on top of potatoes.
Heat oven to 350° and bake until cheese is melted and lightly browned.

title: turkey waldorf salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; toss to coat well. Cover; chill.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: fruit salad(the lazy way)
directions: Combine pudding mix with the liquid drained from the two cans of fruit, then add the fruit and mix together.
Place in refrigerator overnight.

title: last minute dessert
directions: Butter an 8-inch square pan and
add a can of cherry or apple pie filling.
Sprinkle
cake
mix
over the pie filling. Pour the melted butter and the
chopped nuts over the cake and pie mixture. Bake for about
35 minutes or until golden brown in a 350° oven. Real good warm or cold with Cool Whip on top.

title: chocolate cheese cupcakes
directions: Mix until smooth.
Do not overmix!
Fill cupcake cups 1/2 full.
Put 1 heaping teaspoonful of filling in the center.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: fiesta corn
directions: Combine corn, Bisquick, sugar and egg.
Put half of batter in pan.
Cover with layer of cheese, green chilies and layer of cheese and rest of batter.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: scalloped irish potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes thin. Place 1/2 of onion and potatoes in a greased casserole baking dish. Mix soup and milk, and pour 1/2 over potatoes & onion. Sprinkle with 1 cup cheese. Layer again potatoes, onion, and liquid, then cheese. Salt & pepper to taste. Cover and bake 1 hour at 350 degrees. Uncover and bake another 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk biscuits(serving size:  8.  preparation time:  0:40)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut butter into tablespoons and with a pastry blender, blend into dry ingredients until texture of cornmeal.
Stir 1/2 cup buttermilk into beaten egg and add mixture to flour mixture.
Stir quickly, adding remainder of buttermilk as necessary until dough forms a ball.
Turn onto floured surface and knead once.
Let dough rest for a minute, then roll out to 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut into 2-inch rounds.
Place biscuits on buttered baking sheet 1 inch apart.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar, coconut, oats, vanilla, and butter.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.

title: tasty baked pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Set aside.
Saute vegetables in remaining butter; add more, if needed.
Add 1 can croutons to veggie mixture.
Mix 3/4 of Cheez Whiz and water into the mixture (until cheese melts).
If mixture is too dry, add more water and cheese. Spread vegetable/crouton mixture into buttered dish.
Add remaining can of croutons.
Place pork chops on top, then add remaining Cheez Whiz on top of pork chops.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: whisky sour punch
directions: Chill ingredients. Mix adding 7-up last. Add ice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Make sure broccoli is cooled.
Mix next 3 ingredients with broccoli.
Crush crackers and mix with butter and cheese; sprinkle on top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chess squares
directions: Combine butter, cake mix and 1 egg in mixing bowl.
Mix well. Press into 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Combine 2 eggs, sugar and cream cheese in mixer bowl.
Mix until smooth.
Spread over cake mix layer.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Cool on wire rack; cut into squares.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Crumble cake
into
x 12-inch pan.
Boil pudding and Jell-O together
with
cups
water until thick.
Add strawberries and spread even over cake.
Refrigerate about 2 hours. Spread Cool Whip over top.

title: coconut bon bons
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl (except paraffin and chocolate chips); shape into balls (quarter size).
Chill in freezer about 10 minutes.
Melt wax and chips together in top of double boiler over 1 inch boiling water.
Dip balls in chocolate and place on wax paper.

title: lemon pie
directions: Put 1 1/2 cups water and sugar on to boil.
While it is boiling, stir in cornstarch dissolved in 1/2 cup water.
When that is thickened, take off burner.
Add beaten egg yolks to mixture. Put back on burner and boil 1 minute longer.
Take off and add lemon juice, lemon peel and butter.
Pour on baked crust.
Top with meringue.

title: chocolate cake(fat free and sugar free)
directions: Combine white and brown Sugar Twin.
In large bowl, sift and mix flour, cocoa, Sugar Twin, soda and baking powder.
In medium bowl, mix skim milk, prunes, extract and egg whites.
Add coffee. Pour moist ingredients into dry; blending well.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll bread dough into a rectangle 1-inch thick on a floured surface.
Spread pizza sauce over dough. Sprinkle with cheese and pepperoni.
Roll as for a jelly roll. Press edge and ends to seal.
Place on baking pan.
Cut slits in top.
Bake for 20 minutes or until brown.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Cut into slices.
Serve with pizza sauce or Ranch dip.

title: fresh butter beans
directions: Into boiling water, place ham hock and let boil 10 to 15 minutes.
Add beans; simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Add okra, butter, salt and pepper.
Continue cooking 30 minutes longer, maintaining water level.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and boil until tender.
Drain . Mix milk and egg. Put squash, milk and egg mixture in casserole dish.
Add cheese, salt, pepper and butter.
Top with cheese and crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: volcano punch
directions: Mix all together; pour over dry ice.
It will give smoking volcano look.

title: round steak tips
directions: Cut round steak in serving size pieces.
Place on cookie sheet; salt and pepper.
Bake at 250° for 5 minutes.
Turn and bake 5 more minutes.
Put sliced tomatoes and onions on top of steak.
Bake at 250° for 10 minutes.
Put cheese on top.
Bake until cheese is melted and brown.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Cut margarine in small pieces.
Cook over slow heat, stirring constantly, until thick (like pudding pie filling).
Cool filling.
Put into cool crust. Use egg whites for meringue topping.

title: easy bisquick lasagne squares
directions: Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch square baking pan.
Layer cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese in dish.
Mix beef, herbs, tomato paste and 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Spoon evenly over top.

title: 24 hour vegetable salad
directions: Dissolve sugar in vinegar and salad oil and heat slightly. Mix all ingredients and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
You may add other vegetables.
This keeps for several days.
(Nice to share with friends and neighbors.)
