title: cracker jacks
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add soda.
Pour over 5 quarts salted popcorn.
Mix well. Bake in 200 degree oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Cool.

title: glazed strawberry pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add water.
Bring to a boil.
Pour 1 quart fresh strawberries into a pie shell.
Garnish with freshly whipped cream.

title: hot and spicy wings
directions: Deep fry chicken wings until crispy, 7 to 10 minutes.
Melt butter and hot sauce.
Place wings in sauce.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes; serve hot.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup, salt and water until a small amount forms a soft ball (234° to 240°) when tested in cold water.
Take out 1/2 cup of this mixture and cook the rest until it forms a hard ball (250° to 265°) when tried in cold water.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook together Vegeburger, onion, olives, cottage cheese, hot sauce, spaghetti mix, spaghetti sauce and oil.
Place one layer of cooked noodles in a baking dish, then layer the vegeburger mixture and add layer of cheese.
Repeat until baking dish is full.
Cover with remainder of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mushroom soup pape' 89'
directions: Combine mushrooms, broth, jam juice and Tandori and simmer until mushrooms are tender.
Add half and half, water and yogurt to stock and simmer for 1 minute.
Add sherry and bring to a scald.
Do not re-boil.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until thick and clear.
Put strawberries in cooked (cooled) 9-inch pie shell.
Pour gelatin mixture over strawberries.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Bake chicken in covered dish at 425° for 15 minutes; drain. Combine tomatoes, cornstarch, garlic and pepper sauce.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened.
Pour sauce over chicken and cover with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 4.

title: meat loaf with cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put one half of the mixture into a baking pan.
Place slices of cheese over this, then cover with the other half of the mixture.
Bake in moderately hot oven (350°) for 1 hour.

title: chicken divan
directions: Toast crumbs in butter beforehand in oven.
Place broccoli or peas (whatever you use for vegetable) in casserole, arrange chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, juice, and curry powder; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over this.
Spread bread crumbs over this.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ham filled angel biscuits
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Cut in shortening. Dissolve yeast in water.

Add yeast mixture and buttermilk to flour mixture, mixing well. Turn dough out on a floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic (about 8 to 10 minutes). Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness and brush with melted butter.
Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter and place 1/2-inch apart on greased baking dish.
Fill with sliced ham.
Top each with a second biscuit. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: chili-onion dip(lo-fat)
directions: Mix all ingredients except the vegetables in a blender.
Serve with the vegetables as a dip.
Can also be used to top fish and baked potatoes.

title: oriental chicken casserole
directions: Drain cans of vegetables and put into saucepan. Heat slowly. Add chicken pieces, soy sauce, onion and salt.
Heat thoroughly. Remove from stove and drain.

title: raisin bran nut cookies
directions: Mix sugar, oil, water, egg whites, cinnamon, baking soda and salt in a large bowl.
Sir in flour and cereal.
Mix in walnuts. Drop rounded teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until browned.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: hearts of palm
directions: In saucepan, combine melted butter, mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt, whip until smooth and cook over low heat stirring constantly until heated through.
Do not let mixture boil.
Pour over hearts of palms.
Sprinkle almonds over top, then cheese. Bake at 425°
for 10 minutes, or until brown and bubbly on top. Serves 6 to 8.

title: eggplant lasagna
directions: Combine sauce and spices.
Place eggplant on baking sheet and brush with oil.
Broil 5 minutes on each side.
Mix Ricotta with parsley.

title: poppin fresh barbecups
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef and onion.
Add barbecue sauce and brown sugar.
Set aside.
Separate biscuits and flatten each one and place one biscuit in each greased muffin pan hole. Spoon meat mixture into cups, sprinkle each with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Serve with green salad and enjoy!
Serves 2.

title: bell pepper hash
directions: Grind first 3 ingredients and mix together.
Pour boiling water over mixture.
Drain.
Pour boiling water over again.
Let stand for 10 more minutes, then drain.
Add vinegar, salt and sugar.
Add spices to taste.
Let cook for 10 minutes.
Cool and pack in jars.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake according to box directions.
Mix sweetened condensed milk and cream of coconut together.
When cake is done, poke holes with handle of a wooden spoon (lots of holes) and pour milk mixture over cake.
After cake is completely cool, cover with Cool Whip and frozen (thawed) coconut.

title: chinese cabbage salad
directions: Crush noodles and brown in 1/4 cup of butter.
Add soup mix (from Ramen noodle package) and 1/4 cup sesame seed.
Let cool. Toss with cabbage, onions and almonds.

title: shrimp appetizers
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Fill hot dog rolls and arrange on small trays.
Garnish with radish roses and sprigs of parsley.

title: summer slaw or freezer slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, pepper and onion in bowl. In small saucepan mix sugar, salt, celery seed, mustard seed, oil and vinegar. Place on low heat and simmer until sugar dissolves. Pour over vegetables and mix well. Sprinkle with grated carrots. Refrigerate covered. Stir before serving.

title: pasta e fagioli
directions: In 5 to 6-quart Dutch oven, heat oil over medium heat until hot.
Add onion and celery and cook until tender (about 10 minutes).

title: orange wassail
directions: Steep orange supplement in hot water with cinnamon stick and clove.
Rum extract may be added, if desired.

title: cinnamon raisin rice pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients and pour into a 1-quart baking dish.
Place dish in a shallow baking pan filled 1-inch deep with water.
Bake 45 minutes or until center of pudding is firm.
Serve cool or warm with a dollop of low-fat vanilla yogurt.
Serves 6.

title: beef cracker spread
directions: Mix together.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: casserole-one dish dinner
directions: Cook cubed beef in water until tender, about 20 minutes. Remove meat and add soup and noodles.
Cook until noodles are done.
Add remaining ingredients and the beef and put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with crumbs and bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Serves 12.

title: persimmon fudge
directions: Mix pulp, sugar, milk and syrup in large pot.
Cook slowly for 1 1/2 to 2 hours to reach soft ball stage (230°).
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir often.
Add butter; beat well.
When it begins to thicken, stir in 1 cup chopped nuts.
Spread into a buttered 8 1/2 x 13-inch pan.

title: german chocolate sour cream fudge cake
directions: Mix together and pour in 2 round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool!

title: apple nut cake
directions: Spread on cake while cake is hot.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: In medium skillet, melt butter; add stuffing mix and celery. Cook, stirring often, for 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Add 3/4 cup water.
Place 1 cup in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Distribute uncooked, thawed broccoli over stuffing mix and cover with chicken pieces.
In medium bowl, combine chicken soup and mayonnaise.
Spread over chicken and top with reserved cup of browned stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until bubbly.
Can be made day before.

title: irish bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add the egg. Add measured 3 cups firmly packed flour, plus dry ingredients, alternately with milk. Add caraway seed and raisins.
Pour into tube pan. Sprinkle sugar over top and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 or 10 minutes. Rub butter over the top of bread as soon as you remove from the oven.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Arrange potatoes overlapping in a shallow buttered ovenproof dish.
Pour on fruit juices.
Sprinkle with sugar, salt and pepper.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: yellow rice and ham
directions: Bring rice to boil.
Add ham and peas.
Cover and cook according to rice directions.
Add tomato.
Makes a great one-dish dinner in a hurry.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Stir together in a large bowl.
Layer over tortillas in casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 cup shredded Monterey Jack cheese and 1/2 cup shredded Colby cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit crisp
directions: Place pie filling in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix margarine with cake mix until crumbly.
May need to add more margarine.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts, if desired. Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350° or until golden brown. Serve warm with vanilla ice cream. Very quick, easy and inexpensive and delicious.

title: sweet and sour spareribs
directions: Have butcher cut through the bones in 1 1/2 inch parts. Combine next 4 ingredients; mix well and let stand for 30 minutes, then add cornstarch.
Cook 2/3 of the mixture in a pan until thickened.
Add cornstarch and set aside.
Heat 2 to 3 inches of oil until very hot (360°).
Drain spareribs; add to oil, 1/4 at a time, cooking 3 to 4 minutes, until very brown.
Cook all the meat, keeping the temperature at 360°.
Drain well, then drop into prepared sauce.
Mix and chill.
Serve at room temperature.

title: apple delight
directions: Fill pie plate 2/3 full with sliced, peeled apples.
Spread 1 tablespoon of sugar and cinnamon over apples.
Combine flour, 3/4 cup sugar, margarine and egg.
Spread over apples.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix together, form into a roll and chill.
Slice and bake until done at 350°.

title: sky-high strawberry pie
directions: In a large bowl, mash enough berries to equal 3 cups.
In a saucepan, combine the sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in mashed berries and water, mix well.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly, cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat, add food coloring if desired.
Pour into a large bowl.
Fold in remaining berries, pile into shell.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours. In a small mixing bowl, whip cream until soft peaks form. Sprinkle pudding mix over cream and beat until stiff.
Pipe around edge of pie or dollop on each slice.

title: mustard coated grilled flank steak
directions: Mix mustard, soy sauce, whipping cream, thyme, ginger and black pepper.
Marinate steaks in the mixture at least 24 hours and then grill.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix together first four ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients, pour over vegetables and put in refrigerator overnight.

title: black beans, cheese and brown rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Heat oil in saute pan over medium heat.
Add garlic, onion and green pepper and cook until clear.
Stir into beans then mix with rice.
Stir milk into Ricotta cheese.
Blend in 3 cups Cheddar cheese.
Layer in casserole beans, cheese, ending with beans.
Add pepper or hot sauce if desired.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Just before serving sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Allow cheese to melt. Serves 6.

title: gouda cheese spread
directions: Cut a 1/2-inch slice off top of Gouda cheese.
Remove red wrapping.
Carefully scoop out cheese, leaving 1/4-inch shell intact; set shell aside.
Grate remaining cheese.

title: potato puffs
directions: Beat the eggs, and add potatoes.
Combine flour, baking powder, and salt; stir into potato mixture.

title: harvest muffins
directions: Grease mini muffin pans.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Combine apples, carrot and sugar and set aside.
In a separate bowl, combine remaining dry ingredients.
To dry mixture, add egg, vanilla, and oil and mix well.
Stir in apple mixture.
Add coconut, raisins, and pecans.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full with batter.
Top each muffin cup with 1 teaspoon of topping.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
Let muffins cool completely and then drizzle with glaze.

title: honey butter
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy.
Stir in honey and cinnamon.
Cover and refrigerate. Yield: 1 cup.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken in a large skillet on both sides.
Remove chicken.
In reserved oil, saute onion, green peppers and garlic (if cloves are used).

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over all-bran.
Set aside.
Mix the other dry ingredients.
Add eggs, butter and buttermilk.
Beat until well mixed.
Add the hot cereal.
Bake the number of muffins needed at 400° for 20 minutes.
Place the remaining batter in an airtight container and keep in the refrigerator.
Batter will keep for 6 weeks.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple syrup.
Add other ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: applesauce fruitcake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with applesauce, beating each time.
Stir in raisins, fruit and pecans.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Test with toothpick.
Cool in pan.

title: texas beans
directions: Fry hamburger, onions and peppers until meat is brown.
Add the remaining ingredients and bake until bubbly at 375°.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix sugar, molasses, oil, coffee and egg together.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers.
Soak for 2 hours in a solution of 1 part salt to 12 parts water.
Drain.
Add sliced onions.

title: red cabbage and apple slaw
directions: Smoothly mix mayonnaise, yogurt, sugar, salt, celery seed, mustard and pepper.
Lightly mix cabbage, apples and parsley in a large bowl.
Fold in the dressing until well combined.
Chill 1 hour or longer to blend flavors.
Serve in a bowl lined with romaine lettuce.

title: hidden valley beans
directions: Bring beans with liquid to a boil in saucepan.
Drain liquid and immediately pour Hidden Valley salad dressing over beans. Serve hot.
Can be served next day as cold salad.
Top with sliced almonds, water chestnuts or canned French fried onions.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Combine ingredients in a large bowl; stir gently to mix.
Spoon into a 3-quart casserole.
Cover and bake in a 325° oven for 2 hours.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: apple butter
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pan.
Cook, uncovered, in oven for 2 hours at 350°.
Seal in jars or just store in refrigerator.

title: sugar cookies(tea cakes)
directions: Work in enough plain flour to make a stiff dough.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Dissolve soda in milk.
Add alternating with flour.
Chill until dough is stiff.
Roll out and cut.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
This is an old-fashioned tea cake. Over 100 years old.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Tenderize steak; cut into thin 1-inch strips.
Shake with flour, salt and pepper in bag.
Brown in 1/4 cup butter in saucepan.
Saute onions, celery, mushrooms and garlic in 1/4 cup butter in skillet.
Add to steak.
Add sour cream, soup, wine, catsup, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce, dry mustard, thyme and bay leaf; mix well.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve over rice or Chinese noodles.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle nutmeg on top. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350° until slightly firm.

title: peanut butter cookie mix
directions: Layer ingredients into jar in order given.
Press each layer firmly before adding the next ingredient.

title: dibi's chicken and rice
directions: Put rice in bottom of large, flat, greased casserole dish. Place chicken breasts on rice.
Combine cream soups and water. Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle dry soup mix over top.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serves 6.

title: squash souffle
directions: Steam squash and onion together.
Mash squash and add butter. Mix all other ingredients with squash.
Put in casserole and bake for 1 hour at 325°.
After 35 to 40 minutes, sprinkle grated cheese on top.

title: mock lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown beef and onion, then drain. Stir in spaghetti sauce and tomato sauce. Stir until bubbly.
Combine shredded cheese and sour cream.
Pour hot beef mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon cheese and cream mixture over meat.
Roll crescent dough into rectangles and place them on cheese mixture. Mix Parmesan cheese and melted butter together and crumble over crescent rolls.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 25 minutes.

title: reuben dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix together cheese, dressing, sauerkraut and meat.
Spoon into a 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with caraway seed.
Bake 20 minutes.
Serve with crisp rye crackers or cocktail rye bread.
Makes 3 cups.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix well and store in airtight container.
Just heat water and add 2 tablespoons mix.
Top with marshmallows, if desired.

title: egg substitute for one egg(no fat egg substitute for one egg)
directions: Substitute water and baking powder for recipes calling for one egg.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Place apples and sugar in mixing bowl and mix. Let stand 30 minutes (will form own juice). Add eggs and oil; blend. Mix flour, cinnamon, soda and salt. Stir in. Add vanilla and nuts. Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until cakes tests done. This cake may be frozen and improves with age. May also be made into cupcakes.

title: creole chicken gumbo
directions: In a large, heavy pot, heat oil.
Gradually add flour, stirring constantly over low heat until roux is medium brown.
Add okra, onion and celery.
Cook until okra is no longer stringy. Add green onions, garlic, parsley, thyme, marjoram, basil, tomatoes with juice, ham and chicken.
Slowly stir chicken stock into gumbo.
Cook sausage; drain and add to gumbo.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining seasonings.
Add shrimp during last 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 8.

title: angel cornsticks(this is a southern living recipe)
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Combine eggs, buttermilk and oil, then add to dry ingredients.
Stir until batter is smooth. Spoon batter into well-greased cornstick pans, filling half full. Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: weepless meringue
directions: In a small saucepan mix 1/4 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt. Stir in water, stirring over medium heat.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 to 2 minutes, or until thick and clear.	Cool completely.

title: fast fabulous fruit(makes 4 servings)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into square or round baking dish or 4 separate bowls.
Refrigerate until firm and chilled (at least one hour).
Crust can be used if desired.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; drain well. Mix with cheese, milk, onion, salt, pepper and paprika. Grease a casserole dish. Put all in a dish and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream
butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Add to butter and sugar mix.
Stir in
vanilla and pecans.
Spoon batter into greased and floured 13
x
9-inch
pan.
Bake for 18 minutes at 325°. Remove
cake; cover top with marshmallows.
Put back in until soft,
to 3 minutes.
Spread marshmallows and frost immediately.

title: orange julius
directions: Pour all ingredients into blender and mix until smooth and frothy.

title: oreo surprise
directions: Put pudding mixes and enough milk to make each (6 cups) in shaker or mixer and shake or mix until mixes are the consistency of pudding.
Break up the Oreo cookies into 9 x 12-inch cake pan. Pour pudding over the Oreo cookies and then spoon the Cool Whip over the pudding.
Enjoy.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix melted oleo and sugar with a fork until sugar is fully soaked.
Add milk and eggs.
Then beat while slowly adding flour. When mixed well, place on cookie sheet by spoonfuls and bake at 400° for about 10 minutes or until golden.

title: pineapple bars
directions: Drain pineapple.
Beat eggs.
Add eggs to sugar and blend until of a thick consistency.
Add flour to egg and sugar mixture a little at a time, blending each time until flour is covered. Add nuts and pineapple.
Grease a loaf pan and fill with mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Fold cocoa and sugar together.
Add all other ingredients. Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour in bowl.
Break eggs into this.
Mix gently with fork.
Add melted margarine and mix gently.
Add milk and vanilla and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: fried shrimp batter
directions: Combine all ingredients, except shrimp and oil, for frying. Beat well.
Place in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Dry shrimp thoroughly on paper towels and dip in batter.
Fry in hot oil at 375° until golden brown; drain on paper towels or drain in fish drainer.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Heat fruit in saucepan.
Melt margarine in baking dish. Combine flour, sugar and milk.
Pour into baking dish in center of melted margarine.
Pour drained fruit in center of mixture.
Do not stir.
Batter will rise to make a crust.
Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown.

title: orange dessert
directions: Add Jello to hot water and stir until dissolved.
Add orange juice, oranges and pineapple.
Mix thoroughly and pour into 9 x 12-dish.
Chill until congealed.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine first four ingredients in saucepan.
Heat to boiling over medium heat.
Continue cooking, stirring frequently, to 236° (soft ball stage).
Remove from heat.
Add butter and extract. Cool to lukewarm.
Beat until mixture holds its shape and then add Marshmallow Creme and fruit.
Beat until thick and then spread quickly in lightly buttered pan.
When firm, mark into squares. Makes about 1 1/2 pounds.

title: gram's sweet and sour salad dressing
directions: Beat egg in saucepan.
Add flour and dry mustard.
Also add the salt.
Beat together.
Take the vinegar and water and fill the measuring cup (1 cup) with sugar, together, all in the same cup until it overflows.
Add this to the egg mixture and cook unit it boils up good once.
Good on cabbage, slaw, banana salad, as dip for chicken fingers, etc.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except chow mein noodles and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Top with can of chow mein noodles (large can).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and add the following dressing:

title: greek apple cake
directions: Cream together eggs and 1 1/2 cups sugar well. Add flour, baking powder and oil. Mix thoroughly. Add juice of 1 orange and vanilla. Pare, core and slice 4 apples. Mix with cinnamon and 1 tablespoon sugar. Pour egg batter into round (9-inch) cake pan and spread half of apple mixture over batter. Spread rest of batter over apple mixture and bake cake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tuna crunch
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup noodles.
Drain and chunk tuna and combine with remaining ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir and top with reserved noodles.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Serve with soy sauce.
Serves 4.

title: sawdust pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients; mix well. Place in unbaked pie shell at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until set.
Do not overbake!
Let cool.
Top pie with sliced bananas and whipped cream over the bananas.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Puree in blender peppers, onions and vinegar.
Strain through cheese cloth.
Add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups juice.
Cook in a large kettle 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 package pectin; boil for 1 minute.
Add 2 drops of green food coloring. Pour into jars and seal.

title: farmhouse barbecue muffins
directions: Flatten biscuits, place in greased muffin tin; set aside. Brown beef; drain.
In small bowl, mix ketchup, brown sugar, vinegar and chili powder; stir until smooth.
Add to meat; mix well.
Put 1/4 cup in each muffin tin.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool for 5 minutes before serving.

title: pistachio salad-pudding
directions: Empty boxes of pudding into mixing bowl.
Add undrained pineapple; stir well.
Add marshmallows.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add broccoli, mushroom soup, nacho soup and rice.
Put into casserole and bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: sourdough waffles
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Let stand 2 or 3 days.
This is your starter.
The night before add flour and milk.
Next morning take out starter (1/3 to 1/2 cup).
Keep in refrigerator for next batch.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Can be used for pancakes or waffles.

title: party punch
directions: Combine all frozen juices, pineapple juice, cranberry juice and water.
Chill until ready to serve.
Pour juice mixture into punch bowl.
Add ginger ale and club soda.
Yield: 7 quarts.

title: swedish glogg
directions: Cook all the spices except the almonds in a small saucepan in water to a boil.
Add brown sugar to enough water to cover in a large 8-quart pot.
Add the water-spice mixture to brown sugar-water mixture, then add wine, gin and grain alcohol.
Bring to a boil (briefly) after each addition.
Add the almonds and burn off some of the alcohol covering the pot to stifle the flame.

title: blueberry buttermilk biscuits
directions: Combine flour and next 4 ingredients in a bowl; stir well. Add blueberries; toss well.
Combine buttermilk and melted margarine; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Drop dough by heaping tablespoonfuls onto a baking sheet coated with cooking spray.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar evenly over biscuits.
Bake at 450°for 11 minutes, or until golden.

title: pepper steak
directions: Mix soup mix with water.
Add vegetables to browned meat strips.
Stir-fry.
Add soy sauce and soup mixture and cook until thickened, but vegetables are still crisp.
Pour over cooked rice. Serve.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except corn flakes.
Sprinkle on top and bake, uncovered, 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch greased casserole at 350°.

title: erwtensoep(dutch green peas soup)
directions: Boil the legs/ribs/tail in a large pot (8 liters or 2 gallons: see note) in the 4 liters of water with the split peas for at least one hour, until the meat is tender.
If a fresh sausage is used, boil it for the last half hour with the other ingredients.
Stir occasionally.
Take out all the meat.
Cut the meat from the bones and add to the soup.
Cut the sausage in slices, but add it only at the end.
Add all other ingredients and boil 20 to 30 minutes over a low heat.
Stir occasionally.
Add the sausage and pepper to taste.
The soup should be very substantial.
Serve in soup bowls, accompanied with slices of rye bread (black bread) with bacon.
The taste of the soup improves when the soup is made two days in advance.
When reheating (in a smaller portion as desired) stir continuously or reheat in microwave.

title: veracruz bean tortillas
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook sausage and onion about 10 minutes or until done.
Drain off excess fat.
Add refried beans; stir until hot, about 5 minutes.
Soften the tortillas in a microwave or on a hot grill.
Spread each tortilla with 1/4 cup bean and sausage mixture.
Divide cheese evenly over all tortillas, about 1 rounded tablespoonful each.
Roll tortillas and place them in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with water and cover with foil.
Place in 250° oven until serving.
Makes 12 servings.

title: sportsman's pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar with which the spices have been mixed. Add egg, milk, bread, raisins, nuts and soda, dissolved in a little water.
Bake in a slow oven (350°) for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.
Serve with caramel sauce.

title: double chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Gradually blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake; cookies will be soft.
They will puff while baking and flatten while cooling.
Cool sightly; remove from cookie sheet onto wire rack.
Cool completely.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: squash casserole #2
directions: Cook squash down.
Mash and add soup, sour cream, carrot, onion, salt, pepper and red pepper.
Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and sprinkle a layer of bread crumbs in the bottom. Add the squash mixture and cover the mixture with bread crumbs and generous bits of margarine or butter.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: spinach dip in pumpernickel bread
directions: Mix the cream cheese with sour cream.
Add the dry vegetable soup.
Cook spinach; squeeze all water out.
Add dry spinach to cream cheese mix.
Cut round top from pumpernickel bread; take all bread out, leaving a shell.
Fill shell with mixture.
Place on large tray surrounded by bread pieces.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: 5 hour baked beef stew
directions: Mix all together in a large roasting pan with a tight cover. Put in oven at 250° for 5 hours.
Do not uncover or open oven.

title: mediterranean linguini
directions: Coat skillet with cooking spray.
Over medium heat, add mushrooms and next 3 ingredients, saute.
Add artichokes, Italian dressing, olives and parsley.
Cook 3 minutes.

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: Arrange tomatoes in large, shallow dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in covered jar; shake well and pour over tomatoes. Cover and chill for several hours.
Use a dish with cover, turning upside-down while chilling.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Bring vinegar, oil, mustard, salt, sugar and celery seed to boil.
Shave cabbage fine or chop in blender.
Also, add chopped onion.
Pour 1 cup sugar over slaw and let set while making dressing.
When dressing boils, pour over cabbage.
Put into containers and refrigerate.
Very good.

title: carrot cake
directions: Note:
If using self-rising flour, omit baking powder and baking soda.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix together sugar, molasses, butter, cinnamon, cloves, allspice, ginger, soda and water.
Add flour and mix well.
Add eggs, beaten.
Mix.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Test with toothpick.
Done when pick comes out dry.
Do not overbake.

title: apple-carrot slaw
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine mayonnaise and next 3 ingredients.
Pour over cabbage mixture, tossing gently to coat.
Cover and chill.
Serve on cabbage leaves, if desired.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Mix well butter, sugar and eggs.
Stir in Bisquick, nuts and chocolate chips.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake in a 350° oven 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut bars while warm.

title: saucy italian beans
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and heat in saucepan.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with cheese and put in oven long enough to heat through and melt cheese.

title: minted tea
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags; cover and set aside 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags, squeezing gently.
Stir in sugar and next 3 ingredients.
Chill.
To serve, stir in ginger ale and garnish, if desired.
Yields 3 1/2 quarts.

title: jim's no-hurt chili
directions: Brown meat in skillet and drain.
In a large pot, blend all ingredients well.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce to low heat, cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cook until clear.
Cool and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Brown beef, lots of onion and green peppers, salt, pepper and very little chili powder.
Add 2 cans stewed tomatoes and 1 can red beans (drained).
Let simmer about 30 minutes before serving. Add cut up cabbage.
Simmer until cabbage is done to suit your taste.

title: melon cream cheese salad
directions: Beat together first 3 ingredients until smooth and fluffy. Add celery and fruit.
Lastly add whipped topping, chill.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix pineapple, marshmallows and ground cranberries; let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Whip cream; add sugar and mix with the cranberry mixture.
Freeze.
Sprinkle chopped walnuts on top, if desired.
This will keep a long time.
If it melts at mealtime, it can be refrozen.

title: spaghetti salad supreme
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
Chill.
It's better if it marinates overnight.
You may substitute any of your favorite vegetables or delete any one. May use French or Catalina dressing also.

title: twinkie cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix pudding and cream cheese well.
It will have some lumps.
Lay Twinkies, filling side up, in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Pour half of pudding mix over Twinkies.
Then half of fruit filling.
Repeat; top with Cool Whip and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine water, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook until thick and clear.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O and strawberries.
Stir until berries are cooled.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell and refrigerate until set.
Top with Cool Whip and serve.

title: peanut butter cup mousse
directions: Combine all the ingredients and mix well. Refrigerate.

title: turkey-chicken-broccoli casserole(good leftover recipe.)
directions: Place cooked, drained broccoli in a layer in 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Add 1 layer of cooked turkey or chicken.
Combine 1 can of uncooked cream of celery soup and 1/3 cup milk.
Pour over first 2 layers.
Spread 1/2 to 1 cup shredded cheese on top.
Bake at 450° about 15 to 20 minutes, covered or uncovered.

title: chicken with olives
directions: Brown chicken, then add rosemary, sage, garlic and wine.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook and reduce liquid, then add tomato sauce and chicken broth. Bring to a boil, then lower heat and cook 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Add green olives.
Simmer 10 to 12 minutes. Serves 4.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Line dish with 1/2 of the Oreo cookies.
Mix cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk; pour over cookies.
Mix 2/3 of Cool Whip with pudding; spread over cookies.
Put the other 1/2 of cookies in dish.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Garnish with cookie crumbs.

title: congealed apricot salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add marshmallows and dissolve. Add cold water.
Let set until it begins to congeal.
Add pineapple and bananas.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Put all ingredients in pan except Jell-O.
Cook until thick and clear.
Remove from heat; add Jell-O, stirring well.
Pour over berries.
Chill 2 hours.
Top with whipped cream.

title: the best pecan pie
directions: Place all ingredients, except pecans, in a large bowl.
Mix until well blended.
Pour pecans in and stir until all are coated. Pour all ingredients into an unbaked pie shell (deep dish 9-inch) and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Allow to cool before serving.

title: chicken with yogurt (indian)(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Put chopped onions, garlic and ginger in an electric blender. Add 6 tablespoons of water and blend.
Fry chicken in oil for 7 to 8 minutes until they're brown on all sides.
Turn heat to low and put paste from blender with chicken pieces.
Raise heat to medium and fry 9 to 10 minutes.
Add yogurt, one tablespoon at a time, and stir for another 10 minutes.
Add salt and cayenne pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with any kind of rice.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Cut aluminum foil into 12-inch squares for each piece of boneless chicken.
Spray aluminum foil with Pam.
Place a piece of chicken on each piece of aluminum foil.
Slice potatoes and onion over each piece of chicken.
Put 1 tablespoon butter on each and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Fold aluminum foil over the chicken.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Brown ribs.
Combine
all
ingredients in bowl and pour over ribs. Turn ribs over so they are well covered with sauce. Cover with foil and put
in oven.
Bake at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until
done.
Turn	ribs
over
while cooking. Remove foil the last 1/2 hour.

title: polynesian dressing for fruit
directions: Mix together and allow to sit overnight in refrigerator. Serve as a fruit dip or as dressing.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown meat in butter in heavy skillet. Drain pineapple (save juice). Combine water, vinegar, brown sugar, cornstarch, salt, soy sauce and 1 cup pineapple juice. Cook until clear and thickened. Add meat (pineapple, green pepper and onions added later).	Cover and cook over low heat about 1 hour or until fork-tender.

title: quick chicken dinner
directions: Dice chicken and fry in butter; add basil, salt, pepper, garlic powder and meat seasoning while cooking.
As the chicken is cooking, boil water and add noodles and cook until tender; drain water. Then add cheese.
When chicken is ready, add can of tomatoes and sauce. Cook until cheese is melted for noodles.
When finished put chicken and noodles in a large bowl and stir together.

title: hot bacon casserole
directions: Fry 8 oz. bacon, drain and break up into small pieces.
Fry green pepper, onions and hamburg in the bacon fat/drippings until soft and done.
Add brown sugar, vinegar and mustard.
Microwave bacon, peppers, onions, hamburg, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard, covered for 6 - 7 minutes.

title: zucchini bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease two loaf pans.
In a large bowl, mix all the ingredients.
Beat on low speed for at least one minute, scraping the sides constantly.
Pour into pans and bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, about one hour.
Cool 10 minutes, then remove from pan and cool completely before serving.
Store in refrigerator; freezes well.

title: cabbage fruit salad
directions: Mix cabbage, pineapple, apples and grapes.
Mix remaining ingredients; toss with cabbage mixture until evenly coated. Chill.
Yields 6 servings.

title: peanut butter and jelly pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and peanut butter, mixing until well blended.
Add sugar and milk; mix well.
Spoon cream cheese mixture into crust; chill.
Spread with preserves and top with whipped topping.

title: dilly beans
directions: Shake often to dissolve ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Ready in 2 to 3 days.

title: zero dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in jar with tightly fitted top.
Shake well before using.
Also can add chopped parsley, green pepper, mustard seed and horseradish.
One tablespoon yields 3 calories.

title: stuffed fish
directions: Make bread stuffing.
Eliminate poultry seasoning.
In baking dish, layer with fish.
Spread stuffing.
Top with layer of fish. Dot with butter.
Add salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until done.
(It will flake.)

title: peanut butter rice krispy bars
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients in large saucepan and bring just to a boil.
Immediately remove from heat and stir in peanut butter until melted.
Stir in cereal until well mixed, then place in well buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and cover cereal bars, then place in refrigerator until chocolate is hardened.
Cut into bars.

title: simple spareribs
directions: Put spareribs in crock-pot.
Add jar of barbecue sauce. Simmer on low for 8 hours.
Fat will cook off into sauce.
Will melt in your mouth.

title: mom's oven fried chicken
directions: Mix together all ingredients except chicken and crackers. Dip chicken in oil mixture, then roll in cracker crumbs. Bake in greased pan at 350° for about an hour or until juices run clear when chicken is pierced with a fork (time depends on size of chicken pieces).

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar well.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Add carrots and pineapple.
Beat well. Bake in 3 (8-inch) layer pans which have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: sour cream rice with chilies(microwave)
directions: Mix rice, broth and garlic in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly; microwave on High 9 to 10 minutes.
Stir in half of the cheese, sour cream and chilies.
Cover and microwave for 2 to 3 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cover and let stand about 4 minutes, or until cheese is melted.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat soup to boiling.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water and add the soup.
Mix cheese with mayo and add to soup by mixing with mixer.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased mold* with mayo.
Refrigerate; unmold and serve on bed of lettuce with Ritz crackers.

title: nancy's coconut crunch torte
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, coconut and nuts. Beat egg whites with salt and vanilla until foamy. Gradually add sugar and continue beating until egg whites form stiff peaks. Fold cracker mixture into egg white mixture. Spread in well-greased 9-inch pie plate or 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. Cool. Cut in wedges and top with ice cream, if desired.

title: chocolate buttermilk cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; grease 3 (9 inch) cake pans. Beat butter at medium speed with a mixer; gradually add sugar until fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time; add vanilla.

title: spicy avocado dip
directions: Mash avocados with fork or potato masher until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour or until chilled.
Serve with Nabisco crackers, cut up vegetables or chips.

title: riso verda(green rice)
directions: In a large skillet, add butter, olive oil, spinach, onions, parsley, salt and pepper.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Add rice and 1/2 of the chicken broth.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add remainder of chicken broth and simmer for 20 minutes.
Just before serving, add Parmesan cheese on the top.
Cover until it melts then serve. This dish can be prepared the night before and it is still wonderful.
Excellent with all meats and seafood!!!

title: hershey's old fashioned chocolate pudding(microwave)
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, cornstarch and salt in a 2-quart microwavable bowl. Slowly whisk in milk. Stir until cornstarch is completely dissolved.
Cook on High power 7 to 10 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes, until pudding begins to thicken. Stir in butter and vanilla.
Pour into 4 individual serving dishes. Cover with plastic wrap.
Chill.

title: heavenly gooey cake
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine, 1 egg and pecan pieces and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar, 2 eggs and pineapple and pour over batter.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350 degrees in a pre-heated oven.
Cool before cutting into squares.

title: grapefruit marmalade
directions: Wipe fruit and slice very thin, rejecting only seeds and core of grapefruit.
Measure and add 3 times the quantity of water.
Let stand in an earthen dish overnight.
Next morning, boil for 10 minutes.
Leave until next day, then boil for 2 hours.
Measure an equal amount of sugar.
Boil stirring occasionally to prevent burning, about one hour.
Pour into glasses and seal.
Makes about two quarts.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and eggs.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Add all dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll out biscuits on floured wax paper.
Place apples on biscuit; fold over and crimp edges with fork.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch bake dish.
Repeat with all biscuits.
Melt margarine. Add sugar, cinnamon and 7-Up; mix well.
Pour over apples and biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Will be soupy after it comes out of oven.
Spoon juice over dumplings.

title: french chicken(serves 4)
directions: Wash chicken.
Place in baking dish.
Add spices, garlic and bouillon cubes.
Add hot water.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Remove bay leaf.

title: seven minute icing
directions: Put all ingredients, except vanilla, in top of double boiler over boiling water.
Beat with rotary beater for 7 minutes or with an electric beater for 4 minutes or until icing is stiff enough to stand in peaks.
Put in marshmallows and melt them.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes in salted water; drain well.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, eggs, onions, and cheese together.
Sprinkle with crackers or bread.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue beef (pork)
directions: Brown meat in hot fat and add water.
Cover and cook 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Reserve broth.
Add enough water to make 2/3 cup.
Shred meat with fork.
Cook onion and celery until tender.
Add beef broth and remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes or until desired consistency. Good to freeze.

title: fruit punch
directions: In very large punch bowl, pour in all juices.
Mix well.
Now add Kool-Aid, sugar and ginger ale.
Mix well.
Ready to serve with ice.

title: cherry-pineapple salad
directions: Mix and chill before serving.

title: troop peanut butter cups
directions: Mix 1 cup butter, graham cracker crumbs, powdered sugar and peanut butter together until well blended.
Pat firmly into a 10 x 9 x 4-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and butter together.
Pour over peanut butter mixture in pan.
Refrigerate.

title: banana chocolate chip bread
directions: In a bowl, cream sugar and shortening.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and bananas until thoroughly blended.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir just until combined. Fold in chocolate chips.
Spoon into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until the bread tests done with a toothpick.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: curried chicken strips
directions: Remove skin and bones from chicken breasts.
Cut chicken breasts into 3 x 1/2-inch strips.
Set aside.
In 12-inch skillet over medium heat in hot salad oil, cook green pepper and onion until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in curry powder and salt; cook 1 minute.
Add chicken to mixture in skillet; over high heat, cook until chicken just loses its pink color, about 3 to 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat to medium; stir in cream; cook until mixture thickens slightly.
Makes 4 servings. Contains about 395 calories per serving with heavy cream.

title: butter pecan crisps
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix until well blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until lightly brown.
Let stand a few minutes (1 or 2) before removing from baking sheet to cooling rack.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: pastry for fried pies
directions: Mix evaporated milk and egg; set aside.
Combine flour, salt and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle milk and egg mixture over flour mixture.
Stir with a fork until dry ingredients are moistened. Shape dough into a ball and wrap in waxed paper.
Chill at least 1 hour or until ready to use.
Yields 24 (4-inch) pies.

title: chicken and spaghetti casserole
directions: Boil chicken until cooked and tender; salt and pepper the water.
Save broth to cook spaghetti in.
Debone chicken.
Saute onion and bell pepper in 3/4 butter.
Drain spaghetti and return to pot.
Melt cheese in hot spaghetti and 1/4 butter.
Add Ro-Tel, peas, corn and cream of mushroom soup.
Add red pepper.
Stir. Saute onion, bell pepper and chicken.
Stir until all cheese is melted.
Pour in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, then reduce heat to 200° for about 1 hour.

title: do it yourself mini corn dogs
directions: Sift cornmeal, flour and salt together.
Combine egg, Carnation and oil.
Stir Carnation mixture into cornmeal mixture. Pat wieners dry with paper towels.
Insert skewer through end of wiener.
Dip wiener completely in cornmeal mixture.
Pull out, twisting slightly to form even coating.
Deep fry in hot fat (375°) for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove skewer.
Drain on paper towels.
Keep warm.
Serve with Mustard Sauce.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and cherries.
Combine 3 tablespoons pineapple juice with cream cheese and mayonnaise; cream together.
Fold in pineapple, cherries, nuts and marshmallows.

title: rhine wine punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in punch bowl.
Set on bed of ice. Makes 25 to 30 cups.

title: beef and radish ryes
directions: In work bowl of food processor fitted with steel knife blade, whip cream cheese.
Combine all remaining ingredients, except party rye, until smooth.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serve on party rye bread.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding
and milk as directed on package.
Stir in other ingredients in large bowl.
Refrigerate.

title: walnut coffee cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat egg, buttermilk, butter and vanilla.
Add flour mixture, beating until smooth.
Butter well a 2 1/2-quart tube pan.
Coat with a mixture of 1/3 cup ground walnuts and 3 tablespoons of sifted light brown sugar.
Pour batter in prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour. Let cake cool in pan 10 minutes and then turn out onto a wire rack and let cool completely.
Serves 12.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix corn flakes and butter; press lightly on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over corn flakes; top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cherry cola delight
directions: Drain fruit from cherries. Heat and add 2 packages jello and 2 Cokes. Add chipped cherries and nuts.
Let set in refrigerator until firm.
Serve on lettuce leaf if used as salad.
Squirt dollop of whipping cream on square if used as dessert.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix thoroughly sweet potatoes, eggs, sugar, vanilla and 1/2 cup butter.
Place
potato
mixture
in
greased pan.
Mix together brown sugar,
flour,
nuts
and 1 stick butter.
Pour over sweet potato mixture.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: enchirito
directions: Brown the hamburger; then drain and add taco seasoning.
Heat refried beans.
Grate cheeses.
Spoon to your liking, meat, refried beans, sauce and cheeses.
Fold up 4 corners of tortilla shell.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Put taco sauce and cheese on top.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: *Note:
I use dry buttermilk (using the reserved pineapple juice for the water).

title: crab imperial
directions: Combine crab, mayonnaise, egg and dry mustard in a bowl; mix well.
Spoon into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until brown.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Combine cooked rice, raisins, salt and 2 1/4 cups milk in a 2 to 3-quart saucepan over medium heat for 25 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine sugar, eggs and remaining 1/4 cup milk; add to pudding, stirring constantly until mixture thickens or coats spoon.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.

title: sugar-free brazil nut fruit cake
directions: Shell Brazil nuts by covering with water.
Bring to a boil. Boil 3 minutes.
Drain.
Cover with cold water; drain again.
Dry and shell.
(This makes shelling easier.)
Coarsely chop nuts.
In a large bowl, place nuts, dates and cherries; mix and add other fruits.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder over nuts and fruits. Mix with hands until nuts and fruits are coated.
Add vanilla to beaten eggs.
Stir into nut-fruit mixture until well mixed.
Turn into greased and waxed paper-lined 9 1/4 x 5 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Chop chicken into small pieces; mix with creamy chicken gravy and stir-fry.
Peel, chop and boil potatoes until tender.
Boil vegetables until tender.
Finely chop onion.
Mix all ingredients and place in pie pan.
Put top shell on pie and bake at 450° until golden brown.
Umm! Umm! Good!!

title: easy roast beef
directions: Place pot roast into crock-pot.
Pour jar of pepper rings and juice, too, and beer into pot.
Add bouillon cubes and onion slices.
Cook 5 to 6 hours.
Remove roast and let cool.
Remove bones and excess fat.
Chop with knife and fork until meat appears to be shredded.
Return to juice and serve on hard rolls.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; cook in double boiler until thickens. Add 2 teaspoons of vanilla and 1/2 bag of coconut.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: mandarin orange congealed salad
directions: Mix lightly and chill.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Combine sour cream, cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, green onion, garlic powder and season salt in bowl; mix well. Divide in 5 or 6 portions. Spread 1 portion on each tortilla. Top spread with beef deli slices in single layer. Roll to enclose filling. Enclose each tortilla in plastic wrap, twisting ends to seal tightly. Chill for several hours or overnight. Cut in 1/2 to 3/4-inch slices. Serve with salsa.

title: leek and lobster chowder
directions: Combine the broth, potatoes, leeks and mushrooms.
Cook over medium heat until potatoes are tender.
Add lobster meat, wine (optional), and whipping cream.
Reduce heat to low.
In small bowl, combine flour with the milk and beat until smooth.
Add to the chowder along with the Old Bay seasoning.
Simmer until flavors have blended.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Add flour, gelatin, water, oil and unbeaten eggs to cake mix. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed until smooth.
Add frozen strawberries and beat one minute.
Pour into a greased and floured 9-inch layer pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: seafood dill sauce
directions: Combine ingredients. Fine dipping sauce for seafood or vegetables.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10-15 minutes.
May use glaze of pineapple juice and confectioners sugar.
A tbsp. of lemon juice may be added to the drained pineapple to bring out it's flavor, if desired.
These keep fresh a long time.

title: bean soup
directions: Soak beans according to directions.
Bring to a boil and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add small amounts of water as needed to cook down to make a creamy soup.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix together the pudding, Cool Whip, 10x sugar and milk. Cream the butter and cream cheese and mix all together.
Blend the Oreos in a blender and then put some Oreos in the bottom of your flowerpot or bowl, then put some of the pudding mixture, then top with Oreos and decorate as you please.
Layer "dirt" and pudding in pot.
Decorate with silk flowers and gummy worms.
Be creative.

title: hamburger surprise
directions: Divide hamburger into four patties.
Place each patty in center of 10-inch square of foil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Place potato, carrots and onion on patty.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 375° or 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach with artichokes
directions: Place artichokes in buttered casserole.
Press spinach in sieve to remove moisture.
Add salt and pepper.
Arrange spinach over artichokes.
Beat cream cheese, butter and milk.
Spoon over spinach.
Add cheese.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered an additional 10 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: thick 'n cheesy vegetable pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Into lightly oiled 12-inch pizza pan, press dough to form crust; set aside.
In small bowl, blend vegetable recipe soup mix, oil, basil, garlic and pepper; spread evenly on dough.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Bake for 20 minutes, or until cheese is melted and crust is golden brown.
To serve, cut into wedges.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in round balls.
Use fork to pat cookies down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Dip fork in flour to keep from sticking.
Cook at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes, until lightly brown. Makes 8 dozen.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine ingredients and chill until ready to serve.
Use with assorted fresh fruit for a dip.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Put in microwave container and melt in microwave until caramels are melted.
Stir well. Cut up apples and dip and eat.

title: hamburger and doritos casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese and simmer 20 minutes.
Layer in casserole pan:
Doritos (slightly crushed), meat mixture and 1/2 of the grated cheese. Repeat.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and it is warm throughout.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in a skillet.
Add rice and onion; cook or fry in skillet approximately 10 minutes.
In large cake pan, layer approximately 1/2-inch finely chopped cabbage.
Gently spread the mixture you had in the skillet after you drain off the grease.
Do not stir the mixtures together.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shells. Bake at 300° until brown.

title: hot salad dressing and potato salad
directions: Mix sugar, dry mustard and flour together well.
Stir in egg. Add vinegar and milk.
Boil slowly; stir until thick.

title: union station chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; add the rest of the ingredients.
Roll into balls on ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: western macaroni bake
directions: Cook macaroni dinner as directed; set aside.
Brown ground beef, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper; drain.
Add tomato paste and 1 can water; mix.
Add corn and mix.
Add macaroni and cheese dinner and simmer until heated through.

title: mushrooms
directions: Cook mushrooms for 20 minutes.
Drain.
Combine first 5 ingredients to make marinade.
Pour over mushrooms.
Let stand several hours.

title: soda cracker cookie balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use large cookie sheet lined with foil. Grease foil.
Line sheet with whole soda crackers.
Bring to a boil 1 cup butter and 1 cup brown sugar and boil 2 1/2 minutes.
Pour mixture over crackers.
Put into oven and bake 5 to 10 minutes or until crackers are floating.
Remove from oven and spread 2 cups milk chocolate chips over top.
Spread like frosting as they melt. Sprinkle with finely chopped nuts.
Cool a little and cut in squares while still slightly warm (follow cracker lines).
Cut again when cool and chocolate is set.

title: grandma groff's tapioca pudding
directions: Put on to heat milk.
Add tapioca and stir frequently to prevent lumping.
Mix together and add beaten eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Cook, stirring constantly until it comes to a boil and thickens.
If too thick, add milk as desired.
Stir occasionally as it cools to prevent a thick skin from forming.
Making pudding from scratch is easy and delicious!

title: barbecue flavored meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except barbecue sauce. Shape mixture into loaf and place in a rectangular pan.
Spoon barbecue sauce over top.
Bake for 1
to 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Remove from pan.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin ring
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12-cup Bundt pan or angel food cake pan, 10 x 4-inches.
Beat all ingredients on low speed with hand mixer 30 seconds, beat on medium speed 3 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Spread in pan.
Bake 50 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely.

title: creamy broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain.
In medium saucepan combine broccoli and remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until cheese is melted and soup is hot.
Taste and adjust seasoning.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Grease cookie sheets. Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large mixer bowl, mix thoroughly butter, sugar and then the egg.
Then add molasses.
Sift dry ingredients and spices.
Add to batter and blend thoroughly.
Chill dough for an hour or two. Roll into balls the size of walnuts. Dip top in granulated sugar.
Place sugar side up, 3-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle each ball with a couple drops of water to make the top crinkle while it bakes. Bake 10 to 12 minutes just until set, not hard.
Yields 4 dozen (2 1/2-inch cookies).

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add taco seasoning and refried beans. Put on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan; spread.
Add taco sauce, sour cream and grated cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.
Serve with plain taco chips.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Combine chocolate and sugar.
Add cream and butter.
Boil to soft ball stage (234° to 238°).
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until mixture begins to thicken.
Place marshmallows in well buttered dish.
Pour mixture over marshmallows.
Cool and cut into squares.
Serve.

title: ou-e-goo-e cake
directions: Stir melted butter into cake mix and add 2 eggs.
Pat lightly into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine with mixer, cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar. Pour
this mixture over first and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve plain.

title: skillet zucchini and sausage
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet; lightly brown sausage.
Add onion, celery, green pepper, garlic, oregano and pepper.
Cook and stir until vegetables are almost tender.
Add zucchini and tomatoes; cook and stir until zucchini is just tender.
Sprinkle with seasoning and blend.
Yields 8 to 10 side dish servings.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and set aside.
Melt 1/2 stick butter in double boiler over low heat.
Add flour and milk and continue to cook slowly until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add mixture to macaroni and stir until completely mixed.
Grate cheese.
Set aside a small amount to sprinkle later on top of casserole.
Put layer of cheese in bottom of greased medium casserole dish.
Add remaining cheese and soup to macaroni mixture and pour into casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs and dot with pats of butter from remaining 1/2 stick of butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: honey refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix together in large bowl, water, honey and salt.
Blend in yeast.
Beat in egg, softened butter and 3 cups of flour for 2 minutes.
Gradually add 1 cup flour, beating hard.
Use hands to work in all remaining flour until smooth.
Grease top of dough.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoons onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with a small amount of sugar as they cool.

title: beer bread
directions: Combine Bisquick mix and sugar in bowl.
Add beer and mix. Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Let rise 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
While bread is still in pan, pour melted butter over bread; let stand 10 minutes.
Turn bread out on rack.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Drain.
Add cheese slices and butter to squash.
Add mushroom soup, beaten eggs and salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Pour into a greased casserole dish and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together 3 times and add alternately with milk and vanilla to creamed mixture.
Beat until smooth after each addition.
Fold in stiffly-beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased pans and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Cook
noodles
as directed on package, then put them in ice water.
Brown ground beef and onion in skillet;
drain and add spaghetti
sauce.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
In microwave or glass pan
x 9 x 2-inch), put layer of noodles, sauce and cheeses; repeat the layers.	Put in microwave and cook on High for 10 minutes or bake in oven for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crab imperial
directions: Mix all ingredients but bread crumbs together, making sure to beat eggs well.
This makes the crab dish light and fluffy.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix the crab meat, soup, garlic, milk, mayonnaise and spaghetti in a shallow 7 x 11-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake in convection oven on rack position 2 at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve hot.

title: peppered steak with rice
directions: Cut the steak into one-inch strips and place in skillet.
Pour a little soy sauce over each piece of steak.
Saute until brown, adding soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce as needed.
Place 3 cups of water in a pot and bring to a boil; add rice.
Cook the water out of rice and remove from stove.
Cut up the green pepper, onion, garlic and mushrooms into a desirable size.
Add to the steak in skillet.
Add some more soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce to cover the bottom of the skillet.
Also sprinkle some soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce on the vegetables.
Cook until steak strips are dark brown.
Serve over rice.
Also good with salad and garlic bread.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: grandma's dressing
directions: Amounts are approximate since Grandma never measured anything. This recipe applies to a roasting pan.
Make changes to fit pan.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients, then add the rest.
Mix well.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes 2 loaf pans.
Grease and flour pans.

title: shoepeg corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and chill for several hours.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Soften butter and stir in sugar. Add remaining ingredients. Cook 35 minutes at 350°.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large plastic bag, add all ingredients, seal bag and shake until all potatoes are covered. Let sit and marinate.
Empty into shallow baking dish or roast pan and bake, stirring several times to keep from burning.
Bake 40 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Add small amount of oil if needed while baking.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: oregon clam chowder
directions: Drain clams
and
reserve liquor.
Cut bacon into small shreds and cook
in
a
skillet
over medium heat until crisp. Add the onion
to
the
bacon
fat	and
brown
lightly.
Cook potatoes in 2	cups
boiling, salted water until just tender. Add the	bacon, onion,
clam liquor, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add half
and	half and bring to a boil.
Add ground clams and just heat through.

title: five pound fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk in large pot.
Boil 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add salt, butter, vanilla, cream of tartar and chocolate chips.
Stir well until mixed.
Add nuts. Pour into greased pan and cool at room temperature for 1 hour. Cool in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat.
Add onions and other ingredients.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: gravy baked pork chops
directions: Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper.
Brown meat in hot shortening.
Pour off drippings.
Put chops in a large baking pan. Around chops, pour mixture of soup, milk and water.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until chops are tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put the rice in a large pan.
Place the chicken on rice.
Salt and pepper.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture over top of chicken and cover tightly.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours. You don't have to check it.

title: old fashioned stack cake
directions: Sift 2 cups flour, ginger, soda, salt and baking powder together.
Beat shortening (or butter) and sugar until creamy. Beat in eggs and then add molasses.
Add 1/4 of dry ingredients at a time, alternately with buttermilk and remaining flour, a little at a time, until dough is stiff.
Use hands if necessary.
Heat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour 4 (9-inch) layer cake pans.
Bake each layer 10 to 12 minutes.
Stack with cooked, dried apples.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for 2 hours.
Serve with pumpernickel bread.
(Stir before serving.)

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients. Add oil, eggs, vanilla, nuts, carrots, pineapple and dates. Bake in layer or tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Combine flour, eggs, salt, pepper and garlic.
Mix thoroughly. Heat oil in large saute pan.
Dip pork in batter and cook 3 minutes (until brown).
Drain on paper towel.

title: angel pie
directions: Combine egg whites, salt and cream of tartar.
Beat until foamy.
Add sugar gradually, beating after each addition. Continue beating until mixture stands in stiff peaks.
Fold in nuts and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Spoon mixture into lightly greased 8-inch pie pan.
Spread into form of pie shell, building sides 1/2 inch above edge.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool.
Place chocolate and water in saucepan over low heat.
Stir until melted. Cool until thickened.
Add teaspoon of vanilla.
Fold in whipped cream.
Put into pie shell and chill 2 hours before serving.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bone.
Save about 1 quart broth. Cook celery and onion in broth.
Add 1 can of evaporated milk. Next add cooked rice, flour, and a pinch of baking soda.
Finally add chicken back to mixture and let simmer.
Using a larger amount of rice and flour makes a thicker consistency.

title: eggplant
directions: Slice eggplant	lengthwise
(1/4-inch slices), salt and let drain in
colander for 20 minutes. Rinse, pat dry, arrange on cookie sheet
and
lightly brush with olive oil (use pastry brush).
Broil until
light brown;	repeat on other side.
Set aside.
In a
heavy frypan saute onions in 2 tablespoons olive oil until limp.
Add
cloves
garlic,
chopped,
both
cans tomatoes, 2 tablespoons
basil,
dash
of sugar and salt.
Add any leftover wine in fridge and cook 15 to 20 minutes.	Cut up tomatoes if too
large.
In
an
attractive
shallow casserole dish, dribble olive oil
and 2 large spoonfuls of sauce on the bottom. Place one
layer
of eggplant covering bottom of dish. Place sliced Mozzarella
on each slice.
Top with fresh grated cheese and a dab of sauce.	Place remaining eggplant slices on top, matching sizes.
Top
with
remaining	sauce and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Cook
at
350° for 30 minutes or until it looks done.
Serve leftovers the following day in hoagie roll, delicious!	 (with	mayonnaise,
lettuce,
fresh
tomatoes	or plain).

title: chocolate icing
directions: Allow butter to soften, then add sugar and cocoa.
Pour a little milk in at a time until reaches desired thickness.
Mix with blender and add vanilla flavor.

title: squash soup
directions: Cook squash and put through a strainer.
Add other ingredients and simmer until ready to use.
Salt to taste.

title: cheese french loaf
directions: Mix together cheese and minced green onion.
Stir in enough mayonnaise to make mixture spreadable.
Season with garlic powder and pepper to taste.
Spread over each half of the bread to edges. Bake at 350° for 12 to 17 minutes until mixture bubbles.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix together well.
Blend into Cool Whip Lite or whipped D-Zerta topping.
Spread over cooled cake.
(Refrigerate leftover cake.)

title: tuna burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients. Spoon into 6 hot dog buns.
Bake on cookie sheets at 400° about 10 minutes. Serve piping hot.

title: baked sausage hash with eggs
directions: Cook potatoes, drain and pat dry with paper towel.
Remove the casings from sausage.
Cook sausage in a large skillet until browned, stirring to crumble; drain well and set aside.
Melt butter in skillet over medium heat.
Add potatoes and onion; saute until the onion is tender.
Add bell pepper and mushrooms; saute 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in reserved sausage.
Transfer mixture to 12 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: italian baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine bread crumbs and salad dressing mix.
Dip chicken in melted margarine, then in bread crumbs.
Place in greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.

title: cheese dip plus
directions: *Use real crab, either fresh or canned.
If you use canned, rinse and drain well to get rid of excess salt.

title: creole shrimp scampi
directions: In a 2 to 2 1/2 quart pot, cook shrimp, salt, pepper, oil and paprika for 10 minutes.
Then add the garlic, parsley, margarine, green peppers, onion, celery and bay leaf.
Cook until slightly tender, approximately 4 minutes.
Sprinkle the flour over the vegetables.
Add tomatoes and cook for 3 minutes longer.

title: crisco frosting
directions: Cream Crisco; add salt, sugar and water gradually alternating dry and liquid ingredients.
Beat in vanilla.
Frost
Polish Christmas cookies and dip in colored sugars.
Layer in box with waxed paper between layers.

title: beef leftover
directions: Fry onion in oil.
Add other ingredients except macaroni. Simmer 3 minutes.
Add macaroni.
Add sauce.
Place in casserole and bake at 350° until macaroni is done.
Start testing at 30 minutes or can be covered and cooked on stove top.

title: 7 can soup
directions: Combine, heat and eat.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Pour sugar, water and rum in mug.
Add butter.
Sprinkle on nutmeg.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and serve chilled.
Great with all raw vegetables.

title: banana coconut pie
directions: Whip cream.
Blend in sugar, nuts, salt and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with coconut.

title: light as a feather biscuits
directions: Mix the flour and baking soda.
Add enough emptyings to make a fairly soft dough.
Roll or pat out on floured board to 1/2-inch thick; cut into rounds.
Bake in preheated oven at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 24.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and place bacon on top.
Bake uncovered 1 1/2 to 2 hours in a 350° oven.

title: ansley's favorite punch
directions: Put sherbet in punch bowl.
Pour chilled pineapple juice over sherbet.
Last, pour in chilled 7-Up.

title: ham and noodle casserole
directions: Cook onions and green pepper in oil over low heat until transparent.
Add
noodles, tomatoes, ham, water, salt, pepper and paprika.
Simmer
for 10 minutes.
Stir in cheese and put into greased
quart
casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: festive swirls
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Remove 2 triangles from rolls.
Pat out perforation in dough.
Spread layer of cream cheese over rectangle.
Spread 1/4 of mushroom mixture over cheese.
Roll lengthwise.
Refrigerate.
Repeat with remaining dough.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need an 8-inch flowerpot.

title: rice dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients, except whipped topping.
Add and fold in the whipped topping last.
Chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Drain.
Mix other ingredients. Pour into buttered casserole; top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: frosting
directions: Cook milk, salt and flour until it pulls away from the sides of the pan.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients and beat with a hand mixer until creamy.
Add food coloring, if desired.

title: block party beans
directions: Brown hamburger and drain fat.
Add onion and celery. Cook until tender. Stir in soup, tomato paste and catsup. Simmer 20 minutes.
Put in large roaster. Add remaining ingredients and stir well. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 25.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Mix sour cream, marshmallows and coconut with wooden spoon. Stir in oranges and pineapple.
Chill overnight.
Add bananas right before serving.

title: matrimonial bars
directions: Mix together flour and soda.
In a medium bowl, cream the butter and sugar.
Stir in flour mixture until blended.
Add oats. (Dough will be crumbly.)

title: crawfish gumbo
directions: Make a roux with oil and flour.
Add onions.
Cook until clear in color.
Add tomato sauce.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add chicken broth, then bell pepper, garlic, salt and black and red peppers. Bring to a boil and cook for 20 minutes.
Add fat and simmer for 40 minutes or until the desired thickness is achieved.
Add crawfish and simmer for 15 minutes until done.
Sprinkle parsley and green onions on top.
Serves 8.

title: dark devils food cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together, add shortening and water. Beat 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes.
Bake in a 9 X 13-inch pan, or three 8- or 9-inch layers.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes for 9 X 13-inch, or 20 to 25 minutes for layers.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all canned fruits well.
Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: pancakes
directions: Whip egg and milk until frothy.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Do not overmix. Cook on medium heat.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Melt butter.
Add nuts and 1/2 cup sugar.
Stir-fry for 8 to 10 minutes.
In a bowl mix remaining ingredients.
Mix and stir pecans in.
Place on wax paper and cool.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Spray skillet with Pam.
Trim fat from chops.
Dust with flour and brown on one side.
Turn and brown on other side.
If necessary for better browning, add a little oil.
Spray casserole with Pam.
Place chops in casserole.
Place lemon slice on each chop, then add 1 tablespoon brown sugar on top of the lemon slice. Pour tomato sauce over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except pecan pieces; let set in refrigerator until firm.
Shape into a ball; roll in pecan pieces.

title: upside-down french toast
directions: *You may substitute peach or apples slices for pineapple.

title: banana split cake
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, melted 1 stick of butter.
Blend graham cracker crumbs and pat evenly.

title: quick fudge
directions: Put all ingredients in a saucepan over medium heat.
Stir until smooth and creamy.
Spread in a buttered 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Cool.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream together melted butter, sugar and flour.
Add yolks of eggs, beaten to a cream.
Then add juice and grated rind of lemon and milk.
Add whites of eggs, beaten to a froth.
Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry, unbaked and pour in filling.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.
Decrease heat to 350° and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, sugar, chips and egg yolks. In separate bowl, whip the egg whites until stiff and the 1/4 cup sugar to form stiff peaks.
Fold into the chocolate cream mixture. Put into graham cracker crust.
Keep refrigerated.

title: eggless chocolate cake
