directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Heat oven to 350°. Sift flour, sugar, soda, salt and cocoa together. Add coffee, oil, vinegar and vanilla to mixing bowl and beat until smooth using electric mixer. Bake 40 minutes or until toothpick comes clean. As soon as the cake is out of the oven, cover it with the icing. The warmth of the cake gives the icing a shiny glazed look.

title: all in one casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown beef; add soup and spices.
Place mixture into a casserole dish; top with mashed potato.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: georgia's pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sprinkle nuts into bowl with already beaten eggs.
Add sugar and stir slightly.
Add sugar and melted butter and stir just enough until well blended.
Pour into pie shell and bake until firm, approximately 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: gorp
directions: Mix together.
Good trail mix for hikes.
Makes a good high energy snack that is different in every bite!

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice.
Mix sugar and flour together, add pineapple juice.
Place pineapple in baking dish, pour juice mix. over pineapple.
Put grated cheese on top.
Crush crackers and mix with melted butter.
Place on top and bake at 350 degrees for 20 min.
Double for 9x13 pan.

title: graham cracker dessert
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon-colored, gradually add sugar and continue beating.
Stir in cracker crumbs, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Add walnuts and vanilla.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 40 minutes.
Cool.
Cut in squares and top with vanilla ice cream.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy. Add sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla. Mix lightly but well. Combine flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon. Add to zucchini mixture. Stir until well blended. Add pecans and pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: joe's favorite fresh pumpkin pie
directions: Pumpkin, cut and free of any seeds.
Boil until pumpkin is soft.
Scrape pumpkin meat from hull.
Measure 3 1/2 cups and heat in a heavy pan.
Stir frequently for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir together:
sugar, salt and spices.
Add to pumpkin. Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Add milk and cream; beat again.
Add pumpkin mixture and beat until smooth.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 400° approximately 50 minutes.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place oil in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add cake mix, eggs and water.
Stir with fork (mix will be lumpy).
Add 1 cup coconut.
Bake in oven for 25 minutes.
Punch holes in cake with fork.
Pour pina colada mix or cream of coconut over cake. Let cool.
Ice with Cool Whip.
Top with coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll in small balls and then in 4x sugar.
Store in tight tin.

title: orange pineapple cake
directions: Bake in 3 layers.

title: pizza dough
directions: Mix 1/2 cup warm water with yeast until dissolved, then add 3/4 cup warm water, sugar, salt and oleo.
Stir until dissolved. Add 2 cups flour; beat until smooth, then add 1 1/2 to 2 cups flour to make a soft dough.
Knead until smooth.
Grease outside and refrigerate until ready to use (15 minutes or longer).
Use cookie sheet instead of round pizza pan.
Top with sauce, Parmesan cheese and shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: low-fat fruit muffins
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Gently stir in yogurt and milk, blending just until dry ingredients are moist.
Gently fold in fruit.
Fill lightly greased muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 18 minutes.

title: date balls
directions: Mix sugar and melted margarine. Add egg and dates; cook over low heat until bubbly.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and Rice Krispies.
Let cool and roll into small balls.
Coat with coconut.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Combine ground beef and onion soup.
Spread onto oblong baking dish.
Spread Cheddar cheese soup over beef mixture.
Place enough Tater Tots on top to completely cover beef.
Sprinkle cheese over Tater Tots.
Bake until Tater Tots are golden brown.

title: crispy chicken drumsticks
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in blender.
Blend until texture resembles course meal.
Brush drumsticks with honey.
Dredge in oat mixture.
Place drumsticks on rack in a roasting pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Turn drumsticks, bake an additional 20 minutes or until chicken is tender and golden.
Transfer drumsticks to serving platter.

title: crispy chicken
directions: Place Grape-Nuts cereal in blender and blend until finely crushed.
Add salt, garlic salt, rosemary and pepper in bowl.
Add salad oil and stir until all crumbs are coated.
Dip chicken pieces in water; shake off excess water.
Dip chicken into cereal mixture, coating on all sides.
Place in ungreased shallow baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: squash pickles
directions: Sprinkle squash, onion and pepper mixture with salt to taste (approximately 1 1/2 teaspoons).
Cover with ice water and let stand 2 hours (or overnight) in refrigerator.
Mix other ingredients and bring to boil.
Add vegetable mixture but do not boil.
Allow to heat thoroughly but remove from heat as soon as they start to boil.
Fill hot, sterilized jars with hot pickles and add liquid to top.
Seal.

title: broiled grouper
directions: Place the grouper in a pan.
Spread mayonnaise all over top of grouper.
Sprinkle salt, pepper, onion salt and paprika on top. Pour wine in the bottom of pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Broil for 10 minutes after baked.

title: fruit punch
directions: Pour all the juices over the sherbet.

title: lemon squares
directions: Blend the first 3 ingredients together and press evenly into an ungreased 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Beat the remaining ingredients until light and fluffy; pour over hot crust.
Bake 20 minutes more; do not overbake.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 16 squares.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender, tear into bite size pieces in 2-quart casserole bowl.
Pour cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soups over bite size pieces of chicken.
Prepare Stove Top stuffing according to the directions.
Put on top of the casserole.
Bake at 350° until brown, 45 minutes to 1 hour until the soups are bubbling up through.

title: cheese ring
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into ring.
Fill center with strawberry preserves.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: yogurt snack
directions: Mix first two ingredients.
Sprinkle with wheat germ. Refrigerate.

title: meat loaf
directions: Allow 25 minutes per pound for ham weighing 10 to 12 pounds or 20 minutes per pound for a larger one.
Cover ham with cold water and soak for 12 hours in 2 different waters to which has been added 1 cup vinegar for each gallon of water.
Remove and rinse in cold water.
Place in large pot or roaster on top of stove.

Pour over ham 1 gallon water, 1 cup black molasses and 1 cup vinegar. Cover and allow to come to a rolling boil, then lower heat and let simmer slowly until skin can be easily removed (about 2 hours). Remove ham from solution; remove skin and puncture at intervals with an ice pick and insert very small slivers of garlic.
Score fat in diamonds; dot with cloves and place in a preheated oven at 300° for remaining cooking time, basting every 20 minutes with the juices that come from the ham.
Add water to pan as needed.
Allow to cool for a while before slicing.

title: cherry delight coke salad
directions: Drain cherries; add enough water to cherry juice to make 1 cup.
Bring cherry juice to a boil and remove from heat.
Add jello and dissolve.
Add Coca-Cola.
Place in the refrigerator. When mixture begins to thicken, add cherries and nuts.

title: topper stew
directions: Divide beef into 4 patties and brown on both sides.
Put browned beef patties in large skillet or pot with tight-fitting lid.
Sprinkle salt and pepper on beef.
Peel potatoes and slice in 2 pieces.
Slice onion in 4 slices.
On each beef patty, place 1 slice onion and 1 piece of potato.
Pour drained peas over this. Combine tomato soup and water.
Pour over top of mixture.
Simmer for 45 minutes until potatoes are done.

title: turkey-chili supper(microwave)
directions: In a 2 1/2-quart casserole, cook ground turkey, onion, garlic, chili powder and salt, covered, on High for 3 to 5 minutes until turkey is no longer pink, stirring to break up turkey.

title: goooood! cheese ball
directions: Chop corned beef and mix with chopped green onion tops only (do not use the onion).
Mash together with cream cheese and roll in chopped pecans.
Chill and serve.

title: chocolate cake
directions: *I make 4 thin layers; can make 3 layers.

title: hawaiian cheese spread
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed on electric mixer until fluffy, stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve on crackers or bread. Yields 3 1/4 cups.

title: butterball cookies
directions: Mix butter, margarine, powdered sugar and vanilla together very well.
Add flour to mixture.

title: holiday party cookies
directions: Blend butter and sugar.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients to butter, egg mixture. Stir in 1/2 cup of M&M candies.
Drop 3/4 of a teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Decorate top of cookies with more M&M candies.
Bake in a 375° oven for approximately 10 minutes or until golden brown. Makes approximately 72 cookies.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt oleo in 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle crumbs over oleo.
Pour Eagle Brand over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Bake 1/2 hour or until brown.
Cool. Cut into bars.

title: my perfect lunch
directions: Tell Mommy or Daddy I'm hungry.
Go to refrigerator.
Pick out hot dogs.
Climb up on my high chair.
Mommy or Daddy will bring hot dog and cut it up on my Pooh plate.
Eat hot dog.
When I'm finished, throw rest of hot dog on floor.
Hug Mommy or Daddy.

title: peanut taffy candy
directions: Boil together till small drop becomes hard in cold water. Pour into buttered pan or dish.

title: potato soup
directions: Put carrots, onion and celery into kettle; just cover with water (or chicken broth).
Add potatoes and simmer until vegetables are tender.

title: pear marmalade
directions: Cook until thick.
Pear slices will not break down, but will become translucent.
Fill hot jars with hot marmalade.
Process in a hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: one step spareribs
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan and add ribs.
Cook with cover off for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet & sour cabbage borscht
directions: Boil meat in water, add cabbage. When cabbage is soft, add other ingredients.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine sugar, salt, egg and shortening.
Cream; add milk, then flour, baking powder, soda, then choice of fruit.
Just blend in, don't beat, after creaming.
Fill muffin pans 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Fold in wet ingredients, saving hot water until last.
Mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Wrap in wax paper while still hot from oven.
Chill in refrigerator for approximately 3 hours.

title: barbara's summer squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

title: idaho dessert pudding
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in milk, vanilla, potatoes, nectarine and raisins.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish; set dish in a pan of hot water (water should be 1 inch deep).
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm or cold.

title: little cheesecakes
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Line 6 cups of a muffin pan with foil baking cups.
Finely crumble one cookie into each liner.
Blend cottage cheese, egg, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Pour into muffin cups.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Remove foil cups from pan.
Refrigerate until chilled. Top each with 1 teaspoon of preserves before serving.

title: swedish rice pudding(almond-rice cream)
directions: Heat butter, water and rice to boiling in Dutch oven.

Reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, until water is absorbed, about 12 minutes. Stir milk, sugar, salt and cinnamon stick into rice. Heat to boiling. Reduce heat, cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, until milk is absorbed, 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove cinnamon stick.
Cool.
Stir in chopped almonds.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pineapple juice, in a large Dutch oven; stir well.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally. Add pineapple juice; return to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve hot.
Yield: 3 quarts.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Blend cocoa and sugar.
Add butter in saucepan; cook over low heat until melted.
Add milk and cook to boil.
Serve over ice cream hot or cold.
Store in refrigerator.

title: garlic-dill pretzels
directions: Mix together in a bowl oil, garlic salt, dill weed, lemon pepper and Hidden Valley Ranch.
Break up pretzels and put in a gallon Ziplock bag.
Pour dressing mixture over pretzels and seal bag.
Marinate for 1 hour, turning in between to coat.
Then, put pretzels on cookie sheet and bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Stir after first 15 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken, then dice and combine all ingredients, except cheese and potato chips.
Place in well-greased casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese, then chips.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Serve hot and garnish with parsley.

title: voodoo pasta and sausage
directions: Cook fettuccine according to directions.
Drain then return pasta to pot.
Meanwhile, sprinkle sausage with blackening seasoning and place in a large skillet over medium heat and cook until lightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Stir in Alfredo sauce, Tabasco sauce and parsley and heat through.
Pour over pasta and toss until well coated.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook and stir onion and green pepper in oil in 10-inch skillet until onion is tender, about 3 minutes.
Stir in rice, water chestnuts, mushrooms and soy sauce.

title: spanish green beans
directions: If green beans are fresh, parboil about 10 minutes and drain. If canned beans, just drain.
In large saucepan, fry bacon until crisp; remove from pan.
Saute onion in bacon fat; add green pepper.
Add green beans to sauteed onion and green pepper.
Stir in stewed tomatoes, including juice, and catsup.
Simmer, uncovered, until juice is absorbed, about 1/2 hour.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes on bottom and up sides of an 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 10 minutes.
Brown beef.
Drain.
Place beef, broccoli, 1/2 of onions and the tomato in the potato shell.
Combine mushroom soup, milk, 1/2 cheese soup and black pepper.
Pour over beef mixture.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese soup and onions.
Bake, uncovered, for 2 to 3 minutes longer.

title: skillet turkey stew(serves 2)
directions: Brown turkey, with onions and green pepper in a nonstick skillet.
Add remaining ingredients, except yogurt and rice or noodles.
Cover and cook 20 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in yogurt.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Approximately 390 calories per serving.

title: mr. no-bake cookies
directions: In a saucepan, combine the margarine, cocoa, sugar and milk. Bring the mixture to a boil and boil for 1 minute (see note). Remove from the burner and add the remaining ingredients.
Drop from a spoon onto waxed paper.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: herb punch
directions: Mix leaves, sugar and water in large pan.
Simmer 10 minutes. Add tea bags and boiling water.
Cool, then remove tea bags.
Add orange juice; pour over ice.

title: parfait pie
directions: Prepare pastry shell.
In saucepan, mix gelatin with grapefruit juice.
Let stand 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until gelatin is completely dissolved; remove from heat.
Stir in ice cream; chill, stirring occasionally until mixture is consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Beat egg whites until peaks form; slowly add sugar and beat until stiff.
Pour in gelatin mixture, grapefruit sections and pecans.
Pour into shell.
Garnish with grapefruit, pecans and whipped cream.

title: freezer corn
directions: Mix all together.
Bring to a boil and simmer 15 minutes (cool a little).
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Bag or box the next day.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Add to shortening; work into a meal.
Put vinegar and egg into a 1 cup measure and add cold water to fill to 1 cup line.
Add to other ingredients and work dough until it comes off hands.
Form into balls.
Roll dough out on floured surface with floured rolling pin.
Leftover dough can be stored in refrigerator for 2 days, otherwise freeze.
Take dough out of freezer the night before you need it and place in refrigerator.

title: butter cinnamon cake
directions: Mix together cake mix and pudding mix.
Add water, oil, eggs and flavoring. Beat with mixer until well blended.
Mix sugar and cinnamon. Set aside.
Pour half of the batter into a well-greased and floured tube pan. Sprinkle half of the cinnamon and sugar mixture over batter.
Add rest of batter.
Sprinkle rest of cinnamon and sugar on top. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let cool in pan. Remove and glaze with confectioners sugar.

title: baked green beans and mushrooms(from 1975 edition)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: rachel's famous rolls
directions: Pour 1 cup boiling water over shortening, sugar and salt.
Let shortening melt.
Set aside.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into small pieces.
Salt and pepper; put into paper bag with flour and shake until all is covered.
Fry until tender in butter.
I use half butter and half cooking oil.
When all of steak is fried, put onion which has been cut into small pieces, in pan and saute until tender.
Add water, then soup and mushrooms.
Put steak in and simmer 30 minutes.
Add sour cream and let simmer about 5 more minutes.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: italian pizzelle(from 1975 edition)
directions: Beat eggs, adding sugar gradually.
Beat until smooth.
Add cooled, melted margarine and vanilla or anise.
Sift flour and baking powder and add to egg mixture.
Dough will be sticky enough to be dropped by spoon.
Makes 60.

title: jim's chili
directions: Dice onion and bell pepper; cook with the ground beef.
Drain and add chili mix and ketchup.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add pinto beans and sugar.

title: bill's favorite chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs and beat. Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with buttermilk.
Pour into greased and floured loaf cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb preserves
directions: Combine rhubarb, pineapple and sugar.
Place over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Cook over medium heat until clear and thick, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add jello.

title: squash soup
directions: Cover squash with broth.
Add tarragon and parsley and cook until tender.
Saute onions and garlic in butter.
Add sherry; cook until soft.
Add flour to onions.
Mix well.
Whisk squash mixture until smooth.
Add onion mixture to squash and stir. Simmer until mixture is slightly thickened.
Puree in blender or food processor.
Season to taste, adding the celery salt first and then the salt and pepper.
Add cream shortly before serving.

title: zucchini squash relish
directions: Cook all together for 30 minutes (less time for very young squash).
Makes 7 to 8 pints.

title: cheese broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon oil.
Chop broccoli and steam separately.
Add milk and flour to onion and garlic to make a roux.
Add more milk if needed.
Add broccoli and Velveeta cheese.
Cook until cheese melts over low heat, stirring often. Serve with cornbread or rolls.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off tops of green peppers; remove seeds and membranes. Mix beef, then let simmer.

title: delicious dirt
directions: Crush cookies in Baggies.
Mix cream cheese, margarine and sugar in separate bowl.
Mix puddings, milk and Cool Whip in second bowl.
Add cream cheese mixture to pudding mixture.
Layer cookie crumbs with cream cheese mixture.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw spinach.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a 2-quart casserole.
Cook for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: caramel morsel bars
directions: Melt caramels in saucepan with water over low heat.
Stir frequently until sauce is smooth.
Pour over cereal and nuts. Toss until well coated.
With greased fingers, press mixture into greased 13 x 9 baking pan.
Sprinkle morsels on top.
Place in 200° oven for 5 minutes or until morsels soften.
Spread softened morsels until blended to form a frosting.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Grease bottom only of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle marshmallows over bottom.
Combine strawberries and syrup with DRY jello and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients until well blended and pour over marshmallows.
Then pour strawberry mixture evenly over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.
Usually comes out brown.

title: apple dumplins
directions: Peel apples and cut into 8 pieces each. Cook in microwave for 2 minutes. Roll 1 piece of apple up in a crescent roll (may sprinkle with cinnamon if you like). Place in 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt oleo with sugar and pour over rolls. Then pour Mt. Dew over rolls. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Then cover lightly and bake 10 minutes more.

title: crazy mary's chili(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Combine chili powder, salt and pepper in cup; set aside.
Melt butter in heavy large saucepan over medium heat.
Add mushrooms, onion and celery and cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is transparent (about 10 minutes).
Add ground beef and 1/2 of chili powder mixture.
Cook, breaking up meat with fork, until brown. Stir in remaining chili powder mixture, tomatoes, water, sugar and Worcestershire.
Cover partially and simmer 15 minutes.
Add beans and simmer 10 more minutes.
Sprinkle each bowlful with 1 tablespoon Cheddar cheese and broil until cheese melts.
Top with dollop of sour cream.

title: stollen christmas bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make 2 rolls. Bake on cookie sheet.
Put butter on top. Roll in sugar.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: grape conserve
directions: Wash and stem grapes.
With your fingers, squeeze out pulp skins in saucepan, saving the skins. Cool pulp about 5 minutes to soften and then press through a strainer to remove seeds.
Add pulp to skins and boil 5 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Blend sugar and oleo together.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour and cocoa.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch Pyrex.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Melt butter; add dry ingredients.
Add Milnot and mix well. Cook in microwave on Medium until sugar has dissolved.
May also cook in double boiler.
Great served on ice cream.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook onion until tender, blend in flour, salt and broth.
Cook until bubbly.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into pie crust. Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: beef rouladen
directions: In skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove and crumble. Pound round steak.
Spread each with 1 teaspoon mustard.
Place 2 pieces of pickle and 4 pieces carrots across the narrow end; sprinkle with 2 teaspoons onion.
Starting at the narrow end, roll up.
Tuck in ends; fasten with toothpicks or skewers.
Brown roll-ups in drippings; pour off fat.
Stir in soup, celery, parsnips and parsley.
Cover; cook over low heat for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Thin with water if desired.
Serve with mashed potatoes.
Garnish with bacon.
Makes 6 servings.

title: nut-raisin bars
directions: Sift dry ingredients 3 times.
Mix white and brown sugars. Add shortening; stir to blend well.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix to smooth batter.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add chopped nuts and raisins; blend well.
Spread dough in a thin layer in a 2 x 9 x 13-inch baking pan (well-greased and floured).
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool 5 minutes; cut into bars.
This is a quick, easy, "stand-by" recipe.

title: skillet apple cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and sugar in one bowl.
Mix oil, egg, apples, nuts and vanilla in separate bowl.
Mix together in greased iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake 2 layer cake as directed.
To assemble in punch bowl, place one layer cake in bottom of bowl.
Prepare instant pudding; use half on first layer.
Slice bananas over pudding.
Pour half of pineapple (juice and all) over bananas.
Put strawberries 1/4-inch deep over pineapple.
Top with whipped topping.
Repeat layers. Top with pecan halves and refrigerate.
This is a very showy dessert.

title: colleen's easy pralines
directions: Line 9 x 3-inch greased baking pan with graham crackers. Boil 1/2 cup butter and brown sugar until well mixed.
Remove from heat; add nuts.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Slice and serve. Kids luv it!

title: caramel bars
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, oatmeal, brown sugar and butter.
Mix well.
Pat into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut 40 biscuits into quarters and roll into mixture of sugar and cinnamon. Place in greased tube pan and layer with raisins, nuts and/or coconut. Pour mixture of brown sugar and butter over and cook for 45 minutes at 350°. Cool and remove from pan when cool.

title: home fries recipe
directions: Place 2 teaspoons of vegetable oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.
Add the potatoes and other vegetables. Stir.
Mix fairly often to prevent sticking.
Do not cover the mix; it will get soggy.
Heat until the potatoes are soft.

title: hurry up cake
directions: Put back into oven until frosting bubbles.
Use a 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions on package.
Chill. Place in large bowl.
Pour on dressing and Salad Delight.
Toss. Add diced pepper, diced onion, diced tomato and diced or sliced cucumber.
Mix well.
Keep refrigerated.

title: orange salad
directions: Add the sherbet to the Jell-O.
Stir and chill in refrigerator until partially set.
Add the oranges and Cool Whip.
Mix together and chill until well set. Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Break tortilla chips and place on bottom of greased casserole (3-quart).
Mix soups, Pet milk, chopped onion, water and green chilies all together.
Pour over tortilla chips, then layer chicken and cheese, then chips, soup, chicken and cheese again; makes 2 layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes before cutting, then enjoy!

title: granny chicken
directions: Arrange chicken parts in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the soups and water together well; pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until chicken is completely cooked.
Serve over rice.

title: orange bavarian
directions: Mix together milk, sugar, egg yolks, self-rising flour and salt in a heavy saucepan.
Cook until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin and orange juice concentrate.
Beat 4 egg whites until stiff. Fold into 1/2 of the whipped topping.
Then fold this into the cooled, cooked mixture.

title: microwave baked beans
directions: Place cubed bacon and onion in shallow microwave dish or glass bowl.
Cook on High until bacon starts to crisp and onion is transparent.
Place pork and beans, partially drained, into large casserole dish.
Add bacon, onion and grease to beans along with sugar and mustard.
Stir to mix well.
Microwave on High 14 minutes, stirring and turning 1/2 turn after 7 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: pfeffernuss
directions: Combine all ingredients except flour.
Add enough flour, a bit at a time, to make a very stiff dough.
Let stand overnight.
Roll into ropes about 1/2 to 3/4-inch in diameter.
Cut into 1/2 to 3/4-inch pieces.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: macaroni with meat sauce
directions: Cook the macaroni according to package directions, omitting the salt; drain and set aside.
Spray the inside of a 4-quart pot with nonstick vegetable cooking spray and place over high heat.
Add the onions, bell pepper and celery.
Saute for 5 minutes, stirring constantly to prevent burning.
Add the beef and the next 7 ingredients.
Cook, stirring, for 15 minutes.
Then stir in the stock, tomato paste and tomatoes.
Cover, reduce the heat and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring often.
Add the macaroni and cook for 8 minutes; remove from the heat.
Stir in the parsley and let stand for 10 minutes, allowing the macaroni to absorb the meat flavor.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix together oats and buttermilk.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine celery, onion and broccoli and cook.
Cook rice. Combine rice and cooked vegetables.
Fold in cream of chicken soup. Pour into casserole.
Add butter to top of ingredients.
Pour Cheez Whiz over top.
Heat in oven until bubbly at 350°.

title: quick beef soup
directions: Cook beef, onion and garlic in large saucepan over medium-high heat until beef is brown, stirring to separate meat; drain fat. Puree tomatoes with juice in covered blender or food processor. Add tomatoes, water, bouillon cubes and pepper to meat mixture. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low.
Simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes.
Add orzo and vegetables.
Simmer 15 minutes more.

title: nutty pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add butter.
Pack mixture firmly into 2-3 round pans.
Bake at 350°F until brown.

title: oklahoma cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix flour, sugar and soda.
Add 2 beaten eggs and crushed pineapple (do not drain).
Mix all ingredients (except last 5) together.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch (Pam sprayed) pan. Bake 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: hot chicken sticks
directions: You will need 24 (6-inch) skewers.
Soak in water 20 minutes. This prevents burning.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Cut up apples and dip in pineapple juice.
(The pineapple juice will keep the apples from turning dark.)
Mix apple cubes, walnuts, raisins, coconut, and marshmallows in bowl.
Add Miracle Whip and mix until moisten.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: garden cheese salad
directions: Cut vegetables into small pieces.
Onions need to be chopped fine.
Mix altogether in medium mixing bowl.
Other fresh vegetables may be substituted.
Chives, when in season, taste great instead of the onions.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Slit hots dogs lengthwise and put cheese slices in middle. Wrap dough around the hot dogs.
Slide onto sticks lengthwise. Cook over coals until done.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together in small bowl.
Cut one tube of biscuits in quarters and toss in large Tupperware bowl.
Add some cinnamon and sugar mixture to biscuits and shake.
Repeat with remaining tubes of biscuits and cinnamon.
Layer pieces in a buttered tube pan, rectangle pan or 2 separate round pans.

title: mother's potato salad dressing
directions: Place sugar, vinegar and butter in heavy pan; let come to a boil.
Blend together remaining ingredients and add to the boiling mixture.
Stir until it comes to a hard boil.
Take from heat; add some salad dressing.
Keeps well in refrigerator.
Use this dressing with chopped potatoes, celery, onion and eggs.

title: easy cheese and broccoli soup
directions: Saute chopped onion in the margarine until tender and transparent.
Add flour and cook until it thickens.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Add to flour mixture, stirring to mix thoroughly.
Add the frozen broccoli and cook for 10 minutes.
Then add the Velveeta cheese (in cubes).
When cheese is melted, add salt and pepper to taste and serve.

title: sweet biscuits
directions: Sift together all-purpose flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in margarine with fork until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Add milk and blend only until flour is moistened and dough pulls
away from sides of bowl.
Can turn out and knead dough.
Roll it and cut it with biscuit cutter or can use drop method.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 475° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and put in a casserole dish.

title: fried okra
directions: Wash okra.
Cut into slices.
Don't use stem or tip.
Mix together egg and milk.
Add to okra and mix well, coating all okra.
Put meal and flour into a large bowl or gallon Ziploc bag. Add salt and pepper and mix or shake well.
Add okra to batter and mix well until coated or seal bag and shake well until coated. Fry in about 1-inch of oil until brown on all sides.
Drain well on paper towel.

title: starlight mint surprises
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; set aside.
Cream butter and sugars.
Blend into creamed mixture, eggs, water and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Cut Andes candies in half.
Enclose each piece of candy in about 1 tablespoon of chilled dough.
Place on greased cookie baking sheet about 2 inches apart.
Can be topped with nuts or colored sugars.
Other flavors of Andes candies may be used. Bake in 325° oven 10 to 12 minutes.

title: new magic spice cake
directions: Measure all ingredients in mixing bowl and beat 2 minutes. Add 3/4 cup eggs (about 3 medium).
Beat 2 minutes more.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken and bow ties
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid.
In skillet, add reserved liquid and boil 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, chicken, onion, mushrooms, garlic and rosemary.
Cook 6 minutes or until chicken is done, stirring occasionally.
Toss with pasta and cheese.
Garnish with chopped parsley and serve with additional cheese, if desired.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Place unrolled crescents on large cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes.
Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, dressing and mayonnaise to make a creamy spread.
Spread on rolls. Crumble veggies over cream cheese mixture.
Top with shredded cheese.
Serve.

title: swedish pot roast(pressure cooker)
directions: Combine nutmeg, cinnamon, ginger, salt and pepper.
Rub into meat.
Heat cooker.
Add oil and brown meat on both sides.
Add onion, garlic and brown sugar dissolved in wine, water and bay leaves.
Close cover securely.
Cook 35 minutes with pressure regulator or vent pipe.

title: confetti bean soup
directions: Rinse beans with running cold water and discard any stones or shriveled beans.
In a 5-quart Dutch oven over high heat, heat beans and 9 cups water to boiling; cook 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand 1 hour.
Drain and rinse beans.

Return beans to Dutch oven; add next 8 ingredients and 8 cups of water. Over high heat, heat to boiling; reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 2 hours or until beans are tender, stirring occasionally. Remove ham hocks; cut meat into small pieces and return to soup. Add the can of tomatoes with its liquid; over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cook, uncovered, 1 hour longer, stirring to break up tomatoes.
Discard bay leaf.
Serves 10-12.

title: pork scallopini
directions: *Slice pork into thin strips; work best if slightly frozen.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Form into balls.
Roll in sugar. Flatten with fork for Peanut Blossoms.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 375° or until brown.

title: grapefruit salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 9 tablespoons of cold water.
Dissolve sugar in 1 cup boiling water.
Add gelatin to mixture while still hot.
Cool; add 3 cups of grapefruit sections and 1 cup juice. Put 1/2 of mixture into bowl and let congeal in refrigerator. Make sure remaining mixture doesn't congeal.
Soften cream cheese (add milk, if necessary).
Add chopped nuts.
Spread evenly on first layer when it has congealed, then add remaining mixture. Add maraschino cherries for color.

title: icebox cake
directions: Beat whipping cream with sugar, vanilla and cocoa.
When firm, alternate graham crackers with whipped cream mixture on a platter, laying crackers on their side like dominos.
When there is about 1/4 of the whipped cream mixture remaining, coat sides and top with cream.

title: whole wheat pancakes
directions: Put all dry ingredients in a bowl; stir together.
Add buttermilk; stir with fork.
If you want a thinner batter, add more buttermilk.
Add corn oil and stir.
Fry in electric skillet as you would any other pancakes.

title: beef stew
directions: Put into roaster as listed; cover.
Put into oven.
Cook at 250° for about 4 hours.
(Do not open lid while cooking.)

title: butterscotch rolls
directions: Melt butter or margarine and add to warm milk.
Add yeast, sugar and eggs to milk mixture.
Mix well.
Add flour and salt to milk and yeast mixture.
Mix into soft dough.
Place in bowl greased with oil and cover.
Let rise in refrigerator for 3 hours. Then roll dough into an oblong shape about 1/4 inch thick and spread with melted butter or margarine.
Cover with cinnamon. Roll into long roll and cut into 1-inch slices.

title: dilly dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with veggies or chips.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add 2 well beaten eggs and crumble mixture.
Fold in large can of fruit cocktail, undrained.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan (ungreased).
Cover with brown sugar and nut mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rita's p.b.  cookie
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: fried chicken
directions: Soak chicken overnight in salt water.
Combine cream and eggs in shallow dish.
In a plastic bag, combine flour, salt, and pepper.
Dip chicken in egg mixture; place in bag.
Shake bag to coat chicken with flour.
Cook in hot oil until browned, turning to brown both sides.
Cover and cook 25 minutes.
Uncover and cook an additional 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.

title: meat pie
directions: Saute onion and garlic in a little oil.
Add ground beef and cook until browned.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle flour over meat and stir well.
Add soup and pour into pie shells. Cover with cooked mashed potatoes and sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: peach crumble pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add water and corn syrup. Blend well; add peaches.
Bring to boil and cook one minute.
Let cool.
Add lemon juice.
Pour filling into pastry shell.
Sprinkle with Crumble Topping.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 425°.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Melt 1 stick butter and add saltines.
Press into 9-inch pie plate.
Melt remaining butter in skillet and add onions.
Cook over medium heat until tender, but not brown, about 15 minutes. Put into pie shell.
Heat milk.
Beat eggs and add to milk with salt and pepper.
Heat until hot, but do not boil.
Pour over onions.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve hot, cut into wedges.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs together.
Fold sour cream and vanilla carefully into creamed mixture.
Then fold in sifted dry ingredients.
Place 1/4 of batter into greased and flour large angel food tube pan (be sure to grease the tube, too).
Spread over half of the Topping, then balance of batter.
Finish with Topping.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.
Sprinkle while warm with powdered sugar.

title: cake glaze
directions: Mix butter and buttermilk together in saucepan.
Let come to a boil and add sugar.
Cook until it comes to a hard boil.
Wait for 5 minutes before placing on cake.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar and corn syrup.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Let cool slightly. Add eggs, vanilla and salt to mixture.
Mix well.
Pour filling into unbaked pie shell, and top with pecans.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: potato-cheese casserole
directions: Prepare white sauce, remove from heat and add cheese and stir until it has melted and add chives.
Place potatoes in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour sauce over potatoes.
Mix bread crumbs and melted butter, then sprinkle crumbs over potatoes.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until lightly browned in oven at 350°.
